SAM: So I'll sing (singing) It's a sick house,
it's mighty mighty, it's letting it all hang--

00:14:04.290 --> 00:14:05.369
that's it.

00:14:05.369 --> 00:14:10.038
MATT: You guys are mildly confused, but as he
picks up the items, you can see the door sets off

00:14:10.038 --> 00:14:16.186
this small spark of white energy that glistens in
the air, hovers, and then creates a somewhat

00:14:16.186 --> 00:14:20.490
shimmering doorway, just standing in the center of
the space in front of you.

00:14:20.490 --> 00:14:23.821
LAURA: What?

00:14:23.821 --> 00:14:31.465
SAM: Would you like to come into my place? It's a
little modest shack that I've been working on.

00:14:31.465 --> 00:14:33.340
LAURA: Is this a teleport sort of--

00:14:33.340 --> 00:14:34.359
TRAVIS: It's a door.

00:14:34.359 --> 00:14:35.437
MARISHA: Is this a joke?

00:14:35.437 --> 00:14:37.253
TALIESIN: There's nothing on the other side of it,
is there?

00:14:37.253 --> 00:14:43.263
SAM: No, no, it's a place where we can rest for
the evening, totally safe and comfortable. It's on

00:14:43.263 --> 00:14:48.276
a slightly different plane from ours, so nothing
can actually hurt us there or get to us.

00:14:48.276 --> 00:14:54.320
LAURA: Is it that fire plane where we just--
there's no dragons in that plane?

00:14:54.320 --> 00:15:01.696
SAM: I haven't checked in a while. Actually, this
is my first time doing this.

00:15:01.696 --> 00:15:05.623
TRAVIS: We should send somebody ahead first to
check. Vax, are you up to the bit?

00:15:05.623 --> 00:15:08.745
LIAM: Am I up to what? What was that, Grog?

00:15:08.745 --> 00:15:11.296
SAM: It's totally safe, don't worry, don't worry.

00:15:11.296 --> 00:15:15.094
LIAM: As long as you're not going to whip out the
cube, then lead the way.

00:15:15.094 --> 00:15:19.354
SAM: How many people can fit in there? It's pretty
big.

00:15:19.354 --> 00:15:26.283
MATT: Any creature you designate when you cast the
spell to enter. So you could say the entire Pyrah

00:15:26.283 --> 00:15:27.585
tribe if you wanted.

00:15:27.585 --> 00:15:28.461
LAURA: What?

00:15:28.461 --> 00:15:29.498
SAM: Everybody.

00:15:29.498 --> 00:15:30.907
MATT: Everybody in the group, or the Pyrah?

00:15:30.907 --> 00:15:32.346
SAM: How many are there?

00:15:32.346 --> 00:15:36.422
MATT: Here, there's close to 35, including the
Zephrah.

00:15:36.422 --> 00:15:42.090
LAURA: Wait, could you technically do this with
any refugees? I mean, where do they go when you

00:15:42.123 --> 00:15:43.754
make the door go away?

00:15:43.754 --> 00:15:50.865
SAM: This is my place, all right? I don't want any
riffraff in there. Listen, there's a guest list,

00:15:50.865 --> 00:15:52.688
there's a guy at the door--

00:15:52.688 --> 00:15:56.536
TALIESIN: I can solve this really quickly. Are any
of the Pyrah tribe hot?

00:15:56.536 --> 00:15:59.713
LAURA: Like, attractive?

00:15:59.713 --> 00:16:00.917
TALIESIN: Attractive.

00:16:00.917 --> 00:16:02.118
LAURA: They're all hot.

00:16:02.118 --> 00:16:09.760
MATT: Through the soot and ash and the rather
somber atmosphere here that paints them as a

00:16:09.805 --> 00:16:14.267
people that are the survivors of a horrible
calamity, beyond that, there's probably a few that

00:16:14.267 --> 00:16:16.353
you'd consider attractive, sure, if you're that
kind of person.

00:16:16.353 --> 00:16:18.482
TALIESIN: That one over there was looking at you,
I saw her wink at you earlier.

00:16:18.482 --> 00:16:19.462
SAM: Oh, really?

00:16:19.462 --> 00:16:20.388
TALIESIN: You should impress her.

00:16:20.388 --> 00:16:22.478
SAM: The one with her face just sheared off?

00:16:22.478 --> 00:16:23.710
TALIESIN: Yeah, why not?

00:16:23.710 --> 00:16:32.051
SAM: All right. Not really my type. I like
full-faced people, but I'll take it, I'll take my

00:16:32.051 --> 00:16:33.277
chance.

00:16:33.277 --> 00:16:34.655
TALIESIN: I think that's big of you.

00:16:34.655 --> 00:16:35.771
LAURA: So terrible.

00:16:35.771 --> 00:16:39.950
SAM: You know, if there's anyone from your
immediate family that you'd like to give lodging

00:16:39.950 --> 00:16:44.201
to tonight-- okay, we'll take them all, we'll take
them all in. We'll take them all in.

00:16:44.201 --> 00:16:47.987
MARISHA: Sure. Do you want to tell them? It is
your humble abode.

00:16:47.987 --> 00:16:49.262
SAM: Ashari people!

00:16:49.262 --> 00:16:50.494
MARISHA: All right.

00:16:50.494 --> 00:16:53.963
MATT: You see some of them stop and drop the rocks
they're currently holding and building some of

00:16:53.963 --> 00:16:55.231
these small shelters.

00:16:55.231 --> 00:17:00.440
SAM: Don't worry about your shelter for tonight.
Let Scanlan Shorthalt take care of you, in every

00:17:00.440 --> 00:17:06.814
way, shape, and form imaginable. Come with me
through this weird magic door into another plane.

00:17:06.814 --> 00:17:09.753
Believe me, it's going to be okay.

00:17:09.753 --> 00:17:15.967
MATT: They all look at each other with a strange
glance and continue building their current

00:17:15.967 --> 00:17:16.949
shelters.

00:17:16.949 --> 00:17:18.668
LAURA: Why the fuck not? And I walk on through.

00:17:18.668 --> 00:17:23.337
MATT: Okay. You open the door, and as you grab it,
it is a solid door, and the handle spins, you look

00:17:23.337 --> 00:17:33.682
inside, and within you see an incredibly lush
foyer to a grand mansion, a 25-, 30-foot ceiling

00:17:33.682 --> 00:17:39.048
made of marble and dark woods, you see a two-part
staircase that splits off onto a second-tier

00:17:39.048 --> 00:17:44.152
floor, you hear soft music playing in the
distance, and immediately you see two somewhat

00:17:44.152 --> 00:17:48.783
ethereal servants come down, dressed as a butler
and a maid, they come down, with an echoing voice

00:17:48.783 --> 00:17:51.306
that say, "How might we be of service?"

00:17:51.306 --> 00:17:52.713
LAURA: What the fuck.

00:17:52.713 --> 00:17:58.799
SAM: Hi. I step in after her. Yes, I've made some
changes to the place. Living quarters are

00:17:58.799 --> 00:18:04.505
upstairs, there's a kitchen, parlor, game room
over there, billiards, all sorts of stuff. We have

00:18:04.505 --> 00:18:11.432
a music room. There are a hundred attendants who
can wait on us. I've assigned some of them

00:18:11.432 --> 00:18:16.906
specific jobs. Five are going to play music for us
wherever we want, especially during our meals.

00:18:16.906 --> 00:18:19.324
MATT: "Let me take your things, Master."

00:18:19.324 --> 00:18:20.523
SAM: Oh, yes, yes, here.

00:18:20.523 --> 00:18:24.923
TRAVIS: I come inside and I see the ethereal
things, I'm like, ghosts! And I take Craven Edge

00:18:24.923 --> 00:18:27.546
and I swing at the ethereal sumbitch!

00:18:27.546 --> 00:18:34.502
SAM: Are you attacking my attendants?

00:18:34.502 --> 00:18:36.757
TRAVIS: No, the ghosts in your house!

00:18:36.757 --> 00:18:38.538
SAM: They're my people!

00:18:38.538 --> 00:18:39.397
TRAVIS: What?

00:18:39.397 --> 00:18:42.336
MATT: By the time you go to stop him, three of the
servants that have grabbed a few of your

00:18:42.336 --> 00:18:47.025
belongings and been carrying away, are swung at,
Craven Edge passing through, and their energy

00:18:47.025 --> 00:18:51.054
dispersing, and their contents of whatever they're
carrying drop and clink to the ground.

00:18:51.054 --> 00:18:52.103
LAURA: No!

00:18:52.103 --> 00:18:53.487
SAM: Jesus Christ--

00:18:53.487 --> 00:18:54.536
TRAVIS: Thank god I'm here.

00:18:54.536 --> 00:19:00.207
SAM: Grog, Grog, easy. Easy. They're not ghosts,
they're not ghosts. They are supernatural

00:19:00.207 --> 00:19:07.872
spirits-- some would say ghosts-- that are good,
they serve us, they serve me--

00:19:07.872 --> 00:19:10.791
LAURA: Wait, do you pay them or do they just work for
you?

00:19:10.791 --> 00:19:12.971
SAM: They're slave ghosts.

00:19:12.971 --> 00:19:15.280
LAURA: This is terrible. Scanlan!

00:19:15.280 --> 00:19:17.441
SAM: Well, no, they like it for some reason.

00:19:17.441 --> 00:19:18.354
LAURA: Are you sure?

00:19:18.354 --> 00:19:21.014
SAM: I can command them to do literally anything
and they like it.

00:19:21.014 --> 00:19:22.039
LAURA: Have you asked them?

00:19:22.039 --> 00:19:24.758
SAM: Watch this. Watch this. I call one over. You
there, you there.

00:19:24.758 --> 00:19:31.276
MATT: This maid comes over, a plumper older woman,
no feet, just drifting along with this path of

00:19:31.276 --> 00:19:34.087
mist behind her. "Yes, Master?"

00:19:34.087 --> 00:19:35.874
SAM: Can you please braid my chest hair?

00:19:35.874 --> 00:19:37.779
MATT: "But of course, Master."

00:19:37.779 --> 00:19:39.466
SAM: Do you like this job?

00:19:39.466 --> 00:19:41.755
MATT: "It is my purpose, Master."

00:19:41.755 --> 00:19:43.511
SAM: See? This is what I'm telling you.

00:19:43.511 --> 00:19:45.657
LAURA: Your purpose, do you enjoy your purpose?

00:19:45.657 --> 00:19:50.367
MATT: "What does one but enjoy their purpose in
life?" And continues braiding his chest hair,

00:19:50.367 --> 00:19:54.319
these tiny little hairs, doing a very good job.
It's not very long, but sure enough, there is a

00:19:54.319 --> 00:19:55.530
pattern.

00:19:55.530 --> 00:19:56.338
LAURA: Wow.

00:19:56.338 --> 00:19:58.658
SAM: Thank you, you're dismissed. Back to the
music room.

00:19:58.658 --> 00:19:59.871
MATT: "Of course, Master."

00:19:59.871 --> 00:20:00.977
LAURA: Do you tip them?

00:20:00.977 --> 00:20:02.441
SAM: You can tip me, I'll pass it out later.

00:20:02.441 --> 00:20:03.710
LAURA: I believe you.

00:20:03.710 --> 00:20:08.466
TRAVIS: Hey, you there, you, ghostie, do you have
any ale in this establishment?

00:20:08.466 --> 00:20:12.667
MATT: "But of course, sir. We have an entire winery
as part of the mansion."

00:20:12.667 --> 00:20:16.549
LAURA: What in the fuck is this place? How are you
doing this?

00:20:16.549 --> 00:20:18.918
TRAVIS: Bring your most expensive frosty glass of
ale.

00:20:18.918 --> 00:20:20.635
MATT: "All right."

00:20:20.635 --> 00:20:23.350
LIAM: I pull Scanlan over to the
side. Have you always been able to do this? Have

00:20:23.350 --> 00:20:25.415
you been holding out on us, man?

00:20:25.415 --> 00:20:28.566
SAM: It never occurred to me to do this before,
for some reason.

00:20:28.566 --> 00:20:33.055
TRAVIS: You shouldn't be Burt Reynolds, you should
be Hugh Hefner from now on.

00:20:33.055 --> 00:20:41.248
SAM: No, this is a skill that I recently acquired.
I would not hold out on you. This is a new skill

00:20:41.248 --> 00:20:46.789
that I've just learned, and I'm still making
improvements to the house. You'll see that our

00:20:46.789 --> 00:20:54.866
dining room has a portrait of myself in it. Not
the one that I had commissioned, but one that I

00:20:54.866 --> 00:21:02.253
had envisioned before. It's just me in a smoking
jacket standing in front of a fireplace with me in

00:21:02.253 --> 00:21:05.966
a smoking jacket above it, Stephen Colbert-style.

00:21:05.966 --> 00:21:07.184
TRAVIS: Really?

00:21:07.184 --> 00:21:15.575
SAM: And we all have our own separate rooms. All
of the beds are circular, they all have a mirror

00:21:15.575 --> 00:21:16.602
over them.

00:21:16.602 --> 00:21:19.780
TRAVIS: Oh my god. It's Graceland!

00:21:19.780 --> 00:21:23.772
SAM: Mine is a waterbed, so be careful.

00:21:23.772 --> 00:21:28.132
LAURA: So wait, you built this entire castle, so
how do we know that you haven't installed creepy

00:21:28.132 --> 00:21:30.678
spy things into our rooms, Scanlan?

00:21:30.678 --> 00:21:31.992
MARISHA: Yeah, little peep holes.

00:21:31.992 --> 00:21:32.846
LAURA: I don't trust you.

00:21:32.846 --> 00:21:35.404
SAM: On we go to the rest of it!

00:21:35.404 --> 00:21:37.026
TRAVIS: I'm waiting on my beer.

00:21:37.026 --> 00:21:40.650
TALIESIN: I've got a great idea. Let's get some
beer, let's take a rest, and in the morning we can

00:21:40.650 --> 00:21:44.340
go to the game room, get some dice and some
paper--

00:21:44.340 --> 00:21:50.924
TRAVIS: A game within a game. The Inception (bass
note).

00:21:50.924 --> 00:21:53.439
TALIESIN: It's called Meta and Dragons, we're just
going to see how deep it goes.

00:21:53.439 --> 00:21:56.964
MARISHA: Keyleth just gets a nosebleed for no
reason. She's not sure why.

00:21:56.964 --> 00:21:58.779
TALIESIN: Had to get that out of my system.

00:21:58.779 --> 00:22:03.521
MATT: An ever-spinning top on the banister. At
this point, Grog, you can see that the servant you

00:22:03.521 --> 00:22:08.345
had sent off comes up with a very large, somewhat
spectral flagon, that upon handing it to you,

00:22:08.345 --> 00:22:11.635
turns into a solid metallic form, and inside--

00:22:11.635 --> 00:22:12.705
TRAVIS: Holy shit.

00:22:12.705 --> 00:22:15.776
MATT: -- a very, very finely chilled, very
nice-smelling wine.

00:22:15.776 --> 00:22:17.367
TRAVIS: I put my hand up for a high-five.

00:22:17.367 --> 00:22:19.511
MATT: It makes contact.

00:22:19.511 --> 00:22:20.460
TRAVIS: It does?

00:22:20.460 --> 00:22:22.607
MATT: A little cushy, but it does make contact,
yes.

00:22:22.607 --> 00:22:25.597
TRAVIS: Wait, these servants will do whatever you
want to do?

00:22:25.597 --> 00:22:30.811
LAURA: That is terrible, it's a terrible path
you're going down right now, I am uncomfortable

00:22:30.811 --> 00:22:31.510
with this--

00:22:31.510 --> 00:22:37.027
SAM: I am way ahead of you, Grog. I'm way ahead of
you. As I said, there are 100 servants here. 50 of

00:22:37.027 --> 00:22:43.850
them are assigned to me and my own personal
service. The rest are available to you in whatever

00:22:43.850 --> 00:22:45.405
capacity you'd like them.

00:22:45.405 --> 00:22:47.805
TRAVIS: This is going to be the best night ever.

00:22:47.805 --> 00:22:50.984
MARISHA: Let me go try and gather the rest of the
Ashari.

00:22:50.984 --> 00:22:53.435
LAURA: So uncomfortable right now.

00:22:53.435 --> 00:22:58.610
MARISHA: Can I get a plate of food from one of the
ghosts as proof?

00:22:58.610 --> 00:23:01.874
TRAVIS: It's about to get Caligula up in this
bitch.

00:23:01.874 --> 00:23:07.991
MATT: The servants gather up a platter of food,
piling up, grapes and meats and cured ham.

00:23:07.991 --> 00:23:11.971
MARISHA: I just pop out of the door and address
the people.

00:23:11.971 --> 00:23:15.776
MATT: As soon as you pop out of the door, it all
turns to smoke and dissipates.

00:23:15.776 --> 00:23:30.098
MARISHA: Aw, son of a-- Hey, guys, hey. It's okay.
It's actually really nice. It's been rough, why

00:23:30.098 --> 00:23:35.124
don't we all take a night off and everyone come in
and get some food. Take a night off.

00:23:35.124 --> 00:23:37.114
LAURA: Scanlan, where are we staying? Where's our
rooms?

00:23:37.114 --> 00:23:42.233
SAM: Rooms are all upstairs. There's individual
rooms for all of us. Mine is at the end of the

00:23:42.233 --> 00:23:50.503
hallway, and is slightly bigger than the rest.
You will find comfortable beds and things in every

00:23:50.503 --> 00:23:55.772
room. The two rooms next to mine are reserved--

00:23:55.772 --> 00:23:57.292
LAURA: For?

00:23:57.292 --> 00:24:02.622
SAM: One is for Pike, the other across the hallway
is for Kaylie, just in case she ever drops by.

00:24:02.622 --> 00:24:03.849
LAURA: That's really sweet.

00:24:03.849 --> 00:24:05.520
TALIESIN: Weird, but sweet.

00:24:05.520 --> 00:24:07.821
SAM: Don't worry, it's not weird.

00:24:07.821 --> 00:24:09.113
TALIESIN: Oh, it's weird.

00:24:09.113 --> 00:24:11.219
SAM: Keeping her close to my heart.

00:24:11.219 --> 00:24:12.838
LAURA: It's super-duper weird. It's really weird.

00:24:12.838 --> 00:24:18.518
SAM: It's not super-duper-- fine, fine, forget it.
When you have a daughter, you can worry about her

00:24:18.518 --> 00:24:20.412
as much as I do.

00:24:20.412 --> 00:24:25.472
MATT: At this point, Keyleth returns with a few
straggler Pyrah tribal members that come in,

00:24:25.472 --> 00:24:31.090
looking about, surprised, bewildered, and some of
them a little freaked out by this transdimensional

00:24:31.090 --> 00:24:36.809
space they just stepped into, TARDIS-style.
Servants come up and start helping them. Some of

00:24:36.809 --> 00:24:40.880
them are still clutching the rocks they were
building as they pass it off and start making

00:24:40.880 --> 00:24:46.335
their way out to various rooms to inspect the
mansion. A few stay back to continue what they

00:24:46.335 --> 00:24:51.456
were already building, ensuring future
establishments to sleep once you guys have left.

00:24:51.456 --> 00:24:55.307
So yeah, you guys are welcome to rest for the
evening, if you'd like.

00:24:55.307 --> 00:24:58.411
LAURA: Is the door protected? Can anybody come in,
or is it only if you invite them?

00:24:58.411 --> 00:24:59.798
SAM: Only invited.

00:24:59.798 --> 00:25:04.728
LAURA: This is the best fucking mansion ever.
How-- I mean-- what?

00:25:04.728 --> 00:25:06.735
TRAVIS: How many times can you do this?

00:25:06.735 --> 00:25:09.890
SAM: Once a day, but that's all we'll need,
right?

00:25:09.890 --> 00:25:16.557
TRAVIS: Shit, yeah. Wait, wait, wait, so if we
were in a fight and things went really south--

00:25:16.557 --> 00:25:18.176
SAM: We could take a break.

00:25:18.176 --> 00:25:21.128
LAURA: (gasps) No, but they could run away, it's
not like time freezes.

00:25:21.128 --> 00:25:22.501
SAM: It does take a while to cast.

00:25:22.501 --> 00:25:23.850
MATT: It takes a minute, so yeah.

00:25:23.850 --> 00:25:24.901
SAM: It takes a minute to cast.

00:25:24.901 --> 00:25:26.421
MARISHA: So it can't be the middle of a battle,
sure.

00:25:26.421 --> 00:25:30.974
LIAM: Is there anything else you can do that you
haven't-- can you make an army of unicorns or a

00:25:30.974 --> 00:25:35.294
giant in a dancing dress, or is this the extent of
what you can do?

00:25:35.294 --> 00:25:38.555
SAM: I'd like to keep a few secrets, if you don't
mind.

00:25:38.555 --> 00:25:40.566
TRAVIS: Can you make fart sounds with your
armpits?

00:25:40.566 --> 00:25:43.407
SAM: Yes. I can bend my thumb all the way back.

00:25:43.407 --> 00:25:52.669
LAURA: I pull out my crystal and I call upon the
great power of Trinket. I choose you.

00:25:52.669 --> 00:26:02.014
MATT: With a flash of deep blue and black light,
Trinket emerges (bear noises).

00:26:02.014 --> 00:26:05.658
LAURA: We have a mansion! You built a Trinket
room.

00:26:05.658 --> 00:26:09.258
SAM: You know what, I totally forgot to build
Trinket a place to sleep.

00:26:09.258 --> 00:26:12.378
LAURA: That's okay, he'll stay in Kaylie's room
for the time being, and then--

00:26:12.378 --> 00:26:14.066
SAM: No no, Kaylie's room is locked.

00:26:14.066 --> 00:26:17.798
LAURA: Pike loves him, I bet he wouldn't mind--

00:26:17.798 --> 00:26:24.003
SAM: Let me just think about this for a second.
There's the third pantry. The third pantry could

00:26:24.003 --> 00:26:30.239
possibly work. It has some just mostly-- no, no,
it's full, we can't use that.

00:26:30.239 --> 00:26:33.556
LAURA: Do you have any rooms with very high
ceilings?

00:26:33.556 --> 00:26:34.979
SAM: The front.

00:26:34.979 --> 00:26:36.912
LAURA: The very front?

00:26:36.912 --> 00:26:38.591
SAM: The front hall.

00:26:38.591 --> 00:26:42.848
LAURA: But I mean somewhere I could put a bed for
myself and Trinket with very high ceilings.

00:26:42.848 --> 00:26:48.591
SAM: All right, yes, there's a whole basement
area. It's a large space.

00:26:48.591 --> 00:26:50.474
LAURA: Wonderful. I'll move my bed down there.

00:26:50.474 --> 00:26:53.375
SAM: It's for training and working with weapons.

00:26:53.375 --> 00:26:55.082
LAURA: That'll be perfect. Trinket needs to
train.

00:26:55.082 --> 00:26:57.596
TRAVIS: Yeah, I'll go down there and I'll stay
with Trinket.

00:26:57.596 --> 00:26:59.709
LAURA: All right.

00:26:59.709 --> 00:27:04.507
TRAVIS: Yeah, I want to train a little, want to
work out a bit.

00:27:04.507 --> 00:27:06.527
LAURA: Totally. I understand.

00:27:06.527 --> 00:27:13.291
TRAVIS: Yep. I need a target, though. Hey, can you
call one of those little ghostly guys over?

00:27:13.291 --> 00:27:14.671
SAM: You can have five of them.

00:27:14.671 --> 00:27:22.270
TRAVIS: Yeah, right, fine. The first one of you
that brings me a cow wins.

00:27:22.270 --> 00:27:30.169
MATT: They all look at each other. "Right away,
sir." And all five of them drift off. A moment

00:27:30.169 --> 00:27:32.165
later, they all return with a spectral cow.

00:27:32.165 --> 00:27:35.009
MARISHA: Like five cows, they each return with
one?

00:27:35.009 --> 00:27:39.665
MATT: No, each one of them is just traveling with
one cow, they've all brought you together one

00:27:39.665 --> 00:27:40.604
spectral cow.

00:27:40.604 --> 00:27:45.018
TRAVIS: It's like a bunch of Mr. Meeseeks with
cows. Do I get to pick a cow? There's just one cow?

00:27:45.018 --> 00:27:46.368
MATT: There's just one cow.

00:27:46.368 --> 00:27:48.359
TRAVIS: Right. So can I touch the cow on the
head?

00:27:48.359 --> 00:27:51.676
MATT: You touch it, and it has weight to it, it
has surface area.

00:27:51.676 --> 00:27:55.301
LAURA: No, we're killing cows, we're killing,
we're killing poor servants--

00:27:55.301 --> 00:27:57.525
TRAVIS: We're not killing anything! And I punch
the cow in the nose.

00:27:57.525 --> 00:27:59.015
SAM: Jesus!

00:27:59.015 --> 00:28:02.681
LAURA: That's so dark!

00:28:02.681 --> 00:28:06.484
TRAVIS: No, look, I'm just seeing what it is.
Stay, Bessie.

00:28:06.484 --> 00:28:10.055
MARISHA: Grog, you just punched a cow in the
face.

00:28:10.055 --> 00:28:11.876
TRAVIS: What, I'm just seeing if it bled. Did the
nose bleed?

00:28:11.876 --> 00:28:12.858
MATT: There is no blood.

00:28:12.858 --> 00:28:13.810
TRAVIS: I punch it again.

00:28:13.810 --> 00:28:15.348
LAURA: Grog! Stop it!

00:28:15.348 --> 00:28:17.063
TRAVIS: I took a really easy punch.

00:28:17.063 --> 00:28:18.731
LAURA: Look, you're hurting it!

00:28:18.731 --> 00:28:19.977
TRAVIS: No, I'm not. Is there any blood?

00:28:19.977 --> 00:28:20.895
MATT: No blood.

00:28:20.895 --> 00:28:22.754
LAURA: Trinket blocks it.

00:28:22.754 --> 00:28:26.672
TRAVIS: Never mind. You know what, I changed my
mind, I don't need a cow. I'm going to go stay in

00:28:26.672 --> 00:28:27.675
a normal room.

00:28:27.675 --> 00:28:32.935
LAURA: No, Grog, actually, I think you should
train for a little bit at least. Just come down to

00:28:32.935 --> 00:28:34.752
the basement and maybe train for a little bit.

00:28:34.752 --> 00:28:36.046
TRAVIS: All right.

00:28:36.046 --> 00:28:41.010
LIAM: I'm sorry, where did that cow come from? I
call one of the servants over to me. Can you get

00:28:41.010 --> 00:28:43.520
anything? Could you get me a small squid?

00:28:43.520 --> 00:28:50.259
MATT: They all look at each other and shake their
head. "No, sir, we have limited resources here.

00:28:50.259 --> 00:28:51.741
"The cow, we happened to have one."

00:28:51.741 --> 00:28:55.854
LIAM: Is that a real cow, Scanlan, or was that
some sort of ghost cow?

00:28:55.854 --> 00:28:57.074
SAM: Ghost cow.

00:28:57.074 --> 00:29:02.515
MATT: At which point the cow disperses.

00:29:02.515 --> 00:29:04.917
TRAVIS: I punched it so hard it exploded.

00:29:04.917 --> 00:29:08.386
TALIESIN: The ghost of a dinner you've already
eaten, come back to haunt you.

00:29:08.386 --> 00:29:15.801
LAURA: I go down to the training room. And I stop
the servant and go, can you bring down a bed for me?

00:29:15.801 --> 00:29:16.878
MATT: Yes.

00:29:16.878 --> 00:29:19.116
LAURA: Thank you. Grog, can we train, please?

00:29:19.116 --> 00:29:21.463
TRAVIS: Yeah. You want to train with me?

00:29:21.463 --> 00:29:24.516
LAURA: Yes, I think I need to train with you,
specifically.

00:29:24.516 --> 00:29:29.033
TRAVIS: All right. Always a good time to get
better, I guess.

00:29:29.033 --> 00:29:31.151
SAM: What's going on over there?

00:29:31.151 --> 00:29:33.220
MARISHA: I don't know.

00:29:33.220 --> 00:29:37.322
MATT: You guys walk out of the foyer into the main
hallway, and at the end to the left you see a

00:29:37.322 --> 00:29:43.685
doorway appear where there wasn't one before. It
opens up on its own, and as you walk you can see

00:29:43.685 --> 00:29:51.912
stairs that lead down and into a basement chamber
that has a sand pit surrounded by brick. There are

00:29:51.912 --> 00:29:57.909
a series of wooden training dummies and various
training accoutrements. There are chains hanging

00:29:57.909 --> 00:30:03.734
from the ceiling for lifting and climbing
exercises. There is a basic set of weapons against

00:30:03.734 --> 00:30:06.814
the weapon rack and a basic set of armor on the
other set.

00:30:06.814 --> 00:30:07.967
SAM: Muscle-ups.

00:30:07.967 --> 00:30:10.005
TRAVIS: Rope climbs.

00:30:10.005 --> 00:30:15.176
TALIESIN: Are we really about to pretend to do
Crossfit? Is that a thing that's actually about to

00:30:15.176 --> 00:30:16.222
happen?

00:30:16.222 --> 00:30:19.034
SAM: Is there a big thing that says WoD on it?

00:30:19.034 --> 00:30:22.205
TRAVIS: Wizard of the Day?

00:30:22.205 --> 00:30:26.803
LAURA: The minute we get downstairs, I start
pawing into the Bag of Holding.

00:30:26.803 --> 00:30:28.069
TRAVIS: What are you doing?

00:30:28.069 --> 00:30:29.528
LAURA: I just need to (grunts).

00:30:29.528 --> 00:30:30.849
(a phone dings)

00:30:30.849 --> 00:30:32.452
SAM: Ooh, how did you do that?

00:30:32.452 --> 00:30:34.086
TRAVIS: That was awesome.

00:30:34.086 --> 00:30:36.648
TRAVIS: What did you grab?

00:30:36.648 --> 00:30:45.427
LAURA: Oh, just this cleaning utensil, is all. Are
we by ourselves? Nobody else came down, right?

00:30:45.427 --> 00:30:47.063
MATT: Just the two of you.

00:30:47.063 --> 00:30:50.566
LAURA: Yeah, I just wanted to do some cleaning
with this broom that I--

00:30:50.566 --> 00:30:51.923
TRAVIS: But this is where you train.

00:30:51.923 --> 00:30:56.592
LAURA: I put it in the Bag of Holding before.
Maybe you can train over there on those dummies,

00:30:56.592 --> 00:31:01.505
and I can just sweep up some of this sand that's
around in this area right here.

00:31:01.505 --> 00:31:03.703
TRAVIS: I thought we were going to train. I
thought we were going to fight.

00:31:03.703 --> 00:31:09.172
LAURA: Yes. Well, Trinket actually wanted some
training with his cannonball. If you will stand

00:31:09.172 --> 00:31:12.561
still so he can run into you a few times, that
would be swell.

00:31:12.561 --> 00:31:19.000
TRAVIS: I feel like there's a problem with this
idea, but I'm not sure what it is, so I do it.

00:31:19.000 --> 00:31:24.860
MATT: Okay. Trinket comes along with you and, in a
very confused manner, attempts to train with you

00:31:24.860 --> 00:31:28.920
for a short time. It's been a while since you
wrestled a bear, so it's kind of fun at times.

00:31:28.920 --> 00:31:30.321
LAURA: It's fun, right?

00:31:30.321 --> 00:31:35.044
TRAVIS: Look, I know I usually hit back, but
apparently your mum thinks you can cannonball into

00:31:35.044 --> 00:31:37.565
me, so give it a go.

00:31:37.565 --> 00:31:39.254
LAURA: Go ahead and try, Trinket!

00:31:39.254 --> 00:31:45.794
MATT: Trinket backs up (bear growling), looks over
at you again like, "Are you sure?" Across the sand

00:31:45.794 --> 00:31:48.558
flooring into a giant rolling attack towards you.

00:31:48.558 --> 00:31:49.989
TRAVIS: Oh, fuck.

00:31:49.989 --> 00:31:52.728
MATT: That is going to be... What's Trinket's
attack bonus?

00:31:52.728 --> 00:31:54.885
LAURA: Oh, God, you're really doing it.

00:31:54.885 --> 00:31:55.837
TRAVIS: Yes!

00:31:55.837 --> 00:32:01.631
LAURA: Yes, that's the point of this, to get
Trinket to run into you is the point. His attack

00:32:01.631 --> 00:32:04.142
bonus is plus eight.

00:32:04.142 --> 00:32:06.199
MATT: Plus eight, that's a 23 to hit.

00:32:06.199 --> 00:32:07.447
TRAVIS: Yeah, that hits.

00:32:07.447 --> 00:32:10.604
MATT: You go ahead and take seven points of
bludgeoning damage.

00:32:10.604 --> 00:32:12.570
LAURA: And you're knocked prone!

00:32:12.570 --> 00:32:14.662
MATT: Go ahead and make a strength saving throw.

00:32:14.662 --> 00:32:22.457
TRAVIS: (laughing) Okay. 26.

00:32:22.457 --> 00:32:29.356
MATT: So Trinket rams into you, and you hold firm
and flex. Conversely, the giant bear bounces off,

00:32:29.356 --> 00:32:31.365
stumbles back onto Trinket's butt.

00:32:31.365 --> 00:32:37.547
TRAVIS: That was pretty good! I liked it a lot!

00:32:37.547 --> 00:32:41.186
MATT: Licks you right along the face, beard
cowlicks up a little bit.

00:32:41.186 --> 00:32:46.703
TRAVIS: I think this might be a good look for me.
How do I get it to stay?

00:32:46.703 --> 00:32:50.938
LAURA: While all that is going on, I have a broom
in my hand.

00:32:50.938 --> 00:32:52.062
MATT: You do.

00:32:52.062 --> 00:32:53.950
TRAVIS: I start climbing all over the walls.

00:32:53.950 --> 00:33:00.092
LAURA: I put it between my legs and try to sit on
it.

00:33:00.092 --> 00:33:01.383
MATT: All right.

00:33:01.383 --> 00:33:03.523
SAM: Weirdly, I'm doing the same thing upstairs.

00:33:03.523 --> 00:33:05.507
(laughter)

00:33:05.507 --> 00:33:07.896
TRAVIS: Is one of your servants named Broom?

00:33:07.896 --> 00:33:11.347
LAURA: And I jump in the air a little bit.

00:33:11.347 --> 00:33:12.811
MATT: Hop.

00:33:12.811 --> 00:33:32.994
LAURA: Okay. I say, up! Fly! Lift up! Fatty
Arbuckle! Shenanigans! Ren and Stimpy, I don't know.

00:33:32.994 --> 00:33:34.450
TRAVIS: Rotisserie chicken!

00:33:34.450 --> 00:33:37.589
LAURA: Fuck! Grog.

00:33:37.589 --> 00:33:40.031
TALIESIN: Perhaps it requires a bad Irish accent.

00:33:40.031 --> 00:33:42.051
LAURA: (Irish accent) Fatty Arbuckle!

00:33:42.051 --> 00:33:44.612
(laughter)

00:33:44.612 --> 00:33:46.229
LAURA: Nothing.

00:33:46.229 --> 00:33:47.450
MATT: Nothing.

00:33:47.450 --> 00:33:50.375
TRAVIS: Do you usually yell when you clean?

00:33:50.375 --> 00:33:56.247
LAURA: (groans) I put the broom on the ground. I
walk over and I punch Grog as hard as I can.

00:33:56.247 --> 00:33:58.215
TRAVIS: What was that for?

00:33:58.215 --> 00:34:00.798
MATT: Grog, it's not very strong.

00:34:00.798 --> 00:34:03.400
LAURA: It's not. I'm pretty fucking weak.

00:34:03.400 --> 00:34:07.357
TRAVIS: No, I know, but I like to make her feel
good about it. Ow!

00:34:07.357 --> 00:34:12.089
LAURA: Sorry I hurt you, Grog, I know that was a
very strong punch.

00:34:12.089 --> 00:34:13.625
TRAVIS: I look at Trinket and wink.

00:34:13.625 --> 00:34:16.972
LAURA: Are you guys good? Do you want to keep
training?

00:34:16.972 --> 00:34:18.809
TRAVIS: Yeah, what are you doing?

00:34:18.809 --> 00:34:22.906
LAURA: Nothing! I put the fucking broom back in
the Bag of Holding.

00:34:22.906 --> 00:34:24.898
TRAVIS: You didn't clean very much.

00:34:24.898 --> 00:34:30.216
LAURA: I figured the servants can do it. I walk
upstairs.

00:34:30.216 --> 00:34:31.531
MATT: Okay.

00:34:31.531 --> 00:34:34.261
LIAM: Can Scanlan cast Sad Trombone?

00:34:34.261 --> 00:34:38.247
SAM: We have a music room. I actually have a
trombone.

00:34:38.247 --> 00:34:41.127
MATT: That's true.

00:34:41.127 --> 00:34:44.601
SAM: (sad trombone sound)

00:34:44.601 --> 00:34:48.513
MATT: With Vex not there, Trinket gets a little
antsy and eventually your training session with

00:34:48.513 --> 00:34:53.570
Trinket comes to an end as Trinket goes to seek
Vex. You can finish your wall climbing in solace.

00:34:53.570 --> 00:34:58.384
TRAVIS: All right. I'm good for the night.

00:34:58.384 --> 00:34:59.840
MATT: Okay.

00:34:59.840 --> 00:35:02.120
TRAVIS: I wanted that cow.

00:35:02.120 --> 00:35:04.120
LAURA: I go find Keyleth.

00:35:04.120 --> 00:35:09.762
MARISHA: Okay. I don't know, I'm just chilling.
I'm eating food.

00:35:09.762 --> 00:35:12.248
TRAVIS: Eating food.

00:35:12.248 --> 00:35:14.497
MARISHA: Relaxing.

00:35:14.497 --> 00:35:20.816
LAURA: Hey! Actually-- no, I don't want to talk to
you. Keyleth. What do you know about magical

00:35:20.816 --> 00:35:26.521
things? Like a lot?

00:35:26.521 --> 00:35:35.102
MARISHA: I'm not great at identifying what they
are. I can generally be like, that's magical! But

00:35:35.102 --> 00:35:39.917
I don't know arcane things, only natural-based
magics.

00:35:39.917 --> 00:35:44.603
LAURA: Oh, fuck. Thank you so much!

00:35:44.603 --> 00:35:46.295
MARISHA: Why?

00:35:46.295 --> 00:35:47.922
SAM: Anything I can help you with, Vex?

00:35:47.922 --> 00:35:53.016
LAURA: Scanlan! I might need to talk to you,
dear.

00:35:53.016 --> 00:35:55.899
SAM: Should we retire to my room for this?

00:35:55.899 --> 00:35:58.069
LAURA: Why, yes, we should.

00:35:58.069 --> 00:36:03.760
SAM: (excited gasp) I was not expecting that.

00:36:03.760 --> 00:36:09.047
MARISHA: Keyleth just picks up her plate and
awkwardly leaves.

00:36:09.047 --> 00:36:12.017
LAURA: I go get the broom from the Bag of Holding
again.

00:36:12.017 --> 00:36:16.988
SAM: I run up to my room to make sure that
everything's neat. Light a bunch of candles.

00:36:16.988 --> 00:36:19.187
LAURA: I follow him up and knock on the door.

00:36:19.187 --> 00:36:22.335
MATT: Okay. The door opens up at the first knock.
(creak)

00:36:22.335 --> 00:36:28.756
SAM: I'm lying in bed. Black satin sheets. Oh, I
forgot you were coming!

00:36:28.756 --> 00:36:38.364
LAURA: Wow. Well, darling. I shut the door behind
me. I have a favor to ask you.

00:36:38.364 --> 00:36:43.474
SAM: I should warn you, we're not alone. And I
look over to the five musicians and I ask them to

00:36:43.474 --> 00:36:45.709
strike up a little--

00:36:45.709 --> 00:36:53.432
MATT: A gentle classical piece with a small,
low-timbre brass section comes in.

00:36:53.432 --> 00:36:55.149
SAM: Little bossa nova.

00:36:55.149 --> 00:36:58.872
MATT: Yeah, it's nice. It's not too involved,
doesn't distract you too much.

00:36:58.872 --> 00:37:00.826
LAURA: It's nice mood setting, I like it.

00:37:00.826 --> 00:37:05.756
SAM: Whatever. It's, you know, it's my special
place where I like to come and think about

00:37:05.756 --> 00:37:07.572
philosophy and life.

00:37:07.572 --> 00:37:10.674
LAURA: You're so smart. I've always thought that
about you, that you're very smart.

00:37:10.674 --> 00:37:12.598
SAM: Well, many people do.

00:37:12.598 --> 00:37:15.012
LAURA: Yes. I sit down next to him on the bed.

00:37:15.012 --> 00:37:18.407
SAM: (gulps) It goes up and down a bit. It's a
water bed.

00:37:18.407 --> 00:37:23.629
LAURA: Cozy. Help me!

00:37:23.629 --> 00:37:25.540
SAM: Is that--

00:37:25.540 --> 00:37:27.054
LAURA: What?

00:37:27.054 --> 00:37:29.243
SAM: Did we see that before?

00:37:29.243 --> 00:37:34.485
LAURA: Maybe. Okay, Scanlan, I'm a terrible
person, I know.

00:37:34.485 --> 00:37:36.302
SAM: What did you do?

00:37:36.302 --> 00:37:41.078
LAURA: I took a broom from a poor, poor
dragonborn.

00:37:41.078 --> 00:37:44.063
SAM: You took Gern's magical broom?

00:37:44.063 --> 00:37:45.135
LAURA: Maybe.

00:37:45.135 --> 00:37:46.605
SAM: Oh my gods.

00:37:46.605 --> 00:37:50.301
LAURA: I know, I'm sorry, I know, I'm terrible,
and now it won't work and it was pointless and I

00:37:50.301 --> 00:37:51.903
want it to work. Help me.

00:37:51.903 --> 00:37:53.047
SAM: Because it flies?

00:37:53.047 --> 00:37:54.580
LAURA: Because it flies, Scanlan.

00:37:54.580 --> 00:37:56.431
SAM: What is it with you and flying?

00:37:56.431 --> 00:38:01.574
LAURA: I don't know, there's just something about
being up there in the air that makes me feel alive

00:38:01.574 --> 00:38:03.732
in a way that I've never felt before.

00:38:03.732 --> 00:38:05.436
SAM: I could make you fly.

00:38:05.436 --> 00:38:09.375
LAURA: Okay. Wait-- Oh, you mean. With your cube.

00:38:09.375 --> 00:38:11.748
SAM: Yes, that's right.

00:38:11.748 --> 00:38:14.941
LAURA: I'd rather you do it with this broom,
actually. And not in any weird way, just to be

00:38:14.941 --> 00:38:18.418
able to help me make the broom fly. Do you know
how to do that?

00:38:18.418 --> 00:38:25.671
SAM: I will try. I will examine the broom and make
some sort of check on it.

00:38:25.671 --> 00:38:27.018
MATT: Make an arcana check.

00:38:27.018 --> 00:38:28.591
SAM: Oh, that's not good.

00:38:28.591 --> 00:38:30.545
TRAVIS: Should've come to me for that.

00:38:30.545 --> 00:38:31.937
LAURA: Oh, no!

00:38:31.937 --> 00:38:33.445
TALIESIN: It's a number.

00:38:33.445 --> 00:38:34.566
SAM: 14.

00:38:34.566 --> 00:38:41.573
MATT: 14. Okay. Looking over the broom, you can
tell it's enchanted. There are runes along the

00:38:41.573 --> 00:38:49.855
sides of the broom. You do gather from the nature
of the enchantment that it is an item that

00:38:49.855 --> 00:38:58.846
requires a spoken phrase from the wielder to
initiate its magic. Short of an Identify spell,

00:38:58.846 --> 00:39:03.238
you would probably have to guess. If you know the
Identify spell, that would be a way for you to.

00:39:03.238 --> 00:39:08.188
SAM: I don't. Can I examine it to see if there's
any markings, any hidden anything on it?

00:39:08.188 --> 00:39:12.301
MATT: Make an intelligence check. Or, you know
what, this would be specifically investigation.

00:39:12.301 --> 00:39:13.815
Investigation check.

00:39:13.815 --> 00:39:15.901
SAM: Investigation. 21.

00:39:15.901 --> 00:39:23.611
MATT: You do notice that many of the runes
intricately carved on the side of the broom are--

00:39:23.611 --> 00:39:30.890
they're part of the enchantment; however, there is
a certain phrase that is not part of the

00:39:30.890 --> 00:39:37.524
enchantment. It's scrawled into and very cleverly
hidden amongst the broom. It is not Common. What

00:39:37.524 --> 00:39:38.900
languages do you know?

00:39:38.900 --> 00:39:42.792
SAM: Common, Gnome. Pig Latin.

00:39:42.792 --> 00:39:46.140
MATT: It is not a language you recognize.

00:39:46.140 --> 00:39:48.831
LAURA: I speak Elvish, Draconic, Undercommon?

00:39:48.831 --> 00:39:51.162
SAM: You don't see the words, though.

00:39:51.162 --> 00:39:52.514
LAURA: But you saw it.

00:39:52.514 --> 00:39:57.468
SAM: There's some words here that might be a clue
to the code word. Basically, we need to find the

00:39:57.468 --> 00:39:59.549
code word. What do we know about Gern?

00:39:59.549 --> 00:40:02.367
LAURA: Well, I tried Fatty Arbuckle. I thought
maybe that was something.

00:40:02.367 --> 00:40:04.185
SAM: Did you try the others? Coral? Carol?

00:40:04.185 --> 00:40:05.298
LAURA: Coral. Carol.

00:40:05.298 --> 00:40:07.312
SAM: You probably need to hold it.

00:40:07.312 --> 00:40:11.427
LAURA: What was the... Oh. Coral! Carol! I don't
remember the other one's name.

00:40:11.427 --> 00:40:12.781
SAM: I don't either.

00:40:12.781 --> 00:40:14.579
LAURA: Stimpy? Was it Stimpy? It was Stimpy!

00:40:14.579 --> 00:40:18.979
SAM: Try: On Coral! On Carol! On Stimpy! On Fatty
Arbuckle!

00:40:18.979 --> 00:40:21.986
LAURA: Wait, but what does the word say? Where's
the word?

00:40:21.986 --> 00:40:23.342
SAM: I can't read the words.

00:40:23.342 --> 00:40:24.819
LAURA: Can I find it? What is it?

00:40:24.819 --> 00:40:26.045
MATT: Do you point it out to her?

00:40:26.045 --> 00:40:27.194
SAM: I point it out to her.

00:40:27.194 --> 00:40:28.036
LAURA: What is it?

00:40:28.036 --> 00:40:29.189
MATT: It is Draconic.

00:40:29.189 --> 00:40:30.281
LAURA: What does it say?

00:40:30.281 --> 00:40:35.398
MATT: It's archaic Draconic. It's from the base
root of the language, which is one of the oldest

00:40:35.398 --> 00:40:42.709
languages in civilization. It spells out,
phonetically, the word for candle.

00:40:42.709 --> 00:40:48.375
LAURA: That's smart. (hacking spit)

00:40:48.375 --> 00:40:54.862
MATT: At which point, the broom jumps up in your
hands, and almost lifts you off the bed for a

00:40:54.862 --> 00:40:56.777
second, and you catch it and hold it back down.

00:40:56.777 --> 00:41:06.127
LAURA: (singing) Something has changed within me!
Oh my God! Oh my God. Scanlan.

00:41:06.127 --> 00:41:12.991
SAM: Weirdly, you are not the first floating chick
I've had in my bed. But that is amazing! You're

00:41:12.991 --> 00:41:13.999
flying!

00:41:13.999 --> 00:41:17.991
LAURA: I hug him. I hug him as hard as I've ever
hugged Scanlan. I love you so much. You're my

00:41:17.991 --> 00:41:21.964
favorite person in the entire universe right now.
I owe you--

00:41:21.964 --> 00:41:25.518
SAM: Nope. You owe me nothing. That's what friends
are for.

00:41:25.518 --> 00:41:27.860
LAURA: I love you.

00:41:27.860 --> 00:41:30.181
SAM: I shake her little elf hand.

00:41:30.181 --> 00:41:32.685
MATT: It's a pretty big elf hand compared to your
tiny gnome hand.

00:41:32.685 --> 00:41:33.806
SAM: Okay.

00:41:33.806 --> 00:41:38.222
LAURA: I sit on it. How high are the ceilings in
here?

00:41:38.222 --> 00:41:40.236
MATT: How high are the ceilings in your room?

00:41:40.236 --> 00:41:42.430
SAM: As high as they can be on the top floor.

00:41:42.430 --> 00:41:45.722
MATT: For this room, because it is an
extradimensional space, this room is probably a

00:41:45.722 --> 00:41:50.933
good 50 feet high. High ceilings, with drapery.
It's so garish.

00:41:50.933 --> 00:41:52.284
LAURA: Can I sit side-saddle on it?

00:41:52.284 --> 00:41:53.568
MATT: Yeah.

00:41:53.568 --> 00:41:56.391
LAURA: (hacking spit) I don't remember how I said
it before.

00:41:56.391 --> 00:41:57.920
SAM: You're going to have to remember that now.

00:41:57.920 --> 00:41:59.810
MATT: Better write that down. (hacking spit)

00:41:59.810 --> 00:42:03.209
LAURA: Why didn't I choose something more fun to
say?

00:42:03.209 --> 00:42:10.475
MATT: Welcome to D&amp;amp;D. As the words emit from your
mouth, the broom takes off, and you have to aim it

00:42:10.475 --> 00:42:16.040
a bit. You start going around in circles, slowly
rising up towards the roof of the room.

00:42:16.040 --> 00:42:20.639
LAURA: Yay, this is awesome! I'm really high!

00:42:20.639 --> 00:42:24.691
SAM: I instruct the band to start playing Flight
of the Bumblebee.

00:42:24.691 --> 00:42:29.021
MATT: (whistling)

00:42:29.021 --> 00:42:32.707
LAURA: Oh my gosh! Can I take my hands off?

00:42:32.707 --> 00:42:37.867
MATT: You do, and you start going, "Whoa!" Go
ahead and make a dexterity check.

00:42:37.867 --> 00:42:41.951
LAURA: Oh my God. I probably should have been
lower to the ground when I said that. Okay, that's

00:42:41.951 --> 00:42:44.220
fine. Oh, I'm still exhausted!

00:42:44.220 --> 00:42:45.394
MATT: Yep.

00:42:45.394 --> 00:42:47.547
SAM: Oh, shit.

00:42:47.547 --> 00:42:50.337
LAURA: 20.

00:42:50.337 --> 00:42:54.721
MATT: That's fine. You're fine. A really bad roll
might have had a circumstance, but you manage to

00:42:54.721 --> 00:42:58.301
catch yourself on the broom in time and, okay.
You're getting the hang of it. It's still not

00:42:58.301 --> 00:43:01.651
something you're used to, but it's fine.

00:43:01.651 --> 00:43:03.953
LAURA: Can I point it down towards the ground and
get lower?

00:43:03.953 --> 00:43:08.300
MATT: You do. And you take a few minutes to figure
out the pitch and wobble of it, and it's less of a

00:43:08.300 --> 00:43:14.873
directional flight, more than it is a combination
of how you hold the front of the broom and

00:43:14.873 --> 00:43:20.304
concentrate on its direction. But nevertheless, a
few moments pass, and you get the hang of it.

00:43:20.304 --> 00:43:24.743
LAURA: Oh. My. God. This is the best day of my
entire life.

00:43:24.743 --> 00:43:26.078
SAM: You look great up there.

00:43:26.078 --> 00:43:27.539
LAURA: Thank you. Thank you.

00:43:27.539 --> 00:43:31.104
SAM: But you should not have stolen that!

00:43:31.104 --> 00:43:32.516
LAURA: Oh, I know, I know, it's terrible!

00:43:32.516 --> 00:43:34.003
SAM: He was our friend! He helped us!

00:43:34.003 --> 00:43:36.019
LAURA: How bad of a person am I? I'm a horrible
person!

00:43:36.019 --> 00:43:38.574
SAM: We should do something to repay the debt!

00:43:38.574 --> 00:43:41.835
LAURA: Well, I tried. I was going to give him a
lot of dragon scales, and he wandered away!

00:43:41.835 --> 00:43:44.429
SAM: We can't possibly find him now.

00:43:44.429 --> 00:43:47.361
LAURA: Well, how do I help him? Because I feel
terrible.

00:43:47.361 --> 00:43:53.321
SAM: If we can't help him, you're going to have to
help someone else to make up for the lost karma.

00:43:53.321 --> 00:43:58.192
LAURA: I will help as many people as I can while
I'm flying through the air.

00:43:58.192 --> 00:44:05.762
SAM: Perhaps I will pick someone for you to help
someday. To repay us both.

00:44:05.762 --> 00:44:07.443
LAURA: I think that's a deal, Scanlan.

00:44:07.443 --> 00:44:09.370
SAM: All right. I will mark that down.

00:44:09.370 --> 00:44:14.327
LAURA: What are you, like, a hag now? I sit on it,
and I open the door, and I fly through the

00:44:14.327 --> 00:44:15.326
doorway.

00:44:15.326 --> 00:44:19.485
MATT: She drifts out of the room. The door (slam)
shuts behind her.

00:44:19.485 --> 00:44:21.589
MARISHA: You're going to be one of those Segway
assholes now!

00:44:21.589 --> 00:44:22.923
TRAVIS: Yes, totally!

00:44:22.923 --> 00:44:30.882
MATT: You lean back in your bed, on your fine,
black silken sheets, with Flight of the Bumblebees

00:44:30.882 --> 00:44:32.689
still blaring by the fireplace.

00:44:32.689 --> 00:44:35.094
SAM: All right, guys, it didn't work, you can go.

00:44:35.094 --> 00:44:41.162
MATT: They all get up. The music stops. And they
all slowly drift out of the room, one by one.

00:44:41.162 --> 00:44:44.635
Fireplace still crackling.

00:44:44.635 --> 00:44:46.216
SAM: It's nice in here.

00:44:46.216 --> 00:44:49.976
TALIESIN: I'm sitting wherever there's a lounge of
any kind. I'm working in the sketchbook. Working

00:44:49.976 --> 00:44:51.469
on things.

00:44:51.469 --> 00:44:52.843
MATT: Not a worry.

00:44:52.843 --> 00:44:58.044
MARISHA: I'll be reading my alchemy book, because
I have had so little time to catch up on my

00:44:58.044 --> 00:44:58.920
reading.

00:44:58.920 --> 00:45:00.362
TALIESIN: We never talk anymore, do we?

00:45:00.362 --> 00:45:01.681
MARISHA: We never do.

00:45:01.681 --> 00:45:04.203
TALIESIN: Mmm.

00:45:04.203 --> 00:45:09.041
LAURA: I'm so happy! It's the best!

00:45:09.041 --> 00:45:10.785
MATT: So good!

00:45:10.785 --> 00:45:15.601
LAURA: I'm going to try to sleep. It's going to be
really, really hard because I'm so excited, but I

00:45:15.601 --> 00:45:17.288
really need to get some rest!

00:45:17.288 --> 00:45:18.579
MARISHA: Did you feed the dog?

00:45:18.579 --> 00:45:24.479
TALIESIN: Today? I don't know.

00:45:24.479 --> 00:45:28.310
MATT: So, anyone want to do anything else? You
going to go rest for the evening?

00:45:28.310 --> 00:45:30.330
TRAVIS: I rest.

00:45:30.330 --> 00:45:31.272
TALIESIN: I'm good.

00:45:31.272 --> 00:45:36.362
MATT: All right. You all eventually find your ways
to your rooms, happy and comfortable in the fact

00:45:36.362 --> 00:45:44.172
that no one has to take watch for this night. As
you all get to bed, a few hours into the evening,

00:45:44.172 --> 00:45:50.457
Keyleth, you are just starting to doze off when
you hear a knock at the door.

00:45:50.457 --> 00:45:53.710
MARISHA: (gasps awake) Scanlan?

00:45:53.710 --> 00:45:56.067
MATT: You open the door?

00:45:56.067 --> 00:45:58.181
MARISHA: On my door?

00:45:58.181 --> 00:46:00.171
MATT: On your door.

00:46:00.171 --> 00:46:03.346
MARISHA: Who is it?

00:46:03.346 --> 00:46:08.773
MATT: "Keyleth, it is Cerkonos. Please open up. I
wish to speak with you."

00:46:08.773 --> 00:46:10.859
MARISHA: I open the door.

00:46:10.859 --> 00:46:18.894
MATT: Okay. Cerkonos comes in. The first thing you
notice-- previously, you had seen what was his

00:46:18.894 --> 00:46:26.127
burned-off arm at the shoulder. You can now see
the flesh is extended and is currently very slowly

00:46:26.127 --> 00:46:32.108
in the process of regenerating his lost arm. And
it catches you off-guard for a moment, and he puts

00:46:32.108 --> 00:46:38.958
his hand up and says, "Sorry, it is not very
presentable." And he still keeps his hand over it,

00:46:38.958 --> 00:46:51.033
slightly embarrassed by the mid-regenerative state
of it. "I'm sorry to have disturbed you, I come as

00:46:51.033 --> 00:46:56.771
"unease has taken my mind." And he enters the room
and closes the door behind him. "May we sit?"

00:46:56.771 --> 00:46:58.928
MARISHA: Of course, please, Cerkonos.

00:46:58.928 --> 00:47:02.540
MATT: He goes over and takes one of the nearby
chairs and sets it down, places one across from

00:47:02.540 --> 00:47:12.510
him for you to sit, gestures with his one arm.
Sits down. "I would not speak with those I do not

00:47:12.510 --> 00:47:20.513
"trust. And I have seen your purity of soul,
Keyleth. So I come to you with these concerns."

00:47:20.513 --> 00:47:31.133
His eyes trail off for a moment in the distance,
and he gathers his thoughts and his words. "Four

00:47:31.133 --> 00:47:44.207
"years ago, a young woman came to Pyrah for
redemption. A lost girl, cast out and wishing for

00:47:44.207 --> 00:47:56.724
"acceptance. We, as we do with outcasts, took her
in, taught her. And in time, called her one of our

00:47:56.724 --> 00:48:12.099
"own, one of the Pyrah. In recent months, she began
to grow distant, taking to staying in the

00:48:12.099 --> 00:48:22.851
"Cindergrove unattended for days at a time. One
afternoon, the mountain moved, angry with shifting

00:48:22.851 --> 00:48:34.666
"fires. We felt a disturbance in the Gate, and when
we went to investigate, there she was, commanding

00:48:34.666 --> 00:48:37.362
"powers we did not know she had."

00:48:37.362 --> 00:48:42.634
MARISHA: What kind of powers? Beyond those of
druidic nature?

00:48:42.634 --> 00:48:55.260
MATT: "These were the magics taken by man who defied
the gods. These were the purest of ancient arcane

00:48:55.260 --> 00:49:05.716
"threads. We watched as she reached out and tore
open the Gate. She laughed as we called out to

00:49:05.716 --> 00:49:11.523
"stop. But something terrible emerged from that
wounded sky."

00:49:11.523 --> 00:49:13.604
MARISHA: Thordak?

00:49:13.604 --> 00:49:21.445
MATT: "This dragon you speak of, yes. I defended
all that I could, but the power was too great, and

00:49:21.445 --> 00:49:31.584
"unconsciousness took me. I awoke to my people in
tatters, the fires untethered, and this terrible

00:49:31.584 --> 00:49:47.505
"girl gone. It is both embarrassing and greatly
alarming that we could be infiltrated by such an

00:49:47.505 --> 00:49:54.635
"entity. That blame falls on me, as the headmaster,
for not seeing this earlier."

00:49:54.635 --> 00:50:01.281
MARISHA: You acted within the good nature of our
people, there's nothing wrong with that. How old

00:50:01.281 --> 00:50:04.398
was this girl when she came to you? And how old is
she now?

00:50:04.398 --> 00:50:07.018
MATT: "When she came to us she couldn't be more
than 15."

00:50:07.018 --> 00:50:11.076
MARISHA: So she's 19, 20?

00:50:11.076 --> 00:50:21.167
MATT: "Perhaps. She did not seem to blossom into
womanhood as many do. We considered her more of a

00:50:21.167 --> 00:50:24.170
"runt of her litter, if you will."

00:50:24.170 --> 00:50:29.272
MARISHA: And what was her race?

00:50:29.272 --> 00:50:32.171
MATT: "She seemed human."

00:50:32.171 --> 00:50:35.695
MARISHA: She seemed human? What do you mean?

00:50:35.695 --> 00:50:46.290
MATT: "We take many forms as druids. If she was
indeed human, at that age, to command such power...

00:50:46.290 --> 00:50:48.892
"I do not know her true nature."

00:50:48.892 --> 00:50:51.639
MARISHA: What was her name?

00:50:51.639 --> 00:51:05.615
MATT: "Her name was Raishan. Anyway. I wish to
tell you this because my heart is heavy with

00:51:05.615 --> 00:51:21.082
"guilt, and I want you to know that even in places
of comfort, family, be careful, keep those you

00:51:21.082 --> 00:51:30.289
"know you can trust close. Be mindful of those that
promise aid when they have not proven themselves.

00:51:30.289 --> 00:51:35.762
"If you have an instinct, follow it."

00:51:35.762 --> 00:51:40.345
MARISHA: Are you referring to something in
particular, Cerkonos?

00:51:40.345 --> 00:51:49.578
MATT: "I just do not wish you to make the same
mistake I did. Anyway, I thank you for your

00:51:49.578 --> 00:51:53.994
"companions and you coming to our aid. It shall not
be forgotten."

00:51:53.994 --> 00:52:05.054
MARISHA: I shall keep an ear open for the name
Raishan. If I hear anything about her, I'll send word.

00:52:05.054 --> 00:52:13.391
MATT: "Should you need the aid of the Pyrah,
though we are not much at now, come find me. I

00:52:13.391 --> 00:52:19.283
"look forward for to you bringing Zephrah together.
You will make a fine leader."

00:52:19.283 --> 00:52:26.936
MARISHA: Thank you, Cerkonos. And I'm glad that
you're still with us.

00:52:26.936 --> 00:52:29.306
MATT: "Kaitiaki, Keyleth."

00:52:29.306 --> 00:52:30.820
MARISHA: Kaitiaki, Cerkonos.

00:52:30.820 --> 00:52:32.472
MATT: Cerkonos leaves.

00:52:32.472 --> 00:52:40.930
MARISHA: And I start poring through my notes for
the name Raishan, because Keyleth believes she has

00:52:40.930 --> 00:52:47.094
heard that name before as one of the dragons,
correct? One of the white--

00:52:47.094 --> 00:52:48.407
LAURA: (whispering) It's the green one.

00:52:48.407 --> 00:52:51.110
MARISHA: --the green one. Okay, okay.

00:52:51.110 --> 00:52:52.830
MATT: That is true.

00:52:52.830 --> 00:52:57.549
MARISHA: Do I have any other reference, would I
know anything else about that?

00:52:57.549 --> 00:53:04.490
MATT: That's all you know, is the name
Raishan was used when the Conclave attacked Emon.

00:53:04.490 --> 00:53:09.043
And it seemed the name belonged to the green
dragon that initiated the assault where you guys were.

00:53:09.043 --> 00:53:11.248
MARISHA: Fucking bitch.

00:53:11.248 --> 00:53:17.393
MATT: So, these thoughts echoing through your
mind--

00:53:17.393 --> 00:53:20.346
TALIESIN: Streets will run green with revenge!

00:53:20.346 --> 00:53:21.761
MARISHA: Yes, they will!

00:53:21.761 --> 00:53:27.888
MATT: You sleep, but uneasily, as all of these
realizations swirl in your head. Eventually sleep

00:53:27.888 --> 00:53:38.888
takes you, but it is not an easy sleep. Just
enough to function. Barely. Vax. As you yourself

00:53:38.888 --> 00:53:45.499
have attempted to stave off sleep for many days,
pushing yourself to your limits, it finally takes

00:53:45.499 --> 00:53:54.718
its toll, and you drift off into a deep, deep
slumber. In that slumber, you find yourself in

00:53:54.718 --> 00:54:07.223
darkness. Echoes of a distant voice, muffled, as
if underwater. Crash. The darkness is shattered

00:54:07.223 --> 00:54:14.944
into a thousand black feathers, and you find
yourself falling, falling. Falling towards what

00:54:14.944 --> 00:54:22.665
seems to be a tangled net of glowing threads.
You're afraid you might impact at such a speed,

00:54:22.665 --> 00:54:31.617
but before you do, you slow and come to a stop
before this extremely prominent glowing weave,

00:54:31.617 --> 00:54:41.319
this infinite tapestry in all directions. You are
uncertain of the meaning of this moment when a

00:54:41.319 --> 00:54:49.155
large cold hand reaches past your shoulder and
grasps a thread right before your face, this

00:54:49.155 --> 00:54:56.497
singular glowing thread, pulsing with light like a
heartbeat. You follow the arm over your shoulder,

00:54:56.497 --> 00:55:06.155
and glance up directly into the massive form of
the Raven Queen: porcelain face like a mask, long

00:55:06.155 --> 00:55:15.436
jet-black hair, her body encasing you like a
physical cage. Your eyes follow the arm back to

00:55:15.436 --> 00:55:23.551
the thread that she carries between her massive
fingers. She tugs it, ever so gently, and it

00:55:23.551 --> 00:55:33.606
causes waves to ripple through the tapestry into
infinity. Her voice fills your mind, both calm but

00:55:33.606 --> 00:55:47.968
cold. "This is you, my champion. You are
fate-touched. The choice is yours. Rebirth or

00:55:47.968 --> 00:56:01.930
"ruin. Maker or martyr. Conqueror, tyrant, or
nothing." She plucks the thread from the weave,

00:56:01.930 --> 00:56:07.300
snapping it. You plummet into the hole left behind
it, falling faster and faster into the dark.

00:56:07.300 --> 00:56:12.231
Losing control, you turn around and see the Raven
Queen, disappearing into the distance, growing

00:56:12.231 --> 00:56:19.637
smaller and smaller, until suddenly, nothing.

00:56:19.637 --> 00:56:26.302
Grog. You fall into a deep snore, heavy, heavy
snore, after drinking the wine, climbing up walls,

00:56:26.302 --> 00:56:28.602
you've had an exhausting day of--

00:56:28.602 --> 00:56:30.022
TRAVIS: Sleeping in the sand pit.

00:56:30.022 --> 00:56:32.561
MATT: Okay, you are face down.

00:56:32.561 --> 00:56:34.851
TRAVIS: Like a beach, just (snore).

00:56:34.851 --> 00:56:38.988
MATT: It's great. You've drooled into the sand,
and it's clustered around your beard. It's

00:56:38.988 --> 00:56:46.985
horrifying. But in the middle of snoring, this
restful sleep also comes into your mind, and you

00:56:46.985 --> 00:56:52.501
find yourself walking alone. A long hallway, into
blinding light. You have to cover your face, it's

00:56:52.501 --> 00:57:00.499
so bright, but you push forward because you know
there's only one way to go. You cannot see, but

00:57:00.499 --> 00:57:06.688
you can hear around you and sense the hallway's
ended, and there's now space around you. You

00:57:06.688 --> 00:57:14.181
cannot see, but you sense an arena, gladiatorial
in nature. You can hear the distant whisper and

00:57:14.181 --> 00:57:16.881
hum of crowds cheering.

00:57:16.881 --> 00:57:18.871
SAM: Phillip! Phillip!

00:57:18.871 --> 00:57:28.567
MATT: You sense others around you, closing in
suddenly. A voice, ever-whispering in your ear,

00:57:28.567 --> 00:57:36.034
says, "Release me." Still blinded, eyes closed, on
instinct, you pull the cold, dark blade from your

00:57:36.034 --> 00:57:41.771
back and swing wide, over and over again, feeling
the shuddering shock of each impact, your strength

00:57:41.771 --> 00:57:47.778
matched by the razor-like edge of your weapon,
cleaving down any who would approach. The high of

00:57:47.778 --> 00:57:52.273
adrenaline is incredible, and you laugh aloud at
the sheer thrill of your own power.

00:57:52.273 --> 00:57:53.986
TRAVIS: (laughs triumphantly)

00:57:53.986 --> 00:57:59.834
MATT: The light subsides and your vision returns.
You look to see hundreds of people dead at your

00:57:59.834 --> 00:58:13.863
feet. Farmers, children. You see Pike, motionless,
cast among the carnage. You want to scream, but

00:58:13.863 --> 00:58:20.224
instead you laugh, against your own judgment and
intent, like you're locked within yourself and

00:58:20.224 --> 00:58:27.153
have no control. And as you look up from the pile
of corpses at your feet, you see a towering figure

00:58:27.153 --> 00:58:37.287
before you, cast in furs and bone, standing even a
head and a half's height above you, is Kevdak,

00:58:37.287 --> 00:58:48.316
looking down at you with pride. The entire herd
steps up beside him, staring at you atop your

00:58:48.316 --> 00:59:01.509
throne of corpses, and the herd kneels. Kevdak
bows, looking up at you, smiling. "You. You have

00:59:01.509 --> 00:59:07.833
"finally made me proud, Grog."

00:59:07.833 --> 00:59:16.854
You wake up (gasp), spittle and sand and grit
mashed against your face. Who knows how long it's

00:59:16.854 --> 00:59:25.657
been, but it's been a while since you've had a
dream, let alone one like that.

00:59:25.657 --> 00:59:30.106
Now, as you all eventually come to in the morning,
having your evening's rest, you've recovered your

00:59:30.106 --> 00:59:35.899
hit points, your spells, all of the usual good
stuff, in a fantastic mansion. Maybe not the most

00:59:35.899 --> 00:59:41.232
fantastic rest for some of you, but a fantastic
mansion. You all eventually find your way to the

00:59:41.232 --> 00:59:46.887
breakfast nook, which is as extravagant as you
would imagine a Scanlan-based

00:59:46.887 --> 00:59:48.671
breakfast nook would be.

00:59:48.671 --> 00:59:53.793
TALIESIN: Green marble, silver tiling. Sorry,
carry on.

00:59:53.793 --> 00:59:55.178
MARISHA: Crystal chandelier.

00:59:55.178 --> 00:59:56.683
SAM: Waffle presses.

00:59:56.683 --> 01:00:01.233
MATT: There's a fantastic breakfast feast already
prepared, rows of servants along the walls waiting

01:00:01.233 --> 01:00:07.605
eagerly to attend to you guys as you sit down,
pouring fresh juices. It smells fantastic, and

01:00:07.605 --> 01:00:09.906
most of you look rested, except for a handful.

01:00:09.906 --> 01:00:14.357
SAM: Eat! Drink!

01:00:14.357 --> 01:00:16.821
LAURA: I come skipping into the room, for sure.

01:00:16.821 --> 01:00:18.732
TALIESIN: Good morning.

01:00:18.732 --> 01:00:20.766
SAM: You're looking delighted and delightful.

01:00:20.766 --> 01:00:23.185
LAURA: What a beautiful day it is!

01:00:23.185 --> 01:00:26.610
MARISHA: Do you have wine and ale at the breakfast
buffet?

01:00:26.610 --> 01:00:28.755
SAM: Sure, sure. There's mimosas, there's--

01:00:28.755 --> 01:00:30.171
MARISHA: I'll have a mimosa.

01:00:30.171 --> 01:00:32.470
TALIESIN: You've never heard of breakfast beer?

01:00:32.470 --> 01:00:38.383
SAM: Breakfast beer? Sure. There's milk from a cow
with a broken nose.

01:00:38.416 --> 01:00:45.995
LAURA: Oh, that is so sad. Can you heal it? Can it
be healed?

01:00:45.995 --> 01:00:50.754
SAM: It'll be fine. When we leave this place, all
these people die, anyway.

01:00:50.754 --> 01:00:54.298
TALIESIN: You're supposed to churn the milk after
it leaves the cow.

01:00:54.298 --> 01:00:59.162
LAURA: Wait, Scanlan, can we store things here, or
does it all disappear as soon as we leave?

01:00:59.162 --> 01:01:00.876
SAM: I don't know.

01:01:00.876 --> 01:01:02.463
MATT: You haven't tried it before.

01:01:02.463 --> 01:01:05.087
LAURA: We should leave something inconsequential.

01:01:05.087 --> 01:01:08.801
SAM: We'll leave Trinket, and then we'll try it
again, and if Trinket's still here, we'll know.

01:01:08.801 --> 01:01:11.536
MARISHA: Schrodinger's Trinket.

01:01:11.536 --> 01:01:13.992
SAM: It's just-- no?

01:01:13.992 --> 01:01:14.950
LAURA: No.

01:01:14.950 --> 01:01:17.062
SAM: All right. We'll leave the broom and see if
it's still here.

01:01:17.062 --> 01:01:18.604
LAURA: No, no, no, let's not.

01:01:18.604 --> 01:01:19.797
TALIESIN: What broom?

01:01:19.797 --> 01:01:23.769
SAM: Oh, Vex, is there something you'd like to
admit to the rest of the group? They'll see you

01:01:23.769 --> 01:01:25.699
use it sooner or later.

01:01:25.699 --> 01:01:31.199
MATT: You hear a voice go (grunt). Trinket's over
there, face covered in breakfast food, trying to

01:01:31.199 --> 01:01:36.620
sit at one of the edges of the table like a
person, the actual bowing of the wooden bench that

01:01:36.620 --> 01:01:39.650
Trinket's on, you hear the creaking as he moves
around in it.

01:01:39.650 --> 01:01:51.053
LAURA: Thank you, Scanlan, for making me feel...
So, guess what! I can fly! A-plus!

01:01:51.053 --> 01:01:53.356
TALIESIN: How did that happen?

01:01:53.356 --> 01:02:01.563
MARISHA: I had a really weird night, too. What
happened in your... because, I mean, flight?

01:02:01.563 --> 01:02:03.561
LAURA: Did you have a weird night? Do you want to
tell us about it?

01:02:03.561 --> 01:02:05.152
MARISHA: No, I want to hear about your night.

01:02:05.152 --> 01:02:06.994
TALIESIN: I think you go first.

01:02:06.994 --> 01:02:09.914
MARISHA: I want to learn how you fly.

01:02:09.914 --> 01:02:14.734
LAURA: Okay. So I sort of kind of tricked Gern,
I'm a terrible person.

01:02:14.734 --> 01:02:16.433
SAM: Gern, our friend.

01:02:16.433 --> 01:02:18.443
TRAVIS: You swallowed that last part. What did you
say?

01:02:18.443 --> 01:02:27.278
LAURA: I sort of kind of, this is the worst...
took something that wasn't mine? In a way. I mean,

01:02:27.278 --> 01:02:32.789
I was holding on to it, and then I slipped, and it
fell into the Bag of Holding.

01:02:32.789 --> 01:02:35.087
TRAVIS: Why is that bad?

01:02:35.087 --> 01:02:36.755
TALIESIN: You stole from a candlemaker?

01:02:36.755 --> 01:02:38.491
LAURA: I stole from a necromancer.

01:02:38.491 --> 01:02:41.987
TALIESIN: Slash candlemaker.

01:02:41.987 --> 01:02:45.764
LAURA: Yes. No, he was a nice guy.

01:02:45.764 --> 01:02:50.780
SAM: I think we should hear Vax's opinion of this.

01:02:50.780 --> 01:02:53.818
MARISHA: Vax, I think you were a bad influence.

01:02:53.818 --> 01:03:02.412
LIAM: I can't judge. I've done my share in the past. I
thought you were a little overly nice to him.

01:03:02.461 --> 01:03:04.743
TALIESIN: I mean, to be fair, we did steal a
carpet once.

01:03:04.743 --> 01:03:05.767
LAURA: We did.

01:03:05.767 --> 01:03:07.198
SAM: Did we steal that? I thought it was just a--

01:03:07.198 --> 01:03:09.246
MARISHA: We used that in an emergency.

01:03:09.246 --> 01:03:10.549
TRAVIS: We commandeered it.

01:03:10.549 --> 01:03:12.518
LAURA: We took it, Scanlan, and we didn't tell
Allura.

01:03:12.518 --> 01:03:14.208
TALIESIN: And then never gave it back.

01:03:14.208 --> 01:03:15.370
SAM: That's true.

01:03:15.370 --> 01:03:16.364
LAURA: We're terrible.

01:03:16.364 --> 01:03:20.142
LIAM: I don't think any of us can judge you,
Vex'ahlia, but it does strike me as a little bit

01:03:20.142 --> 01:03:23.212
odd, if nothing else.

01:03:23.212 --> 01:03:29.500
LAURA: I know. I know, I'm afraid these rogue
tendencies I've been learning from you, brother,

01:03:29.500 --> 01:03:35.903
maybe rubbed off a little bit. No, I just, I know
I shouldn't have.

01:03:35.903 --> 01:03:37.579
TRAVIS: I don't care.

01:03:37.579 --> 01:03:42.347
LAURA: I wanted to return it right away, and then
he wandered off. That's a lie, I didn't want to

01:03:42.347 --> 01:03:44.395
return it. But I did want to pay him!

01:03:44.395 --> 01:03:46.529
TRAVIS: I don't think you wanted to do that
either.

01:03:46.529 --> 01:03:50.783
LAURA: No, I did! I did, I wanted to pay him! But
he wandered away, and then I didn't pay him, and

01:03:50.783 --> 01:03:57.346
now I have this broom that I stole, and there's
really no way to return it. Well, I probably could

01:03:57.346 --> 01:03:59.947
find him, but I don't want to because now I can
fly, you guys.

01:03:59.947 --> 01:04:01.845
TRAVIS: Are you going to re-gift it?

01:04:01.845 --> 01:04:03.683
LAURA: No. I'm going to keep it.

01:04:03.683 --> 01:04:06.377
MARISHA: What do you say, Percy? I think it's kind
of funny.

01:04:06.377 --> 01:04:09.700
TALIESIN: Are you honestly asking my opinion? You
said what?

01:04:09.700 --> 01:04:13.648
LAURA: Actually, Percy, do you know-- I know you can
build things and make things wonderful.

01:04:13.648 --> 01:04:19.009
TALIESIN: Can you show me? What is this thing,
what did you steal? What is this thing?

01:04:19.009 --> 01:04:21.285
LAURA: I pull out the broom and I lift up in the
air.

01:04:21.285 --> 01:04:24.827
MATT: You guys watch as Vex all of a sudden
(whoosh) takes off above the breakfast room.

01:04:24.827 --> 01:04:25.832
TRAVIS: Sweet!

01:04:25.832 --> 01:04:28.641
MARISHA: All right, that is pretty cool, Vex.
That's pretty badass.

01:04:28.641 --> 01:04:30.336
TALIESIN: I don't know if I approve of the
metaphor, but that's--

01:04:30.336 --> 01:04:32.305
LIAM: What happens when you shoot a couple arrows
from up there?

01:04:32.305 --> 01:04:33.577
TRAVIS: Yeah, shoot me with an arrow!

01:04:33.577 --> 01:04:34.754
MARISHA: Yeah, shoot some arrows!

01:04:34.754 --> 01:04:36.712
TALIESIN: Okay, you're not holding onto the broom
anymore.

01:04:36.712 --> 01:04:38.823
LAURA: No, I've been practicing! I've been
practicing!

01:04:38.823 --> 01:04:44.829
MARISHA: I reach on the table and I grab what I'm
sure is a whole chicken sitting there.

01:04:44.829 --> 01:04:45.815
SAM: Sure.

01:04:45.815 --> 01:04:47.666
MARISHA: And I hold it up and I go--

01:04:47.666 --> 01:04:49.856
TALIESIN: Has it not occurred to you that you're
not going to be able to fly?

01:04:49.856 --> 01:04:53.947
LAURA: No, no, no, look! I'm not holding on,
Percy! Look at me, not holding on!

01:04:53.947 --> 01:04:56.118
MARISHA: Okay, Vex, ready? Ready, Vex? Vex?

01:04:56.118 --> 01:04:56.930
TALIESIN: Oh, dear.

01:04:56.930 --> 01:04:57.874
MARISHA: Trust.

01:04:57.874 --> 01:04:59.406
SAM: Watch your eyes. Watch your eyes.

01:04:59.406 --> 01:05:01.169
MARISHA: Trust Vex!

01:05:01.169 --> 01:05:04.197
MATT: All right, Laura, I want you to go ahead
and, first, roll a dexterity check.

01:05:04.197 --> 01:05:09.025
LAURA: Okay. Shut up! 13.

01:05:09.025 --> 01:05:16.076
MATT: 13, okay. You almost slip off the broom in
the process of drawing the arrow from the quiver.

01:05:16.076 --> 01:05:20.803
You catch yourself and just barely manage to pull
back and fire. I want you to go ahead and roll an

01:05:20.803 --> 01:05:22.588
attack with disadvantage.

01:05:22.588 --> 01:05:25.491
LAURA: Oh, man, disadvantage. Okay.

01:05:25.491 --> 01:05:30.877
MARISHA: Please, god, may your aim be true today,
Vex.

01:05:30.877 --> 01:05:33.165
LAURA: 16.

01:05:33.165 --> 01:05:38.665
MATT: 16. (impact) The arrow does get relatively
close to your hand, but it does

01:05:38.665 --> 01:05:40.365
stick into the turkey.

01:05:40.365 --> 01:05:43.416
MARISHA: She did it! I hand the chicken to
Scanlan.

01:05:43.416 --> 01:05:45.354
SAM: I start eating.

01:05:45.354 --> 01:05:47.307
TALIESIN: I pull the arrow out of the chicken.

01:05:47.307 --> 01:05:51.675
LIAM: Do it again! And I throw the chicken
closest to me into the air.

01:05:51.675 --> 01:05:52.867
LAURA: Oh, shit.

01:05:52.867 --> 01:05:53.840
SAM: A moving target!

01:05:53.840 --> 01:05:54.954
LAURA: Oh, god, okay.

01:05:54.954 --> 01:05:56.341
MATT: Okay, make another dexterity check.

01:05:56.341 --> 01:05:57.442
LAURA: Okay.

01:05:57.442 --> 01:05:58.622
SAM: There's lots of chickens, by the way.

01:05:58.622 --> 01:06:00.382
LAURA: Shit balls. 13.

01:06:00.382 --> 01:06:04.713
MATT: 13. Okay, this time, you start falling off
and you catch yourself entirely. The arrow just

01:06:04.713 --> 01:06:06.838
goes wide, you don't even get a chance to nock it
in the bow.

01:06:06.838 --> 01:06:08.739
LAURA: Mother bitch, I really need to work on
this! Okay.

01:06:08.739 --> 01:06:10.050
MARISHA: It'll take some practice.

01:06:10.050 --> 01:06:12.902
TALIESIN: I don't think this is-- this may be an
engineering issue.

01:06:12.902 --> 01:06:16.249
LAURA: Yes, Percy, this is the thing. Can you
build a seat on this?

01:06:16.249 --> 01:06:20.089
TALIESIN: I pull out my notepad and start
sketching.

01:06:20.089 --> 01:06:24.381
LAURA: What if you could build a seat, and then I
can sit on it instead of trying to sit on this

01:06:24.381 --> 01:06:25.509
tiny little stick?

01:06:25.509 --> 01:06:26.774
TALIESIN: Let me--

01:06:26.774 --> 01:06:28.063
SAM: Tinker?

01:06:28.063 --> 01:06:29.102
TALIESIN: Tinker.

01:06:29.102 --> 01:06:33.719
MARISHA: You know, beyond it being an engineering
issue, it might be a greed issue first.

01:06:33.719 --> 01:06:36.003
LAURA: Really?

01:06:36.003 --> 01:06:39.509
MARISHA: Look--

01:06:39.509 --> 01:06:41.445
LAURA: How's that mimosa treating you?

01:06:41.445 --> 01:06:49.693
MARISHA: It's phenomenal. It's been a long few
weeks. I don't care. I don't care. We're never

01:06:49.693 --> 01:06:53.338
going to see Gern again. I have so many other
things to care about.

01:06:53.338 --> 01:06:54.741
SAM: Oh, no, she's day drunk again.

01:06:54.741 --> 01:06:56.190
LAURA: Oh, no, are you already drunk, Keyleth?

01:06:56.190 --> 01:07:00.279
MARISHA: No! I'm just, it's been a long few--
Look.

01:07:00.279 --> 01:07:01.350
TRAVIS: Oh, Jesus!

01:07:01.350 --> 01:07:03.702
MARISHA: I don't care anymore.

01:07:03.702 --> 01:07:07.282
TRAVIS: How many was that? Just one, right? We've
been here for five minutes.

01:07:07.282 --> 01:07:08.651
LAURA: I float down.

01:07:08.651 --> 01:07:11.101
MARISHA: No! I just don't want you to die.

01:07:11.101 --> 01:07:14.247
LAURA: I float down eye-level, but I'm still
floating.

01:07:14.247 --> 01:07:18.871
MARISHA: I don't want you to die. I don't want you
to die because of your greed. I don't care that

01:07:18.871 --> 01:07:23.382
you have-- You look amazing. Doesn't she look
amazing?

01:07:23.382 --> 01:07:26.917
TALIESIN: Like a real hoverboard, is there a
chance this one might set on fire as well?

01:07:26.917 --> 01:07:28.747
LAURA: Why are you trying to be an asshole?

01:07:28.747 --> 01:07:29.905
TALIESIN: Sorry.

01:07:29.905 --> 01:07:37.513
LAURA: Here's the thing, Keyleth. I'm not afraid
to die anymore. I came to this realization. I've

01:07:37.513 --> 01:07:42.277
seen the other side. I've come to terms with it.

01:07:42.277 --> 01:07:46.103
MARISHA: Well, that's phenomenal that you've come
to terms with it! I don't know about the rest of

01:07:46.103 --> 01:07:48.434
us in the room that all watched you die, though.

01:07:48.434 --> 01:07:51.398
TALIESIN: I feel too guilty to say no to her. I'm
perfectly content to let this go.

01:07:51.398 --> 01:07:53.120
TRAVIS: It is pretty sweet, flying around like
that.

01:07:53.120 --> 01:07:54.161
LAURA: It's pretty wonderful.

01:07:54.161 --> 01:07:55.209
MARISHA: It's really cool.

01:07:55.209 --> 01:08:01.901
TALIESIN: She's an adult. Deep levels of arrested
development, but an adult nonetheless.

01:08:01.901 --> 01:08:04.049
MARISHA: I don't care about the broom.

01:08:04.049 --> 01:08:07.543
SAM: Keyleth, Vex swore to me that she would only
use it for good.

01:08:07.543 --> 01:08:10.964
LAURA: That's right. I'm not going to steal
anything while I'm riding on it.

01:08:10.964 --> 01:08:13.314
TALIESIN: Where would you put it, anyway? You
can't let go.

01:08:13.314 --> 01:08:16.709
MARISHA: Just don't get into trouble, I guess.

01:08:16.709 --> 01:08:20.088
LAURA: I'll practice as much as I can, and Percy's
going to help me.

01:08:20.088 --> 01:08:21.123
TALIESIN: Yes.

01:08:21.123 --> 01:08:22.954
LAURA: So I can be stable on this thing.

01:08:22.954 --> 01:08:25.443
TALIESIN: I may need some money, but we'll put
something together.

01:08:25.443 --> 01:08:26.937
LAURA: I will give you all the money you want.

01:08:26.937 --> 01:08:29.105
LIAM: Are you going to carry that on your back?

01:08:29.105 --> 01:08:30.427
LAURA: Maybe.

01:08:30.427 --> 01:08:32.828
LIAM: You'll look like a Byroden chimney sweep.

01:08:32.828 --> 01:08:35.727
LAURA: But I feel so good.

01:08:35.727 --> 01:08:42.959
MARISHA: You got out, you came out on top this
time. It might not happen next time.

01:08:42.959 --> 01:08:44.735
LAURA: I start eating while sitting on the broom.

01:08:44.735 --> 01:08:46.935
MARISHA: All right. I think she's listening to me.

01:08:46.935 --> 01:08:48.341
SAM: I think you broke through.

01:08:48.341 --> 01:08:49.376
MARISHA: I think I did.

01:08:49.376 --> 01:08:51.286
TALIESIN: I think you're learning to let people be
people.

01:08:51.286 --> 01:08:52.756
MARISHA: I don't care anymore.

01:08:52.756 --> 01:08:56.359
SAM: Oh, look, look! Another round of chickens has
just arrived for us to eat.

01:08:56.359 --> 01:08:57.964
MARISHA: Oh, chicken!

01:08:57.964 --> 01:09:01.982
SAM: I don't know what breakfast is, so I just
keep commanding them to make chickens.

01:09:01.982 --> 01:09:04.664
MATT: So much chicken, guys.

01:09:04.664 --> 01:09:06.609
LAURA: Where should we head to?

01:09:06.609 --> 01:09:13.057
SAM: What is our next-- Shoot, I kept a to-do list
for us, but I didn't bring it tonight.

01:09:13.057 --> 01:09:14.495
TRAVIS: (burps)

01:09:14.495 --> 01:09:17.218
SAM: Oh. I thought you were going to say
something. That was a belch?

01:09:17.218 --> 01:09:18.157
TRAVIS: Yeah.

01:09:18.157 --> 01:09:21.199
LAURA: Did you want to head back to-- Actually,
Keyleth, you said something weird happened last

01:09:21.199 --> 01:09:23.065
night for you as well.

01:09:23.065 --> 01:09:33.430
MARISHA: Yeah. Cerkonos stopped by.

01:09:33.430 --> 01:09:39.742
LAURA: Yeah? I look at my brother. All right,
cool. Keep going.

01:09:39.742 --> 01:09:51.223
MARISHA: Not... As my elder. He stopped by as my
respected elder. Do you all remember

01:09:51.223 --> 01:09:52.958
the name Raishan?

01:09:52.958 --> 01:09:54.274
TALIESIN: Yes.

01:09:54.274 --> 01:09:55.918
LAURA: That's one of the dragons.

01:09:55.918 --> 01:09:59.660
MARISHA: Apparently she's our little
infiltrator.

01:09:59.660 --> 01:10:01.519
LAURA: What do you mean?

01:10:01.519 --> 01:10:11.270
MARISHA: She came to the Fire Ashari, she came to
Pyrah, about four years ago, and the Ashari, being

01:10:11.270 --> 01:10:14.497
the adoptive people that we are, they took her in.

01:10:14.497 --> 01:10:15.867
LAURA: They adopted a dragon?

01:10:15.867 --> 01:10:18.202
MARISHA: They adopted a dragon.

01:10:18.202 --> 01:10:20.136
LAURA: How?

01:10:20.136 --> 01:10:22.960
TALIESIN: Do they think she's the one who
sabotaged the rift?

01:10:22.960 --> 01:10:29.606
MARISHA: They do. They were unaware that she was a
dragon.

01:10:29.606 --> 01:10:32.666
SAM: Does that make her the leader or something?
Is that how all the dragons got through? I'm still

01:10:32.666 --> 01:10:34.042
not quite sure.

01:10:34.042 --> 01:10:35.908
TALIESIN: It makes her the instigator, at the very
least.

01:10:35.908 --> 01:10:42.551
MARISHA: It makes her fairly close to Thordak, it
would seem. Apparently, when she came to the Fire

01:10:42.551 --> 01:10:45.832
Ashari, she was about 15 years old, and...

01:10:45.832 --> 01:10:47.392
SAM: As a dragon?

01:10:47.392 --> 01:10:48.530
TALIESIN: Visually.

01:10:48.530 --> 01:10:50.330
MARISHA: As a human woman.

01:10:50.330 --> 01:10:53.181
LAURA: So she was making it seem like she was 15.

01:10:53.181 --> 01:10:58.547
MARISHA: She was making it seem like she was 15,
and they started realizing that she possessed

01:10:58.547 --> 01:11:08.492
powers far beyond anything that they had seen
before, and then these powers began to exceed

01:11:08.492 --> 01:11:15.217
anything beyond our druidic capabilities. And it
would seem that they realized that too late.

01:11:15.217 --> 01:11:20.574
SAM: Did they say anything about her goals, or
motivations? Her ambitions?

01:11:20.574 --> 01:11:29.379
MARISHA: Cerkonos said one day they woke up and
the mountain was spewing fire, and was angry with

01:11:29.379 --> 01:11:42.838
lava, and when he went to investigate it, she was
there, ripping open the rift. And that was when

01:11:42.838 --> 01:11:46.719
everything happened. When he came to
consciousness, everything was destroyed, so that's

01:11:46.719 --> 01:11:52.297
all he saw. And she was gone. But we know where
she went next.

01:11:52.297 --> 01:11:55.483
TRAVIS: Where?

01:11:55.483 --> 01:11:58.864
SAM: To Emon.

01:11:58.864 --> 01:12:00.312
LAURA: Oh, eventually.

01:12:00.312 --> 01:12:01.453
SAM: Kill everybody.

01:12:01.453 --> 01:12:03.951
LAURA: Right. Totally. That day. The day.

01:12:03.951 --> 01:12:08.550
MARISHA: I was trying to skip exposition, I
thought you guys could fill in the blanks.

01:12:08.550 --> 01:12:12.231
TALIESIN: We thought you had new information
beyond that and would maybe want to add. It was

01:12:12.231 --> 01:12:13.635
certainly set up that way.

01:12:13.635 --> 01:12:15.572
MARISHA: Thank you. I'll work on that next time.

01:12:15.572 --> 01:12:16.812
TALIESIN: It was very leading.

01:12:16.812 --> 01:12:19.035
LAURA: Okay, well that's good to know.

01:12:19.035 --> 01:12:26.401
SAM: So perhaps we should inquire if you think
this-- Raishan?

01:12:26.401 --> 01:12:28.005
MARISHA: Raishan.

01:12:28.005 --> 01:12:34.859
SAM: Has tried to pretend to be a human woman in
any other place? Should we ask around, or was it

01:12:34.859 --> 01:12:39.767
just the one ruse here to gain entry for her
companions?

01:12:39.767 --> 01:12:42.324
MARISHA: I'm not sure.

01:12:42.324 --> 01:12:45.924
SAM: All right. Well, don't trust anyone.

01:12:45.924 --> 01:12:48.489
MARISHA: Don't trust anyone.

01:12:48.489 --> 01:12:49.678
LAURA: Got it.

01:12:49.678 --> 01:12:52.531
MATT: Servant rushes forward, "More chicken,
sir?"

01:12:52.531 --> 01:12:54.361
SAM: Keep it coming.

01:12:54.361 --> 01:12:55.503
MATT: "Right away."

01:12:55.503 --> 01:12:57.414
LAURA: Do you guys have vegetables, maybe? Any
vegetables?

01:12:57.414 --> 01:12:58.712
MATT: "Vegetables, sir?"

01:12:58.712 --> 01:13:01.865
SAM: I forgot to tell them to make them. Sorry.
It's all chicken.

01:13:01.865 --> 01:13:02.996
MATT: "Chicken it is."

01:13:02.996 --> 01:13:08.429
LAURA: Cool. Chicken and mimosas, it's my favorite
breakfast.

01:13:08.429 --> 01:13:10.256
MARISHA: And waffles.

01:13:10.256 --> 01:13:15.432
SAM: Oh, waffles too? Chicken and waffles, that's
right. Maybe someone else should be in charge of

01:13:15.432 --> 01:13:20.206
the food next time we come here. My tastes are a
little--

01:13:20.206 --> 01:13:21.585
TALIESIN: Base?

01:13:21.585 --> 01:13:22.751
LAURA: Little?

01:13:22.751 --> 01:13:24.111
SAM: Singular.

01:13:24.111 --> 01:13:30.337
MARISHA: And one thing that this does confirm is
that this has been a plan that's been in the

01:13:30.337 --> 01:13:33.049
process for a very, very long time.

01:13:33.049 --> 01:13:35.715
SAM: No, I just came up with the chicken this
morning when I woke up.

01:13:35.715 --> 01:13:37.536
LAURA: Where are we going next, you guys?

01:13:37.536 --> 01:13:45.492
SAM: Grog had some brass knuckles to get. Was that
a thing? Did we get those?

01:13:45.492 --> 01:13:50.901
TRAVIS: No. We haven't gotten those yet. But
there's other things to explore.

01:13:50.901 --> 01:13:56.502
SAM: All right. Wait, did we have to go make a
trip to anyone else's homeland? How's Whitestone?

01:13:56.502 --> 01:14:01.366
LAURA: We need to talk to a sphinx. A sphinx's
boyfriend.

01:14:01.366 --> 01:14:05.107
SAM: Oh, that's right. Maybe that should be our
next--

01:14:05.107 --> 01:14:07.154
MARISHA: What was his name? Hang on.

01:14:07.154 --> 01:14:11.525
SAM: And what were we trying to get there? Another
one of the articles of confederation?

01:14:11.525 --> 01:14:16.648
MARISHA: We need the Titanstone Knuckles of Kord,
which Kevdak has.

01:14:16.648 --> 01:14:18.581
TRAVIS: Yep.

01:14:18.581 --> 01:14:21.065
LAURA: That's with your tribe.

01:14:21.065 --> 01:14:22.183
TRAVIS: Yeah.

01:14:22.183 --> 01:14:24.125
SAM: Okay, but then there's the sphinx.

01:14:24.125 --> 01:14:25.871
LIAM: Time for a family reunion, Grog.

01:14:25.871 --> 01:14:27.145
SAM: What's that, Vax?

01:14:27.145 --> 01:14:31.531
LIAM: I said it's time for a family reunion, Grog.
Are you ready for that, or do you want to put that

01:14:31.531 --> 01:14:33.060
off a bit?

01:14:33.060 --> 01:14:39.281
TRAVIS: Oh, no, I mean. Whenever. It's. You know.

01:14:39.281 --> 01:14:43.175
LAURA: So do you want to go now, or do you want to
maybe swing by somewhere?

01:14:43.175 --> 01:14:44.959
TALIESIN: It's either that or the library, I
imagine.

01:14:44.959 --> 01:14:46.677
TRAVIS: You want to go to the library?

01:14:46.677 --> 01:14:49.724
TALIESIN: I was just saying that it's either that
or the library.

01:14:49.724 --> 01:14:52.911
SAM: So it's Grog's herd or the sphinx to get
something.

01:14:52.911 --> 01:14:54.909
LAURA: We'll remember.

01:14:54.909 --> 01:15:02.816
SAM: On the way. And then, or, TBD, find something
else to do. I guess Grog's thing is the most

01:15:02.816 --> 01:15:06.685
promising. We know that there's Knuckles there, we
know that there's people we'll know there.

01:15:06.685 --> 01:15:11.756
LAURA: Well, it's all actually around Westruun,
right? Aren't your people around Westruun?

01:15:11.756 --> 01:15:13.257
TRAVIS: You know, they roam.

01:15:13.257 --> 01:15:15.102
LAURA: So we have to find them.

01:15:15.102 --> 01:15:16.077
TRAVIS: Yeah.

01:15:16.077 --> 01:15:19.437
LAURA: Last time we ran into them, wasn't it on
the way to Kraghammer?

01:15:19.437 --> 01:15:20.852
TALIESIN: From Westruun.

01:15:20.852 --> 01:15:23.943
MARISHA: Odessa's mate is south of the
Frostweald.

01:15:23.943 --> 01:15:25.251
LAURA: I think it was.

01:15:25.251 --> 01:15:26.342
TRAVIS: Was it?

01:15:26.342 --> 01:15:29.200
LIAM: Yeah, it was. On the way to Kraghammer,
that's right.

01:15:29.200 --> 01:15:31.501
SAM: Is Frostweald near Kraghammer as well?

01:15:31.501 --> 01:15:32.879
LAURA: The Frostweald is--

01:15:32.879 --> 01:15:34.207
MATT: South of Westruun.

01:15:34.207 --> 01:15:35.558
LAURA: South of Westruun, yes.

01:15:35.558 --> 01:15:38.640
TALIESIN: So let's make our way to Westruun, I
suppose, then.

01:15:38.640 --> 01:15:43.556
SAM: And that's in the direction of both Grog's
herd and the Frostweald?

01:15:43.556 --> 01:15:45.473
LAURA: Potentially? Well, Grog would know.

01:15:45.473 --> 01:15:47.308
TRAVIS: What?

01:15:47.308 --> 01:15:50.074
LAURA: Cool. Yes, I think Grog really wants to
go.

01:15:50.074 --> 01:15:51.680
SAM: Yeah, we should probably go there.

01:15:51.680 --> 01:15:52.627
LAURA: Yeah.

01:15:52.627 --> 01:15:53.619
SAM: Let's do that.

01:15:53.619 --> 01:15:59.116
MATT: Your herd wanders all across the Silvercut
Roadway, that whole area to the west of Westruun,

01:15:59.116 --> 01:16:01.883
south of Kraghammer, east of Emon, that vicinity.

01:16:01.883 --> 01:16:03.969
TRAVIS: They wander there.

01:16:03.969 --> 01:16:05.227
LAURA: Around there.

01:16:05.227 --> 01:16:06.168
TRAVIS: Yep.

01:16:06.168 --> 01:16:07.822
LAURA: Okay.

01:16:07.822 --> 01:16:16.964
TRAVIS: But look, I was thinking. It might be a
thing when we find them, right? So picture this.

01:16:16.964 --> 01:16:26.845
Me, and then a lot of other me's, and they're all
really big and angry. So if we want to do anything

01:16:26.845 --> 01:16:28.706
else before that happens--

01:16:28.706 --> 01:16:32.966
SAM: You think they'll attack us? But we're with
you! You're our ally!

01:16:32.966 --> 01:16:41.549
TRAVIS: Yeah, and I'm a super cool, awesome, fun
guy, but we didn't really leave in the best terms.

01:16:41.549 --> 01:16:42.934
LAURA: Oh, weren't you--

01:16:42.934 --> 01:16:47.874
TRAVIS: Ass-kicked, yeah. All left for dead,
pretty much.

01:16:47.874 --> 01:16:55.760
MARISHA: You know what, Grog, it's been a while.
Why exactly were you beat up and kicked out of

01:16:55.760 --> 01:16:57.180
your herd?

01:16:57.180 --> 01:17:03.875
TRAVIS: Right, so I was a bit younger, and we were
wandering through the woods, and we came upon this

01:17:03.875 --> 01:17:12.792
little old bearded thing, right? And he was
carrying groceries, like food and stuff, and

01:17:12.792 --> 01:17:18.044
everybody was a little hammered from boozing, and
they were like, hey, let's kill the little thing,

01:17:18.044 --> 01:17:21.889
and we'll string him up and see what his insides
look like! And normally I'm like, yay, I'll wear

01:17:21.889 --> 01:17:30.935
him as a hat! But he looked really sweet, and I
felt bad, so I said we shouldn't do that. And...

01:17:30.935 --> 01:17:39.961
They didn't like that answer. My uncle in
particular, he didn't like that, so he made me

01:17:39.961 --> 01:17:43.667
fight my cousin, his son.

01:17:43.667 --> 01:17:45.545
LAURA: And?

01:17:45.545 --> 01:17:49.315
TRAVIS: That wasn't bad, I handled that. It was
not a problem.

01:17:49.315 --> 01:17:53.368
MARISHA: Okay. So they might have a grudge about
that.

01:17:53.368 --> 01:17:58.105
TRAVIS: No, there's no grudge. They pretty much
think I'm dead, because after I whooped his son's

01:17:58.105 --> 01:17:59.717
ass, he whooped my ass.

01:17:59.717 --> 01:18:01.239
LAURA: Oh.

01:18:01.239 --> 01:18:02.243
TRAVIS: Yeah.

01:18:02.243 --> 01:18:03.823
TALIESIN: We have a thing for that.

01:18:03.823 --> 01:18:04.821
SAM: We do?

01:18:04.821 --> 01:18:06.501
TALIESIN: Can I borrow your hat?

01:18:06.501 --> 01:18:08.729
SAM: Of course you can borrow my hat.

01:18:08.729 --> 01:18:11.048
LAURA: The Hat of Disguise?

01:18:11.048 --> 01:18:15.682
TALIESIN: If you don't want to have an immediate
confrontation with your family, there's no

01:18:15.682 --> 01:18:18.866
particular reason why they have to know you're
alive yet at all.

01:18:18.866 --> 01:18:24.319
SAM: You could wear this hat. Might not fit on
your head, you could maybe put it on one of your

01:18:24.319 --> 01:18:25.418
knuckles.

01:18:25.418 --> 01:18:27.408
TRAVIS: I'm not hiding from my herd.

01:18:27.408 --> 01:18:32.590
TALIESIN: You were giving off the impression of
one who is looking forward to putting something off.

01:18:32.590 --> 01:18:35.230
TRAVIS: I was, was I?

01:18:35.230 --> 01:18:40.554
TALIESIN: You were. You're not anymore, as if
you've been dared, somehow.

01:18:40.554 --> 01:18:42.977
LAURA: Very big.

01:18:42.977 --> 01:18:50.598
SAM: If you're too scared to do it, we can go
elsewhere. Sorry, I will never say that again.

01:18:50.598 --> 01:19:07.986
TRAVIS: No, I'm excited to go. I want to go. We
should go. You know, what we need is the wolf.

01:19:07.986 --> 01:19:09.457
LAURA: The wolf?

01:19:09.457 --> 01:19:10.862
TRAVIS: Yeah. We need--

01:19:10.862 --> 01:19:12.336
LAURA: Oh, the wolf in Whitestone?

01:19:12.336 --> 01:19:16.398
TRAVIS: Yeah. Don't they smell shit? He could help
us find them.

01:19:16.398 --> 01:19:17.750
LAURA: Well, Trinket can smell.

01:19:17.750 --> 01:19:22.124
MARISHA: And I can also theoretically turn into a
wolf to help us find things.

01:19:22.124 --> 01:19:28.014
TRAVIS: I mean, if you want to. I don't know how
long it's been since he's seen a she-wolf, so, you know.

01:19:28.014 --> 01:19:30.462
LIAM: Grog.

01:19:30.462 --> 01:19:32.796
MARISHA: I was talking as in--

01:19:32.796 --> 01:19:35.620
TRAVIS: I mean, it's very generous.

01:19:35.620 --> 01:19:40.205
LIAM: Just out of curiosity, we weren't going to
walk in and negotiate with your uncle. He's not

01:19:40.205 --> 01:19:45.266
going to give us these Knuckles. He's a proud
owner of them, yes?

01:19:45.266 --> 01:19:46.580
TRAVIS: Yep.

01:19:46.580 --> 01:19:50.594
LIAM: And how many are in the herd, roughly?

01:19:50.594 --> 01:19:55.004
TRAVIS: What's a number bigger than five?

01:19:55.004 --> 01:19:56.181
LAURA: Six?

01:19:56.181 --> 01:19:57.649
TRAVIS: Yeah, it's like six.

01:19:57.649 --> 01:20:05.173
MARISHA: You mean it's like at least six? Or
possibly more than six? How fast actually is the

01:20:05.173 --> 01:20:08.771
reproduction process of goliaths?

01:20:08.771 --> 01:20:12.174
TALIESIN: Are there more people in your herd or
fingers on your hand?

01:20:12.174 --> 01:20:18.887
LIAM: I hold up Scanlan's hands and then I hold up
my hands behind them so that all 20 fingers are

01:20:18.887 --> 01:20:23.972
waggling. Grog, are there more than this many in
your herd?

01:20:23.972 --> 01:20:25.493
TRAVIS: Yeah, six.

01:20:25.493 --> 01:20:26.643
LAURA: Okay.

01:20:26.643 --> 01:20:28.226
TALIESIN: He's counting hands, not fingers.

01:20:28.226 --> 01:20:31.087
LAURA: Oh. I hold up mine, too.

01:20:31.087 --> 01:20:33.239
SAM: We all hold up our hands.

01:20:33.239 --> 01:20:34.563
LAURA: How many hands is that?

01:20:34.563 --> 01:20:37.773
LIAM: We're doing rakshasa hands. Grog, is there
more of them than rakshasa hands?

01:20:37.773 --> 01:20:40.387
TRAVIS: That's closer, yeah. It's been a long
time.

01:20:40.387 --> 01:20:43.138
MARISHA: Yeah, this could be bad. This could be
bad.

01:20:43.138 --> 01:20:45.957
TALIESIN: We could attempt to steal them.

01:20:45.957 --> 01:20:49.976
LAURA: Steal from the goliaths? That could work.

01:20:49.976 --> 01:20:51.342
MARISHA: How easy is that?

01:20:51.342 --> 01:20:53.717
LAURA: Does he wear them all the time? Does he put
them in a chest?

01:20:53.717 --> 01:20:55.668
TRAVIS: I mean, they're pretty smart, they're like
me.

01:20:55.668 --> 01:20:58.267
LAURA: Yeah. You're right.

01:20:58.267 --> 01:21:03.283
LIAM: I don't think it's going to be pretty no
matter what we do, but I actually think trying to

01:21:03.283 --> 01:21:11.515
steal them might be a better angle than going
toe-to-toe with "six" goliaths. I just did air quotes.

01:21:11.515 --> 01:21:13.265
LAURA: If six is the right number.

01:21:13.265 --> 01:21:17.680
TRAVIS: Here's the thing, though. Normally, if you
try and steal something, or if you try and break

01:21:17.680 --> 01:21:24.479
the rules and you're like Keyleth and you get
arrested every time, arrested ain't so bad. They

01:21:24.479 --> 01:21:30.446
don't really arrest you. They, like, open you up
and use you as an appetizer.

01:21:30.446 --> 01:21:32.415
LAURA: As a hat.

01:21:32.415 --> 01:21:39.832
TRAVIS: Yeah. That was my thing, though. So I'm a
little nervous about that.

01:21:39.832 --> 01:21:42.818
LIAM: We just have to pick the least terrible
option right now.

01:21:42.818 --> 01:21:47.494
MARISHA: Well, we need these vestiges. We cannot
do anything without these vestiges.

01:21:47.494 --> 01:21:52.639
SAM: It seems to me that no matter where we go, we
are putting ourselves in peril.

01:21:52.639 --> 01:21:54.150
TRAVIS: Yep.

01:21:54.150 --> 01:21:57.653
SAM: So it's really just a question of which peril
do we want to face first.

01:21:57.653 --> 01:22:01.692
MARISHA: And don't we theoretically need the
vestiges before we go visit Odessa's boyfriend?

01:22:01.692 --> 01:22:04.941
SAM: I thought Odessa's boyfriend had a vestige.

01:22:04.941 --> 01:22:06.979
LAURA: No, he has locations of other vestiges.

01:22:06.979 --> 01:22:08.729
TRAVIS: Odessa? Osysa.

01:22:08.729 --> 01:22:09.829
MATT: Osysa.

01:22:09.829 --> 01:22:10.950
MARISHA: Sorry.

01:22:10.950 --> 01:22:14.325
TRAVIS: Shit, that's what I would call her.
Odessa.

01:22:14.325 --> 01:22:24.760
LAURA: I feel like Pike would want to come with
us, Grog. You're very dear to her.

01:22:24.760 --> 01:22:31.266
MARISHA: But wasn't Pike and her grandfather the
reason?

01:22:31.266 --> 01:22:35.651
TRAVIS: It was Pike's grandfather, yeah. And plus,
she's a healer.

01:22:35.651 --> 01:22:40.340
TALIESIN: At the very least, let's make our way to
Westruun, then. Let's get that far and see what's--

01:22:40.340 --> 01:22:43.975
MARISHA: Well, remember Westruun is under dragons
right now.

01:22:43.975 --> 01:22:45.809
SAM: We can instantly transport anywhere.

01:22:45.809 --> 01:22:48.246
LAURA: You know of trees outside of Westruun?

01:22:48.246 --> 01:22:53.668
MARISHA: I can, but it's under dragon reign. In
fact, isn't that where Raishan stopped off?

01:22:53.668 --> 01:22:59.363
MATT: No, the scrying that you saw was Umbrasyl,
the black dragon, that took up residence, it

01:22:59.363 --> 01:23:06.420
seems, in Gatshadow, the mountain north of
Westruun, at the base of the Cloudkeep mountain range.

01:23:06.420 --> 01:23:08.285
LAURA: And Gatshadow is where Grog got his scar,
right?

01:23:08.285 --> 01:23:10.703
MATT: Yep, that's where you guys initially... that
happened.

01:23:10.703 --> 01:23:20.512
TRAVIS: All right. Fuck. Look, if there's a lot of
them, and only a handful of us, it's not usually

01:23:20.512 --> 01:23:28.446
customary to have two sides go at each other. If
we want those Knuckles, I'm pretty sure it might

01:23:28.446 --> 01:23:38.373
have to be one on one. Now, I know I can totally
take my uncle. But I wouldn't mind if we found a

01:23:38.373 --> 01:23:46.517
few extra-credit items before we did that just in
case I have the flu that morning, or it burns when

01:23:46.517 --> 01:23:49.480
I pee. Just something to take the edge off.

01:23:49.480 --> 01:23:51.048
SAM: So sphinx first.

01:23:51.048 --> 01:23:53.977
TRAVIS: If that's what you want to do, then yeah!

01:23:53.977 --> 01:23:55.928
SAM: Say no more.

01:23:55.928 --> 01:24:01.291
MARISHA: Okay. And did we also want to check out
the Cobalt Reserve which was in Westruun, or did

01:24:01.291 --> 01:24:03.345
Allura already handle that and we're cool?

01:24:03.345 --> 01:24:05.015
LAURA: Allura, I think, handled that, right? You
saw her.

01:24:05.015 --> 01:24:10.333
MARISHA: She was there and it looked pretty
trashed. It looked like she grabbed a lot of the

01:24:10.333 --> 01:24:12.017
last of the good things.

01:24:12.017 --> 01:24:15.906
SAM: All right. Let's go to the sphinx, then.
Where's that? The Frostweald, we've been there.

01:24:15.906 --> 01:24:17.837
LAURA: Yes, we have been to the Frostweald.

01:24:17.837 --> 01:24:19.349
SAM: Do you remember any trees there?

01:24:19.349 --> 01:24:22.946
LAURA: Frostweald is where Grog mugged down with
the nymph, right?

01:24:22.946 --> 01:24:25.057
LIAM: Allegedly.

01:24:25.057 --> 01:24:26.147
LAURA: Allegedly.

01:24:26.147 --> 01:24:27.398
SAM: We'll never know.

01:24:27.398 --> 01:24:29.101
TRAVIS: Grog does not kiss and tell.

01:24:29.101 --> 01:24:30.048
LAURA: Yes, you do.

