01:38:22.198 --> 01:38:23.623
TALIESIN: You don't know we're here anymore.

01:38:23.623 --> 01:38:32.677
MATT: Where'd the party go? You all begin to weave
your way through the various lines of high-stalk

01:38:32.677 --> 01:38:37.849
crop. Where are you heading? Are you heading in
towards the city, or are you heading

01:38:37.849 --> 01:38:38.915
towards the farmers?

01:38:38.915 --> 01:38:43.650
LAURA: We just want to sit here for a minute and
talk about it. Can we just say, so here's the

01:38:43.650 --> 01:38:49.030
thing. Those guards are attacking the farmers. I'm
pretty sure they're using slave labor at this

01:38:49.030 --> 01:38:57.082
point. Kind of like you, Scanlan! Slave labor to
provide food for the city. Vax really wanted to

01:38:57.082 --> 01:39:01.974
stop down, but the thing is, if we kill the guards
and set the farmers free, everybody in the city

01:39:01.974 --> 01:39:04.628
might starve. It's a tough situation right now.

01:39:04.628 --> 01:39:07.748
TALIESIN: Or they might just send more guards,
once they know that one's been killed, and then

01:39:07.748 --> 01:39:09.270
kill everybody involved.

01:39:09.270 --> 01:39:14.440
LAURA: I'm afraid right now I don't know what all
we can do in this town until we can defeat the

01:39:14.440 --> 01:39:17.662
dragon, which unfortunately is rather close.

01:39:17.662 --> 01:39:19.298
MARISHA: It's a bigger problem.

01:39:19.298 --> 01:39:22.742
TALIESIN: We can't do anything for them right now
until we actually know what's happening.

01:39:22.742 --> 01:39:26.392
MATT: As you guys are having this conversation,
you can see there's a slight rustle, and a

01:39:26.392 --> 01:39:32.037
farmer comes across, carrying a small satchel as
he's picking things off of one of the nearby areas.

01:39:32.037 --> 01:39:33.636
TRAVIS: Is he close to us?

01:39:33.636 --> 01:39:35.219
MATT: About 15 feet from you.

01:39:35.219 --> 01:39:36.242
MARISHA: Does he see us?

01:39:36.242 --> 01:39:37.567
MATT: He doesn't seem to notice you guys.

01:39:37.567 --> 01:39:40.977
LAURA: I mean, we can tell him to hold out hope.

01:39:40.977 --> 01:39:43.913
TALIESIN: Maybe he knows what's going on.

01:39:43.913 --> 01:39:48.365
LAURA: He could also be one of the assholes that's
serving the dragon, just like people in Emon.

01:39:48.365 --> 01:39:55.445
TRAVIS: I go (clicks).

01:39:55.445 --> 01:40:02.210
MATT: The farmer turns. (gasps) You now see him.
It's a man in his late 40s, early 50s, gray beard.

01:40:02.210 --> 01:40:05.514
TRAVIS: Shh! Help me out. Shh.

01:40:05.514 --> 01:40:06.490
MATT: "Yeah..."

01:40:06.490 --> 01:40:07.419
TRAVIS: Shh!

01:40:07.419 --> 01:40:08.470
LAURA: Act natural!

01:40:08.470 --> 01:40:09.401
TRAVIS: Keep picking!

01:40:09.401 --> 01:40:10.601
LAURA: Keep picking!

01:40:10.601 --> 01:40:12.005
MATT: He keeps picking.

01:40:12.005 --> 01:40:16.992
LAURA: Hey, you. Do you like the dragon or do you
not like the dragon?

01:40:16.992 --> 01:40:21.378
TALIESIN: In the interest of the internet, we
should probably do stage whispers.

01:40:21.378 --> 01:40:23.769
LAURA: Do you like the dragon or do you not like
the dragon?

01:40:23.769 --> 01:40:30.084
MATT: You can see there's some heavy bruising on
his face and part of his cheek is swollen. He

01:40:30.084 --> 01:40:36.114
goes, "It would be hard around these parts to find
someone who likes a dragon, let alone that one."

01:40:36.114 --> 01:40:37.333
LAURA: Good.

01:40:37.333 --> 01:40:40.017
MATT: "Not the worst of the worries right now,
though."

01:40:40.017 --> 01:40:41.280
LAURA: What's the worst?

01:40:41.280 --> 01:40:43.503
MATT: "The ones who work for him."

01:40:43.503 --> 01:40:49.768
LAURA: Right. So you have to provide food for
everybody living in the city? Is that how that goes?

01:40:49.768 --> 01:40:55.580
MATT: "Every one of them. Otherwise they just go
ahead and steal from whoever's nearby. Isn't a

01:40:55.580 --> 01:40:58.189
"caravan that's made their way past Westruun in the
past week."

01:40:58.189 --> 01:41:09.409
LAURA: Well, here's the thing. We're trying to
help you. We're trying to find a way to (clicking)

01:41:09.409 --> 01:41:16.625
(choking) kill the fucks. You get me? Ill-kay the
agons-dray.

01:41:16.625 --> 01:41:19.868
MATT: Drops the fruit he has in his hand. "Please!
Please help us, please!"

01:41:19.868 --> 01:41:28.308
LAURA: Act natural! Keep picking, keep picking, keep
picking! We want to help you. We really, really,

01:41:28.308 --> 01:41:29.902
really want to help you.

01:41:29.902 --> 01:41:31.178
MATT: "They have my daughter."

01:41:31.178 --> 01:41:32.174
LAURA: Oh, shit.

01:41:32.174 --> 01:41:33.082
TALIESIN: Who's in charge?

01:41:33.082 --> 01:41:34.410
SAM: Who has your daughter?

01:41:34.410 --> 01:41:35.754
TALIESIN: No daughters right now.

01:41:35.754 --> 01:41:37.430
MATT: "Those beasts."

01:41:37.430 --> 01:41:38.982
SAM: Beasts? What beasts?

01:41:38.982 --> 01:41:41.484
LAURA: The guards? They're keeping your daughter?

01:41:41.484 --> 01:41:43.361
MATT: "Keeping a lot of people."

01:41:43.361 --> 01:41:45.002
TRAVIS: Do you know where they keep them?

01:41:45.002 --> 01:41:48.821
MATT: He leans over, nudges towards the direction
of the city.

01:41:48.821 --> 01:41:51.899
TALIESIN: Who's in charge?

01:41:51.899 --> 01:41:53.996
MATT: "I don't know his name."

01:41:53.996 --> 01:42:00.115
SAM: And that spot that we saw, just outside of
town, that's where gold is given to the dragon? Do

01:42:00.115 --> 01:42:01.866
you know anything of that?

01:42:01.866 --> 01:42:05.316
MATT: He looks a little confused. "I don't know.
They just take what we have."

01:42:05.316 --> 01:42:08.597
LIAM: The guy, you don't know his name. What does
he look like? Where have you seen him?

01:42:08.597 --> 01:42:10.336
LAURA: Keep your voice down!

01:42:10.336 --> 01:42:15.674
LIAM: I'm talking through Skype, so it's a little
more difficult for me!

01:42:15.674 --> 01:42:18.916
MATT: Who are you talking about?

01:42:18.916 --> 01:42:27.534
LIAM: The guy who's got your child. You don't know
his name. What does he look like? Where have you

01:42:27.534 --> 01:42:28.870
seen him?

01:42:28.870 --> 01:42:33.407
MATT: "I don't know. They're all different types,
I haven't seen the one who has them. They have them."

01:42:33.407 --> 01:42:36.587
LAURA: They, the guards? The people that serve the
dragon?

01:42:36.587 --> 01:42:40.227
MARISHA: What type of people are they interested
in?

01:42:40.227 --> 01:42:47.406
MATT: "Half-orcs-- Interested in? Whoever keeps
him at bay. I don't know, they take whoever seems

01:42:47.406 --> 01:42:51.891
"useful. Sometimes they take them and slaughter
them before us as a warning."

01:42:51.891 --> 01:42:53.670
MARISHA: Then why did they take your daughter?

01:42:53.670 --> 01:42:55.513
MATT: "I don't want to think about it."

01:42:55.513 --> 01:42:56.964
LAURA: To keep him working!

01:42:56.964 --> 01:43:02.321
TRAVIS: Look. Say we were really bored, and we
wanted to get you your family back.

01:43:02.321 --> 01:43:04.590
Where would you go?

01:43:04.590 --> 01:43:14.580
MATT: He points over to the city. "But there's one
right out..." And you see him pointing angrily

01:43:14.580 --> 01:43:18.586
around the corner, probably to the one that you
saw on the outskirts of the farm area you guys

01:43:18.586 --> 01:43:20.111
came down in.

01:43:20.111 --> 01:43:23.134
TALIESIN: Let's go to the city then, I suppose.

01:43:23.134 --> 01:43:24.038
SAM: Wait, what?

01:43:24.038 --> 01:43:25.146
LAURA: There's a dragon!

01:43:25.146 --> 01:43:28.049
SAM: To do what, to attack half-orcs that work for
a dragon?

01:43:28.049 --> 01:43:29.780
LAURA: Farmer. What's your name?

01:43:29.780 --> 01:43:31.179
MATT: "Reginald."

01:43:31.179 --> 01:43:36.657
LAURA: Reginald. Reginald, we want to help. How
often do you see the dragon flying around?

01:43:36.657 --> 01:43:40.845
MATT: "Once every couple days, maybe."

01:43:40.845 --> 01:43:43.459
LAURA: Once every couple days. When was the last
time you saw him?

01:43:43.459 --> 01:43:52.728
MATT: "About half a day ago. Dusk yesterday. I
don't know. We all stay inside around that time

01:43:52.728 --> 01:43:54.020
"just in case."

01:43:54.020 --> 01:43:58.231
MARISHA: Does he have patrols? Does he have
wyverns working for him as well, that fly around?

01:43:58.231 --> 01:44:04.440
MATT: "I haven't seen anything flying but the
dragon. There was a huge fight not more than a

01:44:04.440 --> 01:44:09.510
"week ago between these people and that thing. They
seem to have come to an accord."

01:44:09.510 --> 01:44:11.026
MARISHA: These people?

01:44:11.026 --> 01:44:12.553
SAM: The orcs?

01:44:12.553 --> 01:44:19.169
MATT: "The orcs, the whatever they are. The big
strong angry ones that keep taking all of our stuff."

01:44:19.169 --> 01:44:21.219
MARISHA: Oh, no.

01:44:21.219 --> 01:44:22.706
LAURA: (gasps)

01:44:22.706 --> 01:44:25.435
SAM: What, what?

01:44:25.435 --> 01:44:26.576
LAURA: What do they look like?

01:44:26.576 --> 01:44:28.466
MARISHA: Do they look like him, maybe?

01:44:28.466 --> 01:44:29.394
MATT: "Some do."

01:44:29.394 --> 01:44:30.904
TRAVIS: Oh, fuck me.

01:44:30.904 --> 01:44:35.343
LAURA: Shit.

01:44:35.343 --> 01:44:39.068
TRAVIS: Fuck, fuck, fuck!

01:44:39.068 --> 01:44:46.686
MATT: "The dragon came in and tore everything
down."

01:44:46.686 --> 01:44:50.008
TRAVIS: Damn it. Shit hammer.

01:44:50.008 --> 01:44:56.735
MATT: "Burned, liquefied, dissolved portions of
this city, people screaming. And then it left.

01:44:56.735 --> 01:44:58.691
"Both of them."

01:44:58.691 --> 01:45:04.384
SAM: You'll be okay. We're going to keep going.
Good luck.

01:45:04.384 --> 01:45:05.593
TRAVIS: No, wait, wait.

01:45:05.593 --> 01:45:06.675
LAURA: Scanlan!

01:45:06.675 --> 01:45:10.905
SAM: No, we have to keep going. We can't face
these goliaths and dragons and orc guards!

01:45:10.905 --> 01:45:12.576
This is craziness!

01:45:12.576 --> 01:45:14.358
MARISHA: One of the dragons was green?

01:45:14.358 --> 01:45:16.830
MATT: "From what we saw."

01:45:16.830 --> 01:45:17.936
LAURA: Green and a black.

01:45:17.936 --> 01:45:21.547
MATT: "Green and a black. I think a white one, but
that one kept going.

01:45:21.547 --> 01:45:23.102
SAM: I mean, we'll be fine.

01:45:23.102 --> 01:45:24.622
MARISHA: And the green one kept going?

01:45:24.622 --> 01:45:32.165
MATT: "All of them kept going. We thought we were
safe. We tried to re-gather. And then, within a

01:45:32.226 --> 01:45:40.565
"day, a bunch of these bastards came and took what
was left. Slaughtering, stealing."

01:45:40.565 --> 01:45:49.673
TRAVIS: We've got to go get his kid.

01:45:49.673 --> 01:45:52.496
LAURA: I feel like we have to help them. We have
to help them!

01:45:52.496 --> 01:45:59.638
MARISHA: Oh man. I feel like you all are talking
like I normally do, and I'm talking like Grog

01:45:59.638 --> 01:46:01.944
normally does. This is such a weird day.

01:46:01.944 --> 01:46:04.297
SAM: No, you're using way too many prepositions.

01:46:04.297 --> 01:46:07.119
TRAVIS: You said there are a lot of people that
look like me.

01:46:07.119 --> 01:46:14.980
MATT: "From what I've seen. I don't go too far
into town, they keep me out here, but I've seen a few."

01:46:14.980 --> 01:46:18.005
LAURA: I'm keeping an eye out for the guard. I
want to keep an eye out for the guard, make sure

01:46:18.005 --> 01:46:19.110
he's not noticing.

01:46:19.110 --> 01:46:20.103
MATT: Perception check.

01:46:20.103 --> 01:46:21.386
TRAVIS: They're in the city?

01:46:21.386 --> 01:46:22.555
MATT: "Most of them are, yeah."

01:46:22.555 --> 01:46:24.586
SAM: Were there six of them?

01:46:24.586 --> 01:46:27.392
LAURA: 17.

01:46:27.392 --> 01:46:30.430
MATT: 17, okay. You don't see the guard nearby.

01:46:30.430 --> 01:46:31.759
TRAVIS: We need that guard.

01:46:31.759 --> 01:46:34.828
MARISHA: What are we going to do right now?

01:46:34.828 --> 01:46:36.513
TRAVIS: We're going to ask him some questions.

01:46:36.513 --> 01:46:41.110
MARISHA: This is a coup on a grander scale than
Whitestone that we're talking about.

01:46:41.110 --> 01:46:42.877
TRAVIS: I just want the guard.

01:46:42.877 --> 01:46:44.801
SAM: Where's the guard? Can we see him?

01:46:44.801 --> 01:46:47.821
MATT: You guys want to try and find him?

01:46:47.821 --> 01:46:50.008
LAURA: Well, I saw him on the other side of the
thingie.

01:46:50.008 --> 01:46:56.839
MATT: Okay. You guys begin making your way towards
the direction that Vex saw the guard. You start

01:46:56.839 --> 01:47:01.479
pushing through the crop, making your way to the
edge, and at the point where these high crops end,

01:47:01.479 --> 01:47:06.809
it opens up into what looks like a heavy
root-based field. Potatoes, carrots, things that

01:47:06.809 --> 01:47:16.412
are beneath the ground. You guys see across the
way the two other farmers that were out there, the

01:47:16.412 --> 01:47:22.755
one that you saw being loosely beaten, they're
both filling satchels and emptying them into two

01:47:22.755 --> 01:47:33.054
larger carts that are put up to horses, one of
them a larger pony. You see what appears to be

01:47:33.054 --> 01:47:42.439
another hulking humanoid, taller than an average
person, skin slightly gray, a smattering of

01:47:42.439 --> 01:47:48.493
tattoos across the body. You recognize--

01:47:48.493 --> 01:47:54.263
LIAM: And best we can tell, he's the only guard?
The only one?

01:47:54.263 --> 01:47:56.033
TRAVIS: No, there's two. There's two.

01:47:56.033 --> 01:47:57.284
LAURA: I have an idea!

01:47:57.284 --> 01:47:59.483
SAM: Wait, he was about to tell us who it is.

01:47:59.483 --> 01:48:04.137
MATT: From what you can see, you actually
recognize this individual.

01:48:04.137 --> 01:48:06.768
TRAVIS: Fucking nipple tassels!

01:48:06.768 --> 01:48:16.703
MATT: This is an individual that you knew quite a
ways ago, a young goliath who was still about a

01:48:16.703 --> 01:48:25.876
half a foot shorter than you when you knew him. He
was named Horace, because he hated it, and Kevdak

01:48:25.876 --> 01:48:32.391
gave him this name and you actually, at some point
in the past, recall even giving Horace a good

01:48:32.391 --> 01:48:38.635
beating. A little of the smaller of the goliaths
you've encountered. This is years later. This punk

01:48:38.635 --> 01:48:47.125
kid, and he was kind of a punk, has grown up now,
and is still smaller than you by a size, but still

01:48:47.125 --> 01:48:51.961
seems to be every bit of an agitating little bitch
you remember, from the way that he's treating

01:48:51.961 --> 01:48:53.252
these people.

01:48:53.252 --> 01:48:54.620
TRAVIS: Is he holding anything?

01:48:54.620 --> 01:48:59.227
MATT: Not in his hand at the moment, no, but he
does have across the back what looks to be some

01:48:59.227 --> 01:49:01.136
sort of large blade sheathed.

01:49:01.136 --> 01:49:03.812
LAURA: Can I give my idea?

01:49:03.812 --> 01:49:04.922
TRAVIS: Yep.

01:49:04.922 --> 01:49:11.427
LAURA: What if we ask Reginald to call for help,
like he needs this fuck's help, and then he comes

01:49:11.427 --> 01:49:13.714
over, and then we spring a trap on him.

01:49:13.714 --> 01:49:15.407
MARISHA: That's not a bad idea.

01:49:15.407 --> 01:49:21.001
LAURA: I can use Hide in Plain Sight on us, and
hide us, and make us look like we're part of the crops.

01:49:21.049 --> 01:49:22.125
TRAVIS: I love it.

01:49:22.125 --> 01:49:23.358
LAURA: To set an ambush.

01:49:23.358 --> 01:49:24.313
TRAVIS: I love it.

01:49:24.313 --> 01:49:28.525
LIAM: And the goal is to question this guy or to
take him out? To question, yeah?

01:49:28.525 --> 01:49:33.577
TRAVIS: We're going to ask him questions, and if
he makes a peep-- Hold on, before we do that. Can

01:49:33.577 --> 01:49:35.339
you see the other guard that was out here?

01:49:35.339 --> 01:49:40.534
MATT: Glancing about, because it is a pretty open
area, you can see the secondary guard is walking

01:49:40.534 --> 01:49:44.040
away, looking to check one of the other
homesteads. There is a farmhouse.

01:49:44.040 --> 01:49:46.645
TRAVIS: It's like Kansas, right, it's flat?

01:49:46.645 --> 01:49:51.052
MATT: Yep, it's flat farmland on the outside of
Westruun. As soon as you break the south side of

01:49:51.052 --> 01:49:53.241
the Bramblewood, it's just plain.

01:49:53.241 --> 01:49:57.706
TRAVIS: What distance would you put him at? How
far away would you put him? 100 yards?

01:49:57.706 --> 01:49:59.179
LAURA: The other guard?

01:49:59.179 --> 01:50:01.398
MATT: I'd say the other guard's probably a good
400 feet.

01:50:01.398 --> 01:50:02.672
TRAVIS: Do it.

01:50:02.672 --> 01:50:04.013
LAURA: Yeah?

01:50:04.013 --> 01:50:04.925
TRAVIS: Do it.

01:50:04.925 --> 01:50:07.298
LAURA: Can I take a minute to camouflage us and
then tell Reginald to call him over?

01:50:07.298 --> 01:50:08.084
MATT: Yeah.

01:50:08.084 --> 01:50:11.766
TRAVIS: When he comes over, I grab him. Nobody do
anything that's loud.

01:50:11.766 --> 01:50:13.539
LAURA: Got it.

01:50:13.539 --> 01:50:21.920
MATT: Okay. So, as you all take a moment, stepping
into parts of the stalks of the edge of this land,

01:50:21.920 --> 01:50:28.158
Vex, you go ahead and start taking up leaves,
patches of dirt, mud from freshly watered ground,

01:50:28.158 --> 01:50:33.176
and you start smattering the rest of the group
with it. You guys are going full Arnold from

01:50:33.176 --> 01:50:36.205
Predator. You begin to blend into the vicinity.

01:50:36.205 --> 01:50:42.517
MARISHA: Question. Could I work with Percy?

01:50:42.517 --> 01:50:44.219
TALIESIN: Yes?

01:50:44.219 --> 01:50:55.050
MARISHA: I have Entangle learned today. Could we
fashion a quick Entangle trap, where when the guy

01:50:55.050 --> 01:50:59.130
steps into it he'll be entangled? Or I could maybe
just be prepared for it?

01:50:59.130 --> 01:51:00.618
MATT: You can be prepared for it when it happens.

01:51:00.618 --> 01:51:01.656
MARISHA: I'll be prepared for it.

01:51:01.656 --> 01:51:05.847
TALIESIN: I'm going to draw her a little sketch of
something that would spring, that you can make out

01:51:05.847 --> 01:51:06.822
of wood.

01:51:06.822 --> 01:51:11.880
MATT: The spell expends when cast, so it's more of
waiting to release it. To make it as part of a set

01:51:11.880 --> 01:51:15.426
trap, that would be a consumable trap you would
have to construct.

01:51:15.426 --> 01:51:18.747
MARISHA: All right. I'll just be prepped with it.

01:51:18.747 --> 01:51:22.077
MATT: Okay. So you guys all have hidden.

01:51:22.077 --> 01:51:24.161
LAURA: Reginald.

01:51:24.161 --> 01:51:27.823
MATT: He's behind you guys, watching all of this
happen. "Yes?"

01:51:27.823 --> 01:51:32.979
LAURA: Act like you're still picking and act like
you hurt your ankle, and call for help from that

01:51:32.979 --> 01:51:35.381
guard over there. We'll protect you.

01:51:35.381 --> 01:51:36.596
MATT: "Promise?"

01:51:36.596 --> 01:51:38.522
TRAVIS: Yeah, I promise.

01:51:38.522 --> 01:51:42.923
MARISHA: And try and maybe keep a bit of a
distance, because I'm going to be doing a trap

01:51:42.923 --> 01:51:46.057
here. It's going to be 20 feet. You don't want to
be in it.

01:51:46.057 --> 01:51:47.490
LAURA: Just step back and call for help.

01:51:47.490 --> 01:51:48.903
MARISHA: Just step back, all right?

01:51:48.903 --> 01:51:55.346
MATT: So you guys are all working on the very edge
of where these crop fields begin. Reginald pushes

01:51:55.346 --> 01:52:05.588
through a little bit, and goes, "Ow! Ow! Ow!" You
hear in the distance a voice go, "Hey you! What's

01:52:05.588 --> 01:52:13.405
"your problem?" He goes, "My ankle!" And he starts
hobbling into the crop. "You shut your trap! It's

01:52:13.405 --> 01:52:18.774
"your fucking ankle! What's that stupid-- Oh, you--"
(grunts) He starts lumbering up. "I'm going to

01:52:18.774 --> 01:52:23.725
"teach you about letting a peep out of that stupid
maw of yours! I'm going to beat that face so hard

01:52:23.725 --> 01:52:26.791
"it can't make a noise ever again! Stupid git!"

01:52:26.791 --> 01:52:27.918
TALIESIN: And now.

01:52:27.918 --> 01:52:29.593
MARISHA: (whoosh)

01:52:29.593 --> 01:52:32.548
LAURA: The minute he's in the high crops so he's
out of visual from the other guard.

01:52:32.548 --> 01:52:35.369
MATT: Okay. So as soon as he steps into the high
crop area.

01:52:35.369 --> 01:52:37.800
MARISHA: I'm waiting for Percy's cue.

01:52:37.800 --> 01:52:39.229
TALIESIN: Now!

01:52:39.229 --> 01:52:42.596
MATT: All right. So what are the specifics of the
Entanglement spell?

01:52:42.596 --> 01:52:44.659
MARISHA: 20 feet.

01:52:44.659 --> 01:52:52.293
SAM: It always works and it catches whoever you
want!

01:52:52.293 --> 01:52:53.836
MARISHA: It always works...

01:52:53.836 --> 01:53:00.809
MATT: All of a sudden all of the crops, all of the
large stalks and vines start (whoosh) wrapping

01:53:00.809 --> 01:53:02.139
around his body.

01:53:02.139 --> 01:53:03.236
LAURA: Shit, mother bitch!

01:53:03.236 --> 01:53:04.292
SAM: What's wrong?

01:53:04.292 --> 01:53:05.518
LAURA: That's a bit obvious.

01:53:05.518 --> 01:53:06.439
MARISHA: Is it obvious?

01:53:06.439 --> 01:53:09.784
MATT: It's once he's inside the area, so it's not
like the wall on the outside.

01:53:09.784 --> 01:53:13.212
LAURA: Okay. I was picturing all the plants
suddenly losing their shit.

01:53:13.212 --> 01:53:15.017
MATT: No, just the ones in the immediate
vicinity.

01:53:15.017 --> 01:53:16.850
SAM: Like a used car lot?

01:53:16.850 --> 01:53:19.789
MATT: Okay, so he's going to attempt to make a
strength saving throw.

01:53:19.789 --> 01:53:23.339
LIAM: I'm going to squat at the edge of the high
crops and keep an eye on the other guard who was

01:53:23.339 --> 01:53:25.492
walking off just to make sure he's oblivious.

01:53:25.492 --> 01:53:31.286
MATT: Make a perception check, if you could, Vax.
Surprised so he has disadvantage on the saving

01:53:31.286 --> 01:53:32.959
throw. What's the DC?

01:53:32.959 --> 01:53:34.796
MARISHA: Me? 19.

01:53:34.796 --> 01:53:38.361
MATT: 19? That's a failure. All right, and what?

01:53:38.361 --> 01:53:39.550
LIAM: 28.

01:53:39.550 --> 01:53:43.136
MATT: 28! Yeah, Vax, keeping an eye, the guard
doesn't seem to have kept notice and continues

01:53:43.136 --> 01:53:49.394
walking off towards the distant farmhouse. The
plants all wrap around his body and he:

01:53:49.394 --> 01:53:50.832
"What's this? Stupid-- "

01:53:50.832 --> 01:53:55.871
TRAVIS: I run over and I tackle him, knock him to
the ground, put my hand over his mouth, punch him

01:53:55.871 --> 01:54:04.259
in the forehead. Punch him again. Punch him a
third time. And I barely lift my hand.

01:54:04.259 --> 01:54:06.789
MATT: "You motherfucker-- "

01:54:06.789 --> 01:54:08.368
TRAVIS: Punch him again.

01:54:08.368 --> 01:54:11.990
MATT: At this point, now he's got blood pouring
out of the corner of the eye. One eye has gone a

01:54:11.990 --> 01:54:16.323
little red from burst vessels. You can see it
starting to swell up already. Blood's now pouring

01:54:16.323 --> 01:54:20.258
out the side of the nose where you've hit it, and
he's still fighting even though the plants have

01:54:20.258 --> 01:54:24.349
kept him entangled. As soon as the calm comes to
him (heavy breathing).

01:54:24.349 --> 01:54:26.958
TRAVIS: (sing-song) Horace.

01:54:26.958 --> 01:54:34.851
MATT: The eyes go wide and all the tension in the
body loosens. "Fucking hell."

01:54:34.851 --> 01:54:36.323
TRAVIS: (muffled) Fucking hell.

01:54:36.323 --> 01:54:39.302
MATT: You're still holding his face? (muffled)
"Fucking hell."

01:54:39.302 --> 01:54:48.275
TRAVIS: I'm going to move my hand. If you make a
sound, wash, rinse, repeat, yeah? Nod.

01:54:48.275 --> 01:54:50.365
Shut the fuck up.

01:54:50.365 --> 01:54:56.899
MATT: He spits a couple teeth out the side of his
mouth.

01:54:56.899 --> 01:54:59.887
TRAVIS: You're looking big.

01:54:59.887 --> 01:55:07.911
MATT: "You're supposed to be dead. You're supposed
to be fucking dead. I watched you beaten to death.

01:55:07.911 --> 01:55:10.143
"Why the fuck are you still alive?"

01:55:10.143 --> 01:55:16.737
TRAVIS: Yeah, right. Funny thing about me. So
look, who else is out in this field with you right now?

01:55:16.737 --> 01:55:29.976
MATT: "No one. It's me and Cole, but Cole's
heading back to the city. We have other ones

01:55:29.976 --> 01:55:33.934
"passed out around, but most of them stay in town,
especially during the day. That's where the

01:55:33.934 --> 01:55:36.367
"festivities are."

01:55:36.417 --> 01:55:38.078
LAURA: Festivities?

01:55:38.078 --> 01:55:43.201
MATT: "Do you want back in? You're alive, man. Now's
the time. It's a good time for the herd."

01:55:43.201 --> 01:55:48.914
TRAVIS: Yeah, no I want back in, for sure. That's
what I've come here for: to come back in. But

01:55:48.914 --> 01:55:56.221
here's the thing. It's a bit of a surprise, right?
Other people haven't seen me. You like a good

01:55:56.221 --> 01:55:57.841
surprise, right, Horace?

01:55:57.841 --> 01:56:00.736
MATT: "Yeah?"

01:56:00.736 --> 01:56:06.371
TRAVIS: Yeah. I thought you might. Here's my
question: have you seen my cousin Zanror?

01:56:06.371 --> 01:56:07.994
Is he in the city?

01:56:07.994 --> 01:56:09.460
MATT: "Probably, aye."

01:56:09.460 --> 01:56:14.483
TRAVIS: Right. And what about Kevdak?

01:56:14.483 --> 01:56:21.154
MATT: "Kevdak stays in the city, as well. Up at
the old Margrave's place, actually. Turned it into

01:56:21.154 --> 01:56:24.608
"his palace. Want me to take you?"

01:56:24.608 --> 01:56:30.563
TALIESIN: Before we go any further, what do I roll
if I want to find out if Horace really does like

01:56:30.563 --> 01:56:33.901
surprises? I'm not kidding.

01:56:33.901 --> 01:56:37.061
MATT: Make an insight check. All of you guys are
still hidden, by the way, unless you want

01:56:37.061 --> 01:56:38.291
to do something.

01:56:38.291 --> 01:56:39.364
TALIESIN: No, I'm just watching.

01:56:39.364 --> 01:56:41.870
LAURA: And we gained another plus ten, so now we
have plus 20 to all of our stealth, by the way,

01:56:41.870 --> 01:56:43.283
from that Hide in Plain Sight.

01:56:43.283 --> 01:56:44.747
SAM: Wait, what?

01:56:44.747 --> 01:56:48.718
LAURA: We have Pass Without a Trace, which adds
plus ten, Hide in Plain Sight adds plus ten.

01:56:48.718 --> 01:56:50.844
That's what I camouflaged us fucking for.

01:56:50.844 --> 01:56:52.788
SAM: How do you have all these things?

01:56:52.788 --> 01:56:56.967
MATT: All of you guys make another stealth check
with plus 20.

01:56:56.967 --> 01:57:04.308
MARISHA: Natural 20, so 40. Actually, I have a
stealth of seven.

01:57:04.308 --> 01:57:05.599
LAURA: 46.

01:57:05.599 --> 01:57:06.937
TALIESIN: 43.

01:57:06.937 --> 01:57:08.550
MARISHA: 47.

01:57:08.550 --> 01:57:12.205
MATT: You guys have never been seen.
Retroactively, no one's ever seen you in your

01:57:12.205 --> 01:57:13.473
entire lives.

01:57:13.473 --> 01:57:16.048
TALIESIN: I could fire my gun, at this point, and
they'd be like, oh, rain's coming.

01:57:16.048 --> 01:57:19.603
MATT: If it was Bad News, it would still probably
break stealth.

01:57:19.603 --> 01:57:20.939
TALIESIN: Well, if it was Bad News, yeah.

01:57:20.939 --> 01:57:30.501
MATT: Okay, unless you rolled a one. Yeah, no.
(laughs) Horace hasn't seen anyone.

01:57:30.501 --> 01:57:34.875
"I could take you in."

01:57:34.875 --> 01:57:39.406
TRAVIS: Right, listen. I was going to pounce on
this poor farmer over here, but I saw you were

01:57:39.406 --> 01:57:42.818
obviously keeping your eye on him. Why are you
doing that?

01:57:42.818 --> 01:57:45.658
MATT: "Which one are you talking about? Reggie?"

01:57:45.658 --> 01:57:47.856
TRAVIS: Yeah. Old Broken Foot over here.

01:57:47.856 --> 01:57:55.113
MATT: (laughs) "He's a little bitch, that one is.
No, but you know what? I caught him sniffing

01:57:55.113 --> 01:57:57.516
"around. I think he's keeping some gold hidden."

01:57:57.516 --> 01:58:00.399
TRAVIS: Really? Gold? This poor farmer?

01:58:00.399 --> 01:58:01.800
MATT: "Twisted his arm a couple of times."

01:58:01.800 --> 01:58:02.998
TRAVIS: Have you?

01:58:02.998 --> 01:58:06.504
MATT: "We could do this for old times' sake. Each
take an arm, pull until he tells us."

01:58:06.504 --> 01:58:08.292
TRAVIS: Oh, like wishbone?

01:58:08.292 --> 01:58:09.623
MATT: "Yeah."

01:58:09.623 --> 01:58:15.748
TRAVIS: Yeah, that does sound like a good idea.
Here's my thing. Why are you guys in this city?

01:58:15.748 --> 01:58:20.796
It's not really our thing to be in civilized
places.

01:58:20.796 --> 01:58:27.915
MATT: "Here's the thing. Let me get loose here for
a minute. I'm feeling a bit uncomfortable."

01:58:27.915 --> 01:58:30.305
TRAVIS: No, I don't think I will, Horace.

01:58:30.305 --> 01:58:41.803
MATT: "Okay. We were heading up north. We took out
a small caravan just south of the road cuts, near

01:58:41.803 --> 01:58:46.807
"the Silvercut Way, and all of a sudden out of the
sky, we saw these streaking dragons come through.

01:58:46.807 --> 01:58:53.523
"Largest I've ever seen. Dangerous as the day's
long. So we fled. We watched them come here and

01:58:53.523 --> 01:59:00.773
"tear into this city. Rend it, destroy it, smoke
and flames and ice and all sorts of craziness. And

01:59:00.773 --> 01:59:07.863
"they kept going. We figured, dragons come, didn't
take the spoils, there's plenty of spoils for us.

01:59:07.863 --> 01:59:13.526
"More than we could ever dream of. Most of it's
pretty well-guarded, but there couldn't be much

01:59:13.526 --> 01:59:19.416
"left over there. So we gathered up who we had, and
mind you, the herd's swelled a bit since you left,

01:59:19.416 --> 01:59:30.278
"my friend. We conquered another wandering tribe
last year. Zanror took the head of their leader

01:59:30.278 --> 01:59:33.807
"and commanded them to join. We're about a hundred
strong these days."

01:59:33.807 --> 01:59:35.362
TRAVIS: Jesus.

01:59:35.362 --> 01:59:36.800
MARISHA: Fuck.

01:59:36.800 --> 01:59:44.385
MATT: "Pecking order. Still us goliaths at the
top. We got all sorts of other piddly men."

01:59:44.385 --> 01:59:45.533
TRAVIS: Really?

01:59:45.533 --> 01:59:52.683
MATT: "Half-men, half-orcs. A few brutalized elves
here and there. They make cooking easy. Anyway, we

01:59:52.683 --> 01:59:59.404
"took that moment and we rushed into the town. Took
it before the day was over. Killed all who didn't

01:59:59.404 --> 02:00:09.897
"bow before Kevdak himself. Days of revelry ensued,
my friend. Oh, you missed out. Wine, women, gold.

02:00:09.897 --> 02:00:21.520
"We took what we wanted until one of them dragons
came back. Black one. Scary. Killed a lot of us.

02:00:21.520 --> 02:00:27.820
"We weren't so much a hundred strong then, but by
the end of that we had 50 or 60 to our name before

02:00:27.820 --> 02:00:38.232
"the anger finally stopped. Kevdak bent a knee and
made an offering to this dragon."

02:00:38.232 --> 02:00:39.750
TRAVIS: Kevdak did?

02:00:39.750 --> 02:00:52.033
MATT: "I know. But trust me, you see a beast this
size... it was survival through a mutual discussion, if you

02:00:52.033 --> 02:01:00.977
"will. Promised our might to its worship, gathered
our spoils, deliver it every now and then. We got

02:01:00.977 --> 02:01:08.826
"to have the leftovers. We rule the city in its
stead. Not a bad deal. Doesn't watch. We leave it

02:01:08.826 --> 02:01:15.706
"what we find-- most of it, at least, we keep a
little on the side-- and we live like kings here.

02:01:15.706 --> 02:01:19.002
"Westruun is now property of the herd."

02:01:19.002 --> 02:01:25.562
TRAVIS: Well, it sounds really good.

02:01:25.562 --> 02:01:31.624
MATT: "You've missed out, and there's quite a few
openings now, since we've lost a few of the less

02:01:31.624 --> 02:01:35.931
"than strong folk. You look strapping. I'm sure
Kevdak would be more than happy to have you back."

02:01:35.931 --> 02:01:38.282
TRAVIS: I do. I've actually brought a few gifts.

02:01:38.282 --> 02:01:40.721
LAURA: (whispering) I notch an arrow.

02:01:40.721 --> 02:01:43.287
TRAVIS: I unsheathe Craven Edge.

02:01:43.287 --> 02:01:46.257
MATT: "That's a good blade."

02:01:46.257 --> 02:01:51.212
TRAVIS: Isn't it. And I ask out loud, are you
hungry?

02:01:51.212 --> 02:02:02.270
MATT: "It's been probably half a day since
breakfast. Aye. Why?" His expression begins to

02:02:02.270 --> 02:02:06.245
shift as realization begins to dawn on his face.

02:02:06.245 --> 02:02:10.174
TRAVIS: I pull it back. I stick the point in
between his ribcage, and I drive it up through him.

02:02:10.174 --> 02:02:12.251
(shocked noises)

02:02:12.251 --> 02:02:18.319
MATT: Before he can say a word-- he tries to speak
through the pain, but it's met with the gurgle as

02:02:18.319 --> 02:02:22.745
various bodily fluids fill the inside of his lungs
and throat.

02:02:22.745 --> 02:02:24.622
TRAVIS: Oh, more?

02:02:24.622 --> 02:02:30.265
MATT: The blade, now, you can see (choking noise)
peeks through the back of the mouth as his eyes go

02:02:30.265 --> 02:02:35.917
ever so dull, the rest of the blood flow pouring
out the sides of his mouth.

02:02:35.917 --> 02:02:39.168
TRAVIS: Pity that, acid reflux.

02:02:39.168 --> 02:02:44.980
LAURA: Grog! Oh shit. Good job, there.

02:02:44.980 --> 02:02:46.371
MARISHA: Vex?

02:02:46.371 --> 02:02:51.783
MATT: As this is happening, the blood that has
filled the mouth begins to seep back into the

02:02:51.783 --> 02:02:58.221
mouth. The trails are still there, but what was
once filled to the brim has been slowly recessed,

02:02:58.221 --> 02:03:07.935
swallowed. Not by the unmoving body of Horace, but
the dark blade itself now drawing from the inside.

02:03:07.935 --> 02:03:11.771
LAURA: What the fuck is that sword, Grog?

02:03:11.771 --> 02:03:13.108
TRAVIS: What?

02:03:13.108 --> 02:03:14.848
LAURA: What is your sword doing?

02:03:14.848 --> 02:03:22.054
TRAVIS: Nothing. It takes in the strength of who
it slays.

02:03:22.054 --> 02:03:24.191
LAURA: It takes in the blood?

02:03:24.191 --> 02:03:26.940
TRAVIS: Did it do that?

02:03:26.940 --> 02:03:28.374
LAURA: Grog.

02:03:28.374 --> 02:03:29.654
TRAVIS: What?

02:03:29.654 --> 02:03:34.340
SAM: You killed him. Was he related to you in some
way?

02:03:34.340 --> 02:03:40.283
TRAVIS: I don't know. I remember him. He was
always a little shit.

02:03:40.283 --> 02:03:45.047
MARISHA: Grog, do you remember killing him five
seconds ago?

02:03:45.047 --> 02:03:46.408
TRAVIS: Who?

02:03:46.408 --> 02:03:49.133
MARISHA: Oh no. You guys.

02:03:49.133 --> 02:03:50.656
LAURA: The little dude. Your little friend?

02:03:50.656 --> 02:03:52.047
TRAVIS: Horace?

02:03:52.047 --> 02:03:54.260
LAURA: You killed him. On purpose?

02:03:54.260 --> 02:03:55.181
TRAVIS: Sure.

02:03:55.181 --> 02:03:56.202
LAURA: You wanted to?

02:03:56.202 --> 02:03:57.822
TRAVIS: Yeah, he was going to go tell about us.

02:03:57.822 --> 02:03:59.653
MARISHA: You were conscious of that?

02:03:59.653 --> 02:04:00.970
TRAVIS: What?

02:04:00.970 --> 02:04:02.533
MARISHA: Is it me?

02:04:02.533 --> 02:04:04.816
SAM: You're using too-big words.

02:04:04.816 --> 02:04:14.769
TRAVIS: So listen, right? Either we stay and do
some recon, or we take out the other guy that's

02:04:14.769 --> 02:04:23.872
walking back to the city. Really shouldn't be a
problem. But if they're all in there, 50 strong, I

02:04:23.872 --> 02:04:30.073
don't think we're quite ready for that. The sneaky
fucks in our group could go take a look, if you're

02:04:30.073 --> 02:04:31.387
feeling randy.

02:04:31.387 --> 02:04:34.530
SAM: What would be our mission?

02:04:34.530 --> 02:04:36.920
TRAVIS: Info only.

02:04:36.920 --> 02:04:42.835
SAM: You killed this one quite easily.

02:04:42.835 --> 02:04:44.300
MARISHA: Very easily.

02:04:44.300 --> 02:04:47.444
TRAVIS: Yeah, but that's because we did it as a
group.

02:04:47.444 --> 02:04:48.580
MARISHA: Did we?

02:04:48.580 --> 02:04:52.678
LAURA: Could we wait until nightfall?

02:04:52.678 --> 02:04:57.404
SAM: I'm going to check out his body. See if
there's any booty on his body.

02:04:57.404 --> 02:05:03.267
LAURA: Well, as soon as we move, we won't be
camouflaged in this crop anymore. We'll lose that.

02:05:03.267 --> 02:05:05.021
MARISHA: Yeah, we won't look like crops.

02:05:05.021 --> 02:05:16.526
MATT: As the stalks unwind, leaving his defiled
body and you draw the blade free, Scanlan, you

02:05:16.526 --> 02:05:23.339
find, across the body, there is a simple, slightly
chipped-but-still-functional greatsword that was

02:05:23.339 --> 02:05:32.051
sheathed in the back, wrapped in a haphazard hide
that functioned as a scabbard. Mostly just leather

02:05:32.051 --> 02:05:38.146
pants, a few furs, looks to be a bone necklace and
a bone bracelet around the wrist which looks to be

02:05:38.146 --> 02:05:45.967
teeth, human teeth. About 27 gold pieces in total
change.

02:05:45.967 --> 02:05:48.607
TRAVIS: How far are we from the city here?

02:05:48.607 --> 02:05:51.989
MATT: About a five-minute walk.

02:05:51.989 --> 02:05:53.765
TRAVIS: Five-minute walk. That's not far.

02:05:53.765 --> 02:05:57.256
LAURA: Keyleth, can you use your powers to suck
him into the ground so that nobody sees him?

02:05:57.256 --> 02:06:02.288
TALIESIN: I honestly don't think they're going to
find him, anyway.

02:06:02.288 --> 02:06:07.123
LAURA: I use my abilities and try to camouflage
the body so that nobody finds him.

02:06:07.123 --> 02:06:12.473
MATT: You pull him up into one of the walls of the
plant stalks and set him in there, mounding up

02:06:12.473 --> 02:06:15.494
whatever bits of fallen leaves and dirt you can.
He's pretty well-hidden.

02:06:15.494 --> 02:06:21.997
MARISHA: I use my Druidcraft to grow some flowers
on top of the dirt.

02:06:21.997 --> 02:06:27.103
MATT: Some flowers come up there. Some of the
local leaves from the stalks bend down and help

02:06:27.103 --> 02:06:28.152
cover him up.

02:06:28.152 --> 02:06:30.298
TALIESIN: Leave a couple of his human teeth that
he's collected--

02:06:30.298 --> 02:06:32.715
SAM: I'll leave all his human teeth, I'm not
gonna take that shit.

02:06:32.715 --> 02:06:37.737
MARISHA: Great, so very successful trip. Stopping
down.

02:06:37.737 --> 02:06:39.516
LAURA: Reggie?

02:06:39.516 --> 02:06:41.465
LIAM: His partner's still long-gone.

02:06:41.465 --> 02:06:42.516
TRAVIS: That guard?

02:06:42.516 --> 02:06:43.516
LAURA: The other guard, yeah?

02:06:43.516 --> 02:06:48.018
MATT: The guard's gone. Reggie's still sitting
there, watched this whole thing happen. Looking at

02:06:48.018 --> 02:06:53.847
you and goes, "You did good. You did good."

02:06:53.847 --> 02:06:57.497
TRAVIS: I know I did. Just imagine what we'll do
to the rest of them.

02:06:57.497 --> 02:07:00.817
MATT: "Thank you. Thank you."

02:07:00.817 --> 02:07:04.794
SAM: Are we going to do anything to the rest of
them?

02:07:04.794 --> 02:07:06.091
LAURA: Right now?

02:07:06.091 --> 02:07:07.702
TALIESIN: I think we're going to go take a look.

02:07:07.702 --> 02:07:14.556
TRAVIS: I don't mind you taking a look, but &lt;i&gt;be
careful&lt;/i&gt;.

02:07:14.556 --> 02:07:19.716
TALIESIN: We can also still turn into mist.

02:07:19.716 --> 02:07:21.155
MARISHA: We can.

02:07:21.155 --> 02:07:22.856
LAURA: They can't hurt us when we're mist.

02:07:22.856 --> 02:07:25.327
SAM: We can all mist and go into the city and
check it out.

02:07:25.327 --> 02:07:26.373
LAURA: See what we see.

02:07:26.373 --> 02:07:27.369
TALIESIN: Be fast and stealthy.

02:07:27.369 --> 02:07:29.209
LAURA: Can we stealth while we're misting?

02:07:29.209 --> 02:07:31.860
SAM: It doesn't matter if they see us, they can't
do anything to us.

02:07:31.860 --> 02:07:37.025
MATT: Yeah, it would be being conscious of the
cloud patterns in the sky, moving with the wind in

02:07:37.025 --> 02:07:42.466
a way where you become less noticeable as something
strange. So it's possible.

02:07:42.466 --> 02:07:45.680
LAURA: Let's try that, so we can spy on the city!
Get closer in.

02:07:45.680 --> 02:07:47.307
TRAVIS: It feels kind of cheap.

02:07:47.307 --> 02:07:49.058
LAURA: Why?

02:07:49.058 --> 02:07:53.029
TRAVIS: I don't know.

02:07:53.029 --> 02:07:58.140
LAURA: At least if we go in, Grog, we can see what
we're up against.

02:07:58.140 --> 02:08:06.463
TRAVIS: Yeah, but can't we use our eyes? Just as
they are. Do we have to turn to smoke this time?

02:08:06.463 --> 02:08:11.254
MARISHA: Why would we not?

02:08:11.254 --> 02:08:13.964
TRAVIS: It feels a little cowardly.

02:08:13.964 --> 02:08:16.713
LAURA: It's not cowardly, Grog, it's safe.

02:08:16.713 --> 02:08:18.110
SAM: You can stay behind.

02:08:18.110 --> 02:08:25.697
LIAM: What if Vex and I went as mist, just the two
of us, quickly? Just the two of us.

02:08:25.697 --> 02:08:27.575
TRAVIS: Yeah, that's fine.

02:08:27.575 --> 02:08:32.112
TALIESIN: I may join you two for this as well.

02:08:32.112 --> 02:08:33.300
LAURA: All right.

02:08:33.300 --> 02:08:39.401
MARISHA: And what are the rest of us going to do?
Just wait? Me, Scanlan, and Grog?

02:08:39.401 --> 02:08:43.317
TRAVIS: You can turn into a cloud, and float in
there, and see what you want to see, but I'm not

02:08:43.317 --> 02:08:48.876
turning into mist when my herd is inside that
city. If I go in, I'm going in.

02:08:48.876 --> 02:08:52.199
SAM: As Grog.

02:08:52.199 --> 02:08:53.524
TRAVIS: Yeah.

02:08:53.524 --> 02:08:56.000
MARISHA: So why don't we just not go in right
now?

02:08:56.000 --> 02:09:00.717
SAM: Why don't you all go in, I'll stay back with
Grog.

02:09:00.717 --> 02:09:03.235
TRAVIS: Thank you.

02:09:03.235 --> 02:09:05.160
LAURA: All right.

02:09:05.160 --> 02:09:08.218
TALIESIN: Not crazy-ish.

02:09:08.218 --> 02:09:16.505
MATT: All right, the four of you convert into mist
form, crest up over the edge and start drifting

02:09:16.505 --> 02:09:25.511
your way over the top of Westruun, leaving
Scanlan, Grog, and Reginald amongst the crops.

02:09:25.511 --> 02:09:28.659
TRAVIS: Reginald, you want some ale?

02:09:28.659 --> 02:09:30.979
MATT: "Do you have some?"

02:09:30.979 --> 02:09:36.075
TRAVIS: No, I do, yeah, hold on. Get the cask out,
pour him a cup.

02:09:36.075 --> 02:09:40.219
MATT: He drinks thirstily, both because he seems
genuinely thirsty, and second, it seems like he

02:09:40.219 --> 02:09:41.926
could use a long, hard drink.

02:09:41.926 --> 02:09:44.358
TRAVIS: Pace yourself, son, there's a lot that's
here.

02:09:44.358 --> 02:09:48.113
MATT: "I've been drinking longer than you've been
alive, friend." Just (guzzles).

02:09:48.113 --> 02:09:50.139
TRAVIS: Wow. Another?

02:09:50.139 --> 02:09:51.795
MATT: "Yeah."

02:09:51.795 --> 02:09:53.301
TRAVIS: I'll keep them coming.

02:09:53.301 --> 02:09:57.254
MATT: And, for that, we'll take a quick break,
come back here. See you guys here in a few

02:09:57.254 --> 02:10:01.844
minutes, and we'll continue this story. See you in
a minute!

02:10:01.844 --> 02:26:57.507
[break]

02:26:57.560 --> 02:26:58.863
TALIESIN: Cock goblin.

02:26:58.863 --> 02:27:04.721
MATT: Welcome back! Ha ha, they got it on stream!
Sorry, Liam, we're not as good as you are at it.

02:27:04.721 --> 02:27:08.947
So, guys, quick note before we get back into the
game. Apparently, the shirt link wasn't working

02:27:08.995 --> 02:27:14.005
earlier, it is working now. They got it
functional, so go ahead and hop on now while you

02:27:14.005 --> 02:27:22.861
can. Returning from the break, as Grog and Scanlan
sit, waiting to hear back from the rest of the

02:27:22.861 --> 02:27:28.803
team, traversing over towards Westruun, seeking
information in their mist forms. The two of you

02:27:28.803 --> 02:27:34.520
remain behind. The four of you guys who are in
mist form, where are you going?

02:27:34.520 --> 02:27:43.253
LAURA: Can we stealthily head towards a pocket of
people? Do we see a crowd of people being held?

02:27:43.253 --> 02:27:46.278
MATT: This is your mist form?

02:27:46.278 --> 02:27:47.493
LAURA: This is my mist form.

02:27:47.493 --> 02:27:49.756
MATT: Ocean. I like it. I'd like you guys to make
stealth checks.

02:27:49.756 --> 02:27:51.173
LAURA: Stealth checks!

02:27:51.173 --> 02:27:53.807
MARISHA: Do we still have Pass Without a Trace?

02:27:53.807 --> 02:27:54.888
LAURA: Yes!

02:27:54.888 --> 02:28:00.644
39.

02:28:00.644 --> 02:28:02.533
LIAM: 42.

02:28:02.533 --> 02:28:03.965
TALIESIN: 33.

02:28:03.965 --> 02:28:05.224
MARISHA: 24.

02:28:05.224 --> 02:28:15.253
MATT: You guys make your way across the rest of
the fields. You head over Cole, you can see

02:28:15.253 --> 02:28:21.110
walking his way to the outside of the western side
of the city. You come towards the bottom of the

02:28:21.110 --> 02:28:28.619
gate. You can see the rigid, small fence structure
you noticed when you were far away from the city

02:28:28.619 --> 02:28:36.997
becomes more clearly visible. It is a series of
spears and pikes that are set up as a barrier or a

02:28:36.997 --> 02:28:43.273
barricade to the outside world to Westruun. You do
see adorned atop a number of them a few heads,

02:28:43.273 --> 02:28:46.458
varying sizes, various people, various ages.

02:28:46.458 --> 02:28:49.658
MARISHA: Does this appear to be goliath-built?

02:28:49.658 --> 02:28:53.478
MATT: It's hard to say. It looks built.

02:28:53.478 --> 02:28:56.777
LAURA: And the spikes are facing inward towards
the city, or outward?

02:28:56.777 --> 02:29:02.818
MATT: Outwards. There are breaks in it, but
essentially it's partially a pseudo-defense

02:29:02.818 --> 02:29:06.494
mechanism, it's more as a warning, it's a point of
intimidation.

02:29:06.494 --> 02:29:11.504
MARISHA: So does it look pretty jerry-rigged?

02:29:11.504 --> 02:29:17.432
MATT: Yeah. It's not anything too classically
designed.

02:29:17.432 --> 02:29:20.415
LIAM: No flying buttresses?

02:29:20.415 --> 02:29:22.252
MATT: Not quite, no.

02:29:22.252 --> 02:29:28.244
TALIESIN: Doric columns, oh my &lt;i&gt;god&lt;/i&gt;! Awful!
Tacky!

02:29:28.244 --> 02:29:32.784
MATT: You coast over the outside wall and glance
down within. You can see there are people

02:29:32.784 --> 02:29:42.268
wandering the town, townsfolk that are out in the
streets. Many of them are in pairs or groups, two

02:29:42.268 --> 02:29:49.745
to four people, appear to be traveling from
one place to another. Most of them are accompanied

02:29:49.745 --> 02:29:57.344
by one or two armed individuals. Some of the
people have chains around their neck. You do see a

02:29:57.344 --> 02:30:02.527
number of these buildings are in ruins, patchwork
places. Some are just crushed. Some appear to have

02:30:02.527 --> 02:30:08.990
been melted down, like the wood or stonework
itself has been dissolved into a pile of matter.

02:30:08.990 --> 02:30:17.913
You see places where fires have broken out and
some places have burned into a giant cluster of

02:30:17.913 --> 02:30:26.190
ash and broken wood. A quick memory glance at this
height, you start looking for specific areas that

02:30:26.190 --> 02:30:31.649
you recall from memory. One: you glance over and
see where you first came to meet Pike, where she

02:30:31.649 --> 02:30:39.731
and Wilhand lived. That area is the area of town
that was, apparently, salvaged from the battle. It

02:30:39.731 --> 02:30:45.438
still stands, there appears to be very minimal
impact. As you give yourself enough closeness to

02:30:45.438 --> 02:30:49.899
check in, the red brick homestead of Wilhand does
appear to be standing.

02:30:49.899 --> 02:30:51.742
LAURA: Can we see Wilhand anywhere?

02:30:51.742 --> 02:31:04.701
MATT: At this distance, no. You also note, towards
the shopping district of Westruun, there is the shop

02:31:04.701 --> 02:31:09.160
of Abjurist Noja, one of your first enchanter
friends who protected you during your first

02:31:09.160 --> 02:31:10.295
Winter's Crest.

02:31:10.295 --> 02:31:13.103
MARISHA: Yeah! He cast the protection spell on
us!

02:31:13.103 --> 02:31:14.793
TALIESIN: This is making me feel very old.

02:31:14.793 --> 02:31:20.864
MATT: His structure is still standing as well. A
few buildings around did not fare so well, but his

02:31:20.864 --> 02:31:29.486
shop and a number of other ones adjacent to it
seem to still be standing. You can't really tell

02:31:29.486 --> 02:31:33.500
if they're functional, or how busy they are, or if
anyone's doing anything with them, but that's still

02:31:33.500 --> 02:31:41.513
there. You do notice, though, at numerous parts of
the street, there are just piles and piles of

02:31:41.513 --> 02:31:50.768
burnt wood and ash, like they're large burn piles
that were set at different periods of time and

02:31:50.768 --> 02:31:57.516
have long since burned. Little bits of white,
post-burning plumes that still smolder over the

02:31:57.516 --> 02:32:03.067
past few days. You're not quite sure what these
piles contained at the time they were set ablaze.

02:32:03.067 --> 02:32:12.746
There is still the worship district here. You have
the various temples. Best you can glance, a few of

02:32:12.746 --> 02:32:17.883
them have been partially toppled. There is damage
to some of the buildings. Still too far away to

02:32:17.883 --> 02:32:24.307
make out any specific details beyond that, some of the
structures having taken a hit in previous

02:32:24.307 --> 02:32:26.426
conflicts. You're not sure from which source.

02:32:26.426 --> 02:32:30.222
LAURA: What about the mayor's house where we heard
Horace--?

02:32:30.222 --> 02:32:39.374
MATT: The Margrave's. Towards the southern central portion
of Westruun, south of the main town square where

02:32:39.374 --> 02:32:45.007
the bulk of your first Winter's Crest festival
here in Westruun took place. The Margrave's house

02:32:45.007 --> 02:32:50.943
is at the very southernmost portion of that. That
entire square is lined with row after row of

02:32:50.943 --> 02:32:59.429
sharpened wood sticks and various other weapons,
tridents, broken swords that have been, with

02:32:59.429 --> 02:33:06.205
ropes, strapped together to form a military
barricade. If anything were to attempt to attack

02:33:06.205 --> 02:33:12.680
from the ground, it would be difficult to do so if this
area was filled with prepared soldiers, using

02:33:12.680 --> 02:33:22.098
these as protective guard. The actual Margrave's
home is intact, although at this glance, you can

02:33:22.098 --> 02:33:30.161
see a lot of it has been defiled, elements of the
outside walls are strewn with dark burgundy paint

02:33:30.161 --> 02:33:40.287
slapped over. You can see what looks to be some
sort of strings adorning edges of it, like

02:33:40.287 --> 02:33:49.590
decoration. You see, walking through this area,
what looks to be 12 or 13 or so armed individuals

02:33:49.590 --> 02:33:55.231
of varying heights. Probably a good six or seven
goliaths among them. Others appear to be human,

02:33:55.231 --> 02:34:00.050
half-orc, it's hard to make out the full details
from this distance. They're all on the outskirts

02:34:00.050 --> 02:34:07.073
surrounding what was previously the Margrave's
home. Now the homestead of Kevdak, seemingly.

02:34:07.073 --> 02:34:09.462
LAURA: Can we see Kevdak anywhere?

02:34:09.462 --> 02:34:11.516
MATT: You have no idea what Kevdak looks like.

02:34:11.516 --> 02:34:15.389
LAURA: I look for a bigger goliath than the rest,
or one that looks older and bigger.

02:34:15.389 --> 02:34:18.353
MATT: Make a perception check.

02:34:18.353 --> 02:34:20.991
LAURA: 16.

02:34:20.991 --> 02:34:24.923
MATT: 16. At this distance, it's hard to make out
any specific details. You can barely make out the

02:34:24.923 --> 02:34:28.907
fact that they're goliath. It's only because
you've traveled with Grog so long you can pick out

02:34:28.907 --> 02:34:34.805
the details, the hairless form, the tattoos, the
general tone of skin. They're male and female,

02:34:34.805 --> 02:34:41.260
it's a smattering of all different types of
goliaths. Some of different thickness, some that

02:34:41.260 --> 02:34:46.687
are a little more barrel-chested and wide, some
that are a little shorter. There are other

02:34:46.687 --> 02:34:49.998
similarly dressed individuals that are not
goliaths as well, but they seem to be more of a

02:34:49.998 --> 02:34:54.682
subservient role within the herd than the goliaths
that would be the ruling class within this

02:34:54.682 --> 02:35:02.507
self-contained society. But no one stands out to
you as matching the descriptions of Kevdak that

02:35:02.507 --> 02:35:03.502
Grog gave you.

02:35:03.502 --> 02:35:06.296
TALIESIN: The mansion seems to be where they've
based their operations, though.

02:35:06.296 --> 02:35:07.878
MATT: Seemingly.

02:35:07.878 --> 02:35:11.631
LAURA: We don't see a cluster of prisoners
anywhere out in the open?

02:35:11.631 --> 02:35:13.878
TALIESIN: Where's the prison I was being held in?

02:35:13.878 --> 02:35:18.290
MATT: The prison you were being held in was in the
Umbra Hills. That's far north of Westruun.

02:35:18.290 --> 02:35:20.287
LIAM: That's when we fought the Nightmare.

02:35:20.287 --> 02:35:21.399
LAURA: Yeah!

02:35:21.399 --> 02:35:25.795
TALIESIN: (laughs) (imitates Laura) Yeah!

02:35:25.795 --> 02:35:28.615
LAURA: Do we see a cluster?

02:35:28.615 --> 02:35:31.107
MATT: Do you see a what?

02:35:31.107 --> 02:35:34.405
LAURA: A cluster of prisoners out in the open at
all, or is it just out around--?

02:35:34.405 --> 02:35:37.022
MATT: It's hard to tell because most everyone who
lives here is, in some, way, shape, or form a

02:35:37.022 --> 02:35:46.011
prisoner. You do see at the various gates of the city
as you went through, there's about three, four

02:35:46.011 --> 02:35:53.078
individuals average stationed there. Nobody seems
to be entering or exiting. And the pace of those

02:35:53.078 --> 02:36:00.141
that are not of the herd that you see walking
through the city has a feel of hopelessness, or

02:36:00.141 --> 02:36:06.990
at least their presence outdoors is more of
function. They do what they're told, and if

02:36:06.990 --> 02:36:10.442
they're not, you've already seen what happens to
them.

02:36:10.442 --> 02:36:14.382
MARISHA: Now what?

02:36:14.382 --> 02:36:18.973
TALIESIN: Maybe stealth isn't-- maybe Grog's
right-- we can't talk, can we?

02:36:18.973 --> 02:36:20.388
MARISHA: No, we're fucking clouds.

02:36:20.388 --> 02:36:24.368
LAURA: Can we say go back to the--

02:36:24.368 --> 02:36:26.858
LIAM: Yeah, I'm gesturing to go. Get out.

02:36:26.858 --> 02:36:28.289
LAURA: Yeah, let's go back.

02:36:28.289 --> 02:36:30.878
MATT: Make a stealth check, guys, on the way out.

02:36:30.878 --> 02:36:33.141
SAM: 93.

02:36:33.141 --> 02:36:36.715
TRAVIS: Scanlan and I have been alone.

02:36:36.715 --> 02:36:38.102
LAURA: 39.

02:36:38.102 --> 02:36:39.507
MARISHA: 32.

02:36:39.507 --> 02:36:40.648
LIAM: 44.

02:36:40.648 --> 02:36:41.982
TALIESIN: 26.

02:36:41.982 --> 02:36:48.025
MATT: Okay! You guys make your way westward. Is
there anything you guys wanted to accomplish while

02:36:48.025 --> 02:36:49.361
they were gone?

02:36:49.361 --> 02:36:51.436
SAM: Just massage each other.

02:36:51.436 --> 02:36:58.427
TRAVIS: Right, so I turn to Scanlan. And I say:
you and I are mates, right?

02:36:58.427 --> 02:37:00.590
SAM: Yes, the best of mates.

02:37:00.590 --> 02:37:06.899
TRAVIS: Right. Could I confide something in you?

02:37:06.899 --> 02:37:10.169
SAM: I wasn't aware that you knew what that word
meant.

02:37:10.169 --> 02:37:20.453
TRAVIS: (clears throat) Right. Well, I'm full of
surprises. One of which is-- so, I had this

02:37:20.453 --> 02:37:27.629
horrible dream recently, and in the dream, I was
killing all these people with this amazing sword

02:37:27.629 --> 02:37:28.858
that I have.

02:37:28.858 --> 02:37:30.096
SAM: Yes?

02:37:30.096 --> 02:37:35.820
TRAVIS: But there were a lot of people, and some
of the people that got killed I knew. And I feel

02:37:35.820 --> 02:37:45.372
it has something to do with this sword that I
have. And the secret is: I can hear the sword

02:37:45.372 --> 02:37:47.397
talking to me.

02:37:47.397 --> 02:37:50.773
SAM: Like, talking-talking, or you just--

02:37:50.773 --> 02:37:57.149
TRAVIS: Yeah, look, so I'm telling you because you
and I have such a history, right? And I feel like

02:37:57.149 --> 02:38:01.857
you won't judge me, but, like, I'm afraid the rest
of the group won't quite understand. I don't know

02:38:01.857 --> 02:38:05.941
if I'm crazy or if this sword is talking to me.

02:38:05.941 --> 02:38:08.086
SAM: Do you see a mouth on it or anything?

02:38:08.086 --> 02:38:10.692
TRAVIS: No, I just hear a voice and I was
wondering if maybe I take it out--

02:38:10.692 --> 02:38:11.878
SAM: All the time?

02:38:11.878 --> 02:38:15.450
TRAVIS: No, only when I'm holding it. So, like, I
could take it out now and we could see maybe if

02:38:15.450 --> 02:38:16.655
you hear it.

02:38:16.655 --> 02:38:17.580
SAM: Okay.

02:38:17.580 --> 02:38:19.035
TRAVIS: So I take out Craven Edge.

02:38:19.035 --> 02:38:22.182
MATT: You take out Craven Edge, you hold it out in
front of you.

02:38:22.182 --> 02:38:28.796
TRAVIS: Craven Edge. How did you enjoy your
snack?

02:38:28.796 --> 02:38:35.926
MATT: "It was a good snack. A snack it was. If
there's more where that came from,

02:38:35.926 --> 02:38:38.427
"I would be so thankful."

02:38:38.427 --> 02:38:40.281
TRAVIS: Are you getting that?!

02:38:40.281 --> 02:38:42.966
SAM: No, Grog, I'm not.

02:38:42.966 --> 02:38:47.726
TRAVIS: You're not hearing anything? No, like,
super sexy (low-pitched growl) voice? Nothing?

02:38:47.726 --> 02:38:49.527
SAM: Try one more time.

02:38:49.527 --> 02:38:59.075
TRAVIS: No, it's not worth it. Look, do you want
to hold the sword?

02:38:59.075 --> 02:39:05.124
SAM: Sure! That's a good idea, actually! Can I
hold the sword? How big is it?

02:39:05.124 --> 02:39:12.985
MATT: It's a greatsword. It's almost twice the
length of your whole body and probably weighs

02:39:12.985 --> 02:39:14.879
close to as much as you do.

02:39:14.879 --> 02:39:19.096
SAM: Can you hold the top part and I'll just hold it by
the handle, the hilty-part?

02:39:19.096 --> 02:39:21.915
TRAVIS: I hold the blade, and I hand the hilt
towards Scanlan.

02:39:21.915 --> 02:39:26.028
MATT: As you hand the hilt over towards him, there's
hesitation in the voice, "Only you are worthy of

02:39:26.028 --> 02:39:28.447
"holding me. You will hand me to no one."

02:39:28.447 --> 02:39:38.910
TRAVIS: (grunts) See, now, now, now, Craven, I'm
starting to feel like I'm doubting myself. I'm

02:39:38.910 --> 02:39:42.165
seeing things-- he's talking to me.

02:39:42.165 --> 02:39:43.300
SAM: Okay.

02:39:43.300 --> 02:39:48.984
TRAVIS: I'm going to take it right back, I just
want him to experience your glory.

02:39:48.984 --> 02:39:50.420
MATT: Make a charisma check.

02:39:50.420 --> 02:39:53.442
TRAVIS: Shit. Fuck. That's bad.

02:39:53.442 --> 02:39:54.678
LAURA: No.

02:39:54.678 --> 02:39:59.922
TRAVIS: (gulp) Seven.

02:39:59.922 --> 02:40:18.018
MATT: Seven? Okay. You can't give the sword up. It
means too much, and the voice in your head says,

02:40:18.018 --> 02:40:24.219
"Only those proven worthy to feed me can
carry me. And you, Grog--"

02:40:24.219 --> 02:40:26.456
SAM: Grog, hand me the sword.

02:40:26.456 --> 02:40:33.716
TRAVIS: (pained) No. On second thought, don't
worry about it. It's clearly-- and I take it

02:40:33.716 --> 02:40:43.038
back-- it's not, it's just-- maybe I just need to
see someone or talk to somebody. Clearly, I mean,

02:40:43.038 --> 02:40:45.785
you don't-- it's talking, you don't hear it,
right?

02:40:45.785 --> 02:40:49.672
SAM: I don't hear it, but maybe if you handed it
to me, I could.

02:40:49.672 --> 02:40:53.649
TRAVIS: No, it's really heavy, too. And I sheathe
it.

02:40:53.649 --> 02:40:55.403
SAM: Do I believe him?

02:40:55.403 --> 02:40:58.911
MATT: Make an insight check.

02:40:58.911 --> 02:40:59.954
SAM: Not good.

02:40:59.954 --> 02:41:02.041
MATT: Grog, make a deception check.

02:41:02.041 --> 02:41:05.175
SAM: Not good! Seven!

02:41:05.175 --> 02:41:06.311
TRAVIS: Three!

02:41:06.311 --> 02:41:09.307
(laughing)

02:41:09.307 --> 02:41:16.011
MATT: Grog's not the most able liar, you glean.
You're pretty good at seeing past the deceit of

02:41:16.011 --> 02:41:20.102
others. This definitely falls under the line of
deceit, as adorable as it is to see him try.

02:41:20.102 --> 02:41:28.597
SAM: Grog, you want to give me the sword. And I
will cast Suggestion on him.

02:41:28.597 --> 02:41:31.104
LAURA: Ooh!

02:41:31.104 --> 02:41:33.340
MATT: Is it a wisdom saving throw?

02:41:33.340 --> 02:41:35.858
SAM: I haven't used it in a while, and I don't
have my thing.

02:41:35.858 --> 02:41:39.070
MATT: I'll pull it up real fast, just to make
sure. I'm pretty sure it is.

02:41:39.070 --> 02:41:40.660
TALIESIN: I think it is.

02:41:40.660 --> 02:41:48.358
MATT: Yep, make a wisdom saving throw.

02:41:48.358 --> 02:41:55.086
TRAVIS: Giant modifier on this one. 16. With a
modifier of zero.

02:41:55.086 --> 02:41:56.677
SAM: Well, 18, if I'm not using my thing.

02:41:56.677 --> 02:42:00.710
MATT: Not using the cone, so no, it still fails.
So you feel compelled now to give this sword.

02:42:00.710 --> 02:42:02.665
You're like, no, that's a great idea.

02:42:02.665 --> 02:42:07.381
TRAVIS: You know what? That's a great idea! I feel
like you should hold this sword. And I hold on to the

02:42:07.381 --> 02:42:09.926
blade, but I still hand the hilt to him.

02:42:09.926 --> 02:42:19.657
MATT: As he holds up the sword towards you,
you grasp the handle. As his hand touches it, the

02:42:19.657 --> 02:42:26.473
voice goes, "No! Only you can wield me!" Go ahead
and make a wisdom saving throw again.

02:42:26.473 --> 02:42:29.428
TRAVIS: 18.

02:42:29.428 --> 02:42:31.429
MATT: I'm sorry, that's a charisma saving throw.

02:42:31.429 --> 02:42:32.671
TRAVIS: 19.

02:42:32.671 --> 02:42:34.683
MATT: 19?

02:42:34.683 --> 02:42:35.892
TRAVIS: Yeah, plus one.

02:42:35.892 --> 02:42:42.108
MATT: All right. You feel the influence of the
blade begin into creep into your mind, but the

02:42:42.108 --> 02:42:48.103
bond you have with Scanlan and the time you've
traveled together, you manage to shrug it off.

02:42:48.103 --> 02:42:57.330
Fighting that impulse, you still hand the blade
over. You take the handle. You let go of the

02:42:57.330 --> 02:43:01.392
weapon. You hold it in your hand now. It's a
(heavy thud).

02:43:01.392 --> 02:43:05.225
TALIESIN: You ruin everything good! You take
everything good away from all of us!

02:43:05.225 --> 02:43:07.563
SAM: Well, it's heavy.

02:43:07.563 --> 02:43:09.949
TALIESIN: Throw it into acid, why don't you?!

02:43:09.949 --> 02:43:11.503
TRAVIS: Ask it a question!

02:43:11.503 --> 02:43:13.389
SAM: Oh! I talk to it?

02:43:13.389 --> 02:43:17.041
TRAVIS: Yeah! And it'll talk right back, it's like
that!

02:43:17.041 --> 02:43:29.991
SAM: Oi, Craven Edge. Have you been talking to my
friend Grog?

02:43:29.991 --> 02:43:46.299
MATT: There's a long beat of silence. And then a
barely audible (annoyed sigh).

02:43:46.299 --> 02:43:49.065
LIAM: Sing to it!

02:43:49.065 --> 02:43:59.388
MATT: All of a sudden, you hear this tiny voice
creep up in the back of your head: "If you truly

02:43:59.388 --> 02:44:11.315
"wish to hold me in your grasp, I require you to
prove to me your worthiness."

02:44:11.315 --> 02:44:15.487
TRAVIS: Is it saying something?

02:44:15.487 --> 02:44:17.645
SAM: No.

02:44:17.645 --> 02:44:20.486
TRAVIS: No?! It's not saying anything?!

02:44:20.486 --> 02:44:28.128
SAM: Craven Edge? How do I prove I'm worthy?

02:44:28.128 --> 02:44:29.499
TRAVIS: What?

02:44:29.499 --> 02:44:33.872
(laughing)

02:44:33.872 --> 02:44:40.740
MATT: The blade, all of a sudden, it almost seems
to have a slight shift of its own, like a divining

02:44:40.740 --> 02:44:46.579
rod, and it moves. And the blade shifts away from
the direction of you and Grog and gently shifts

02:44:46.579 --> 02:44:53.157
down the way to an older gentleman who's now
returned to picking a few crops and it points in

02:44:53.157 --> 02:44:58.187
his direction and says, "Prove to me."

02:44:58.187 --> 02:44:59.956
LAURA: Is it Reggie?

02:44:59.956 --> 02:45:01.355
MATT: Pointing to Reginald.

02:45:01.355 --> 02:45:02.545
LAURA: No!

02:45:02.545 --> 02:45:03.758
MARISHA: Not Reggie!

02:45:03.758 --> 02:45:06.312
TRAVIS: Why are you pointing it at Reggie?

02:45:06.312 --> 02:45:17.156
SAM: I don't think I can. I don't think I want to.
So I think I'll try to give the sword back to Grog.

02:45:17.156 --> 02:45:19.225
MATT: Make a charisma check.

02:45:19.225 --> 02:45:24.587
SAM: Is this magic?

02:45:24.587 --> 02:45:35.321
MATT: It's not a spell. Let me double-check, if
you're referring to the gnomish racial capability.

02:45:35.321 --> 02:45:38.422
Let me go ahead and check the rules here, because
this could make a difference here.

02:45:38.422 --> 02:45:42.413
SAM: Well, it's fine.

02:45:42.413 --> 02:45:46.823
MATT: Against magic? I'll say yes, because it's
technically a magical entity.

02:45:46.823 --> 02:45:49.815
SAM: Natural 20.

02:45:49.815 --> 02:45:54.085
TALIESIN: Witchcraft!

02:45:54.085 --> 02:45:58.468
MATT: The sheer force of personality that begins
to exude from this weapon, you sense that it is

02:45:58.468 --> 02:46:05.234
old, it has seen many a hand, and has probably
taken far many more a life. But it's not met a

02:46:05.234 --> 02:46:08.004
gnome like you before, Scanlan Shorthalt.

02:46:08.004 --> 02:46:12.415
TALIESIN: (singing) Never known a gnome like you
before!

02:46:12.415 --> 02:46:14.555
SAM: Take this back, will you?

02:46:14.555 --> 02:46:20.608
TRAVIS: Yeah! I take it back. It talked to you,
then, yeah?

02:46:20.608 --> 02:46:22.788
SAM: Yes, it did.

02:46:22.788 --> 02:46:24.912
TRAVIS: Right, it's creepy as shit.

02:46:24.912 --> 02:46:31.077
SAM: It's very compelling. I don't know if you
should have this, Grog.

02:46:31.077 --> 02:46:35.807
TRAVIS: (confused sputtering) Now, hold on! I just
wanted to make sure that I wasn't fucking, you

02:46:35.807 --> 02:46:41.431
know, batshit crazy, which I'm not! And I'm really
glad that we're sharing in this now. But hey!

02:46:41.431 --> 02:46:51.737
Hey! Don't tell anyone. Promise me.

02:46:51.737 --> 02:46:59.013
SAM: All right. I won't tell anyone. But I might
have to ask some questions about this.

02:46:59.013 --> 02:47:02.868
TRAVIS: No, that's why I brought you in! You're
all smart, right? And I always want to ask

02:47:02.868 --> 02:47:07.149
questions like, what's the first thing it
remembers, what was it doing with Lord Briarwood--?

02:47:07.149 --> 02:47:09.177
SAM: Does it tell you to kill things?

02:47:09.177 --> 02:47:10.352
TRAVIS: No!

02:47:10.352 --> 02:47:12.747
SAM: A lot? I know it does, it just told me to
kill something.

02:47:12.747 --> 02:47:15.120
TRAVIS: You must be a dark wizard.

02:47:15.120 --> 02:47:18.153
SAM: Does it tell you to kill things?

02:47:18.153 --> 02:47:20.216
TRAVIS: No! It just says it's hungry.

02:47:20.216 --> 02:47:27.277
MATT: At which point, you both hear a voice
simultaneously go, "Always hungry."

02:47:27.277 --> 02:47:28.526
SAM: Yeah!

02:47:28.526 --> 02:47:32.996
TRAVIS: You heard it that time! Holy shit! I feel
like Kevin Costner in Field of Dreams and you're

02:47:32.996 --> 02:47:36.541
James Earl Jones! I've got a friend in this now!

02:47:36.541 --> 02:47:39.539
(laughing)

02:47:39.539 --> 02:47:43.634
TALIESIN: Oh boy.

02:47:43.634 --> 02:47:47.662
TRAVIS: Right, so, look, you know.

02:47:47.662 --> 02:47:49.998
SAM: We should not tell the others about this.
This is very strange.

02:47:49.998 --> 02:47:50.937
TRAVIS: Yeah!

02:47:50.937 --> 02:47:51.999
SAM: They might freak out.

02:47:51.999 --> 02:47:52.808
TRAVIS: Right!

02:47:52.808 --> 02:47:56.463
SAM: I'm going to ask about this. When next we see
Pike, I'll ask her about it.

02:47:56.463 --> 02:47:57.591
TRAVIS: Yeah.

02:47:57.591 --> 02:48:03.553
SAM: Find out if it's good or bad or neutral.
Because I don't know anything about this. Right, I

02:48:03.553 --> 02:48:05.296
don't know anything about this?

02:48:05.296 --> 02:48:06.977
MATT: Make an arcana check.

02:48:06.977 --> 02:48:08.848
TRAVIS: It could be good; there's nothing wrong
with being hungry.

02:48:08.848 --> 02:48:10.302
SAM: 12.

02:48:10.302 --> 02:48:12.653
MATT: 12. It seems magical.

02:48:12.653 --> 02:48:17.008
SAM: Yeah, I don't know. Don't know anything about
this.

02:48:17.008 --> 02:48:24.924
MATT: As a bard, you understand that there are
certain artifacts, weapons that either upon their

02:48:24.924 --> 02:48:30.758
creation, upon their development, had the essence
of a creature or soul put into it. Or, conversely,

02:48:30.758 --> 02:48:39.903
the weapon came into being as its own personality.
You're not sure of the nature of this, and you're

02:48:39.903 --> 02:48:44.779
unable to ascertain which side of the spectrum it
lies on as far as morality goes.

02:48:44.779 --> 02:48:50.695
SAM: I'll do some investigating. In the meantime,
try not to kill anyone in our party.

02:48:50.695 --> 02:48:53.697
If it tells you to.

02:48:53.697 --> 02:48:55.273
TRAVIS: I would never!

02:48:55.273 --> 02:48:56.200
SAM: Well.

02:48:56.200 --> 02:48:57.155
TRAVIS: Never!

02:48:57.155 --> 02:48:58.034
SAM: Okay.

02:48:58.034 --> 02:48:59.894
TRAVIS: No, yeah there's never even, like--

02:48:59.894 --> 02:49:01.189
SAM: Let's just keep this between us.

02:49:01.189 --> 02:49:02.560
TRAVIS: Yeah, totes.

02:49:02.560 --> 02:49:05.641
SAM: Just like that time in Emon when we--

02:49:05.641 --> 02:49:06.593
TRAVIS: Yep!

02:49:06.593 --> 02:49:07.386
SAM: --double-teamed--

02:49:07.386 --> 02:49:10.115
TRAVIS: The Eiffel Tower!

02:49:10.115 --> 02:49:11.001
SAM: Yep!

02:49:11.001 --> 02:49:12.074
TRAVIS: Yep! All right!

02:49:12.074 --> 02:49:13.388
SAM: It was a--

02:49:13.388 --> 02:49:14.951
TALIESIN: Oh, that went up my nose!

02:49:14.951 --> 02:49:17.695
LAURA: Ugh!

02:49:17.695 --> 02:49:21.930
MATT: At which point, a few clusters of wind come
landing out of the sky.

02:49:21.930 --> 02:49:23.177
MARISHA: What? Green lights?

02:49:23.177 --> 02:49:24.084
LAURA: That's us.

02:49:24.084 --> 02:49:25.514
MATT: You guys, you're the mist!

02:49:25.514 --> 02:49:27.724
MARISHA: (panicked yelling) Oh! It's just me!

02:49:27.724 --> 02:49:30.586
TALIESIN: You're literally just scared of your
hands.

02:49:30.586 --> 02:49:32.565
MARISHA: (relieved) Oh!

02:49:32.565 --> 02:49:34.929
TRAVIS: What did--

02:49:34.929 --> 02:49:36.566
SAM: Nothing happened here. How was your trip?

02:49:36.566 --> 02:49:37.756
TRAVIS: Yeah, boring here.

02:49:37.756 --> 02:49:38.593
LAURA: Totally boring?

02:49:38.593 --> 02:49:39.777
TRAVIS: Yep. No action.

02:49:39.777 --> 02:49:44.212
LAURA: You know, not a lot to see there. There's a
lot of goliaths and a lot of other bad guys

02:49:44.212 --> 02:49:47.660
walking around, oppressing very nice-looking
people.

02:49:47.660 --> 02:49:48.875
TRAVIS: A lot of goliaths?

02:49:48.875 --> 02:49:52.573
MARISHA: They've made really poky fences
everywhere.

02:49:52.573 --> 02:49:53.887
TRAVIS: That's what I'd do.

02:49:53.887 --> 02:50:03.257
LAURA: It looks like if we barged in, straight in,
they'd probably have very good fortifications.

02:50:03.257 --> 02:50:04.470
TRAVIS: Right.

02:50:04.470 --> 02:50:06.694
MARISHA: I also think they're trying to be scary.

02:50:06.694 --> 02:50:08.917
TRAVIS: Trying to be scary?

02:50:08.917 --> 02:50:14.948
MARISHA: Not that you're not scary all the time,
Grog. I just think they're like, ooh.

02:50:14.948 --> 02:50:16.634
LAURA: They really want to look scary.

02:50:16.634 --> 02:50:18.760
MARISHA: They really want to look tough, yeah.

02:50:18.760 --> 02:50:25.237
LAURA: So, here's the thing. Do we barge in,
totally risk our lives? Or try to find a way

02:50:25.237 --> 02:50:28.689
around this situation?

02:50:28.689 --> 02:50:31.474
SAM: There's a central stronghold of some sort?

02:50:31.474 --> 02:50:32.472
TALIESIN: Yes.

02:50:32.472 --> 02:50:33.586
SAM: Is it a fortress?

02:50:33.586 --> 02:50:35.407
LAURA: It's where the mayor lived before.

02:50:35.407 --> 02:50:36.481
SAM: It's a house?

02:50:36.481 --> 02:50:37.955
LAURA: Yeah, it's like a big house.

02:50:37.955 --> 02:50:39.577
TALIESIN and MARISHA: It's a nice house.

02:50:39.577 --> 02:50:45.478
SAM: And if we were to make our way into it,
somehow, what would our mission be?

02:50:45.478 --> 02:50:52.471
LIAM: Well, let's put on the table what we're
doing here. Right? Kevdak has the Knuckles. We

02:50:52.471 --> 02:50:57.392
don't know where he is. He's probably pretty
formidable on his own. And in a day or two, a

02:50:57.392 --> 02:51:02.620
dragon is going to be swinging by, so it's not one
problem, it's a very large problem

02:51:02.620 --> 02:51:04.178
and a &lt;i&gt;massive&lt;/i&gt; problem.

02:51:04.178 --> 02:51:05.469
TRAVIS: Agreed.

02:51:05.469 --> 02:51:12.823
LAURA: I wonder if Kevdak goes to the sacrificial
area where they leave the hoard for the dragon.

02:51:12.823 --> 02:51:14.979
TALIESIN: I wouldn't.

02:51:14.979 --> 02:51:18.810
MARISHA: Or if he does rounds to check in on people.

02:51:18.810 --> 02:51:24.684
TALIESIN: I'll also say I think it's more than
likely that, in the end, I doubt the dragons would

02:51:24.684 --> 02:51:27.941
care who is filling the sacrificial plate.

02:51:27.941 --> 02:51:29.450
LAURA: As long as someone is.

02:51:29.450 --> 02:51:30.728
TALIESIN: As long as the plate's full.

02:51:30.728 --> 02:51:40.196
TRAVIS: As far as this city goes, correct me if
I'm wrong, but we have two options. Either we

02:51:40.196 --> 02:51:49.218
stealth in with the stealthy people, not me
included, and we try and pickpocket Kevdak for the

02:51:49.218 --> 02:51:56.203
Knuckles. Or I challenge Kevdak for the Knuckles.

02:51:56.203 --> 02:52:02.676
MARISHA: Is Kevdak known to ever wander off by
himself? Does he take interest in his subjects to

02:52:02.676 --> 02:52:04.338
where we could corner him alone?

02:52:04.338 --> 02:52:07.879
LAURA: Or is it a walk in and try to challenge
him?

02:52:07.879 --> 02:52:11.293
SAM: We could take out that guard, what was his
name, Cole or something?

02:52:11.293 --> 02:52:14.562
TRAVIS: Yeah, Cole was heading back to the city,
though.

02:52:14.562 --> 02:52:18.136
SAM: Well, we could find one of your goliath
friends, hold them hostage,

02:52:18.136 --> 02:52:20.251
and draw out Kevdak that way.

02:52:20.251 --> 02:52:23.539
TRAVIS: They won't care about a hostage.

02:52:23.539 --> 02:52:26.522
MARISHA: There also could be the issue of are they
going to go looking for Horace?

02:52:26.522 --> 02:52:30.865
TRAVIS: Maybe. Not that hard, though.

02:52:30.865 --> 02:52:37.177
SAM: We could do some sort of a diversion, set a
fire or something that would draw them out. Or set

02:52:37.177 --> 02:52:39.447
a fire to the house they live in.

02:52:39.447 --> 02:52:41.723
MARISHA: That's not a bad idea. What would bring
Kevdak out?

02:52:41.723 --> 02:52:43.736
TALIESIN: Grog. Grog would bring Kevdak out.

02:52:43.736 --> 02:52:44.918
MARISHA: Grog?

02:52:44.918 --> 02:52:48.211
SAM: Do you want to march in there, solo, while we
stealth--

02:52:48.211 --> 02:52:49.290
LAURA: &lt;i&gt;No!&lt;/i&gt;

02:52:49.290 --> 02:52:54.614
SAM: No, no, while we all stealth around in the
rooftops watching, ready to act.

02:52:54.614 --> 02:53:03.219
LIAM: Grog, I'm curious how tied you feel to the
ways of your people now, or if you do. Do you feel

02:53:03.219 --> 02:53:09.620
the need, yourself, to face him on your own, or
would you be amenable, would you be friendly to

02:53:09.620 --> 02:53:14.971
the idea of my sister and I softening him up for a
moment, and then letting you have at it? What do

02:53:14.971 --> 02:53:18.333
you want to do here?

02:53:18.333 --> 02:53:30.752
TRAVIS: So my fear is this: that if it's anyone
but me and him, everyone gets involved. Not just

02:53:30.752 --> 02:53:38.750
us, but all 60 of them in that stronghold. I don't
think we walk out of that very well. I'm not

02:53:38.750 --> 02:53:46.834
opposed to facing him head-on and seeing what fate
has in store for me while you free any prisoners

02:53:46.834 --> 02:53:53.093
that might be around, or ransacking his house for
any fun bits, but I think he's going to have the

02:53:53.093 --> 02:53:54.995
Knuckles on him.

02:53:54.995 --> 02:54:04.074
MARISHA: Question. Is your herd and Kevdak the
type where, if you start getting the upper hand in

02:54:04.074 --> 02:54:07.760
this fight, will the herd move to protect Kevdak?

02:54:07.760 --> 02:54:08.928
TRAVIS: No.

02:54:08.928 --> 02:54:15.114
MARISHA: So they'll honor a one-on-one fight?
They'll honor that? They won't pull a fast one and

02:54:15.114 --> 02:54:17.394
swarm in when he's on his last leg?

02:54:17.394 --> 02:54:23.937
SAM: Tell us this. If we walk in with you into
town, is that not good? Should you walk into town

02:54:23.937 --> 02:54:26.110
alone and we lurk in the shadows?

02:54:26.110 --> 02:54:31.358
MARISHA: Do you want to be on a hilltop, like
standing on a hilltop?

02:54:31.358 --> 02:54:33.363
Because we could arrange that.

02:54:33.363 --> 02:54:45.007
TRAVIS: I would need to think about it.
Regardless, I think now is not the time. Perhaps

02:54:45.007 --> 02:54:48.588
we go look for Osysa's mate.

02:54:48.588 --> 02:54:51.798
SAM: You don't want to do this now? It seems like
now or never!

02:54:51.798 --> 02:54:55.415
MARISHA: We know where Kevdak is, he doesn't seem
to be going anywhere.

02:54:55.415 --> 02:54:57.632
SAM: We may not know where he is after this.

02:54:57.632 --> 02:55:03.115
TRAVIS: He seems pretty fortified. And we don't
have Pike. And this is her hometown.

02:55:03.115 --> 02:55:06.435
MARISHA: Judging by the-- no, I didn't hear any of
that.

02:55:06.435 --> 02:55:12.178
LIAM: I want to throw something in here as well.
